title: rotel tomatoes
directions: Cook all ingredients together until tomatoes will mash easy. Fill jars and seal.
Cold pack for 25 minutes.
Makes 9 pints.

title: chocolate bonbons
directions: Combine butter, sugar, milk, nuts and coconut.
Mix well. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on baking sheet.
Chill until firm.

title: three pounds butter from one pound
directions: Take a generous amount of self-respect.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt margarine and mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Press into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan or Pyrex dish.
Whip 3 packages of cream cheese, which have been softened with 2 cups sugar.
Spread over graham cracker mixture.
Slice bananas and place over cream cheese mixture.
Spread medium can of crushed, drained pineapple over bananas.
Thaw 12 ounces Cool Whip and spread over pineapple. Sprinkle nuts and cherries over top.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the sugar, butter and eggs.
Add vanilla, buttermilk, flour, baking powder, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Drop on floured cookie sheet.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pineapple into 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Pour cherry pie filling over pineapple.
Sprinkle cake mix directly from box over cherry filling.
Spread pecans over cake.
Cover cake with a thin layer of butter.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Top with whipped cream, if desired.
Yield:
12 to 15 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: In bowl, beat eggs, syrup, sugar, butter and extract.
Stir in pecans.
Pour in pie shell. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix ingredients well; add eggs one at a time.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: brer rabbit barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Use for basting or pour over chicken, ribs, hamburger, etc.
Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Put a tight lid on berries and water and cook until all of the cranberries have popped.
Add the pinch of soda and skim quickly. Add sugar and simmer.
Mix cornstarch in cold water and cook a few minutes.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in their skins until tender.
Peel and slice thinly into bowl.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Cook the onoin in bacon fat in the skillet until yellow.
Mix in flour, salt, sugar, celery seed and pepper.
Stir in water and vinegar gradually.
Cook, stirring until mixture boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Pour over potatoes. Add the crisp bacon, broken into pieces.
Cover and let stand until ready to serve.
Heat over hot water.
Serve in a large bowl, garnished with parsley or chives.
Serves 6. Yummy!

title: applesauce bread or muffins
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients; set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°. Lightly grease 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Cream butter and sugar in large bowl.
Beat in applesauce and eggs.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in oats, nuts and raisins.
Pour into loaf pan and bake until bread is golden (for 55 to 60 minutes).
Cool slightly in pan; remove and cool on rack.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Add and mix in order given.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef - bean casserole
directions: While you are browning meat and onion, mix the remaining ingredients, then add all together.
Put into casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 to 2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cookies for a crowd
directions: Mix sugars, shortening, eggs and vanilla in an extra large bowl until smooth.
Mix flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Stir both mixtures together until smooth and then add oatmeal and chocolate chips.
Use ice cream scoop to measure mixture and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for approximately 14 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Sprinkle gelatine over orange juice and warm over low heat until dissolved.
I use blender to chop cranberries.
Add sugar and let set 15 minutes.
Add apples, celery and pecans to cranberry mix; add gelatin mix, stir and pour into mold.
(Better to fix a day ahead of time.)

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook chopped onion and pepper with hamburger.
Put macaroni (drained) in bottom of dish and put hamburger mixture on top.
Mix tomato and mushroom soup, peas and saucer together.
Pour over mixture.
Put cheese on top and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil, eggs and pumpkin together.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon.
Pour into a 9 x 13 cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sourdough pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Cook as you would normal pancakes.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook fettuccine noodles as directed on box; return to dry pot.

title: baked potato soup
directions: In a large pot, cover potatoes with water and boil until tender.
Mix soups and milk and add to potatoes and water.
When potatoes are tender, stir well.
Add cubed cheese.
Simmer on low. Season to taste with salt, pepper and Tabasco sauce (optional). Stir often and watch carefully.
It will stick easily.
Great as a main course.
Serves 4 to 6 adults.

title: vinegar pie(year 1917)
directions: Put water, vinegar and egg yolks on stove to heat while you mix flour and sugar together.
Add to mixture on stove and cook until thick.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix all
ingredients, except the Hershey bar, chocolate chips and paraffin,
and	shape
into
balls.
Melt
one 8 1/2 ounce Hershey bar with the chocolate chips and paraffin in top of double boiler.
Dip
balls
in chocolate mixture and lay on wax paper to dry.

title: buffalo chips cookies
directions: Melt together:
shortening and butter.
Blend in:
brown sugar, white sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Mix together and add to above: flour, baking soda, baking powder.
Then add:
uncooked oatmeal, bran or corn flakes, pecans or Walnuts to taste, coconut, chocolate chips and peanut butter or butterscotch chips.
Use a LARGE bowl to mix the ingredients.
Add a little extra of all ingredients for good measure.
Use ice cream scoop to measure out cookies (about 1/4 cup each).
Place 6 cookies per sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes very large cookies.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix water and sugar in a pan;
bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; stir in fruit juice
and
bananas.
Pour
in	large container; freeze until firm.
When
ready	to
serve,
remove from freezer and let set at room temperature; add ginger ale.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Use less water to dissolve Jell-O.

title: spinach cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: mama's old-fashioned egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs with salt.
Add sugar and flour sifted together. Stir in milk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese and egg souffle
directions: Grease a large casserole dish, put alternating layers of bread and cheese.
Mix the other ingredients and pour over cheese and bread.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Put in cold oven.

title: smores-over the fire
directions: Put a marshmallow on a stick.
Stick over the fire.
When you think it is done, take it out.
Put chocolate on graham cracker, then put marshmallow on the graham cracker.

title: strawberry topping
directions: Measure the 1 cup strawberries after hulling and mashing. Place in bowl.
Add the sugar, egg white and salt.
Beat with electric mixer for 7 to 10 minutes, until mixture forms peaks. Use over sliced cake.
Makes 8 servings.

title: summer sunset slaw
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients and chill.

title: ranch treat
directions: Divide chips into 4 small bowls.
Heat beans until they come to boil.
Spoon equally over chips.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cinnamon loaf
directions: Cream 2 cups sugar and oil together.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift flour and baking powder and add to creamed mixture.
Add 1 cup milk; mix well.
Use well-greased loaf pans.
Mix cinnamon and 3 tablespoons sugar together.
Now alternate batter and cinnamon/sugar mixture 3 times.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Cool.
Makes 2 large loaves or 1 large and 2 small loaves.

title: company casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add sauce, oregano and basil.
In bowl, mix sour cream, cream cheese and onion.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan half the noodles, then the cheese soup and other half of the noodles.
Pour meat sauce over the top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mom's lebkuchens
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill overnight.
Roll out in rectangle 1/4 inch thick, no less.
Cut with pizza cutter.

title: mexican chicken(a gephart favorite)
directions: In a crock-pot or 9 x 13-inch baking dish, mix soup, tomatoes and green chilies.
Layer chicken, soup mixture, Doritos and cheese (2 layers) and end with cheese.
Cook on high for 1 hour in crock-pot or bake at 350° for 20 minutes (in 9 x 13-inch baking dish).
Top with sour cream and salsa.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix cream cheese and Blue cheese together in bowl.
Stir in celery and onions.
Chill for 2 hours.
Remove and shape into log. Refrigerate once more.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In a dish blend soup, milk, mustard and pepper.
Stir in cooked macaroni and 1 1/2 cups Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until hot.
Take out of oven and stir.
Top with onions and remaining cheese. Bake until cheese melts, about 5 to 10 minutes more.

title: nacho dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and sour cream.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in bean dip, chili seasoning mix, hot sauce, taco sauce, 3/4 cup Cheddar cheese and 3/4 cup Jack cheese.
Place in casserole dish and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: baked cranberry relish
directions: Place cranberries and sugar in shallow baking dish.
Cover tightly with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove from oven and stir in nuts, marmalade and lemon juice.
Chill and serve.

title: perfect apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, spices and dash of salt; mix with apples.
Line 9-inch pie crust with apple mixture.
Dot with butter.
Cut slits in top crust.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Place seeded
peppers and vinegar in food processor and finely chop.
Add this to sugar in heavy 5-quart pan; bring to boil for 3 minutes.
Remove
from
heat.
Let
stand	for
20 minutes to clear.
Skim
and
remove
heavy
pulp.
Return
to heat; boil 2 more
minutes.
Remove from heat, add pectin and mix
well.
Pour into sterilized jars and refrigerate.
Makes 3 1/2 cups jelly.

title: green beans, basilicata style
directions: Wash beans and break off ends.

Leave whole or cut as desired. Add 1 teaspoon salt to boiling water. Stir in beans; cover and bring to boiling. Cook 10 minutes or until crisp-tender. While beans are cooking, saute onion in olive oil until transparent (about 8 minutes). When beans are done cooking, drain and add to onion. Season with salt and pepper. Add mint leaves and vinegar. Toss gently. Serve while still hot.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: creamy pear freeze
directions: Blend cream
cheese, lemon juice, sugar, mayonnaise and salt. Add pears,
avocado
and
cherries.
Fold	in
whipped cream. Pour into
refrigerator tray.
Freeze about 6 hours or until firm. Let
stand
at
room
temperature before serving. Makes refreshing summer
salad (or dessert) with sandwiches or crackers.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.
Keeps several weeks. Good on hot dog and bun.

title: quick guacamole
directions: Mash the avocado.
Stir in cottage cheese and picante sauce. Add jalapeno pepper if desired.
Serve with tortilla chips or vegetables.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: asparagus-english pea casserole
directions: Butter bottom and sides of a casserole dish.
Sprinkle some cracker crumbs in bottom; then add alternately asparagus, cheese, cracker crumbs, half of asparagus juice and mushroom soup.
Then add onion salt and pepper.
Next, layer peas, cheese, cracker crumbs, etc. in same order.
The top layer of cheese is a bit thicker.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 2-quart casserole dish. In a medium bowl, combine the flour, sugar and milk. Beat with wire whisk. Carefully pour mixture in center of melted butter. DO NOT STIR. Pour peaches (with juice) in center of batter mix. DO NOT STIR. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients together except nuts and apples.
Add these last.
Bake in a tube or Bundt cake pan at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: apple butter cake
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Beat until fluffy.
Stir in 1 cup apple butter.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add sour milk to batter alternately with sifted ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased and floured round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes; cool.

title: easy rhubarb pie
directions: Crust:
Mix together the flour, oil and milk right in pie pan. Reserve 1/2 cup of mixture.
Pat the remaining crust into pie plate and up the edges.

title: swiss steak
directions: Hammer steak to tenderize.
Flour each side and brown with onions.
Add water and bouillon cubes.
Cook 2 hours.
Make gravy from pan drippings.

title: taco-filled peppers
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Stir in taco seasoning and drained kidney beans and salsa.
Simmer 3 to 5 minutes.
Cut peppers in half and clean.
Immerse in boiling water for 2 minutes. Drain.
Fill with meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, covered.
Top with chopped tomatoes, shredded Cheddar cheese and sour cream (optional).
Serves 4.

title: johnny appleseed tea
directions: Bring 1 quart water to boil; add tea bags.
Remove from heat. Cover and let steep for 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags.
Add remaining ingredients (the extra quart of water as well).
Cook over low heat until thoroughly heated.
Serve hot.
Makes 9 cups.

title: brownies
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 25 minutes.

title: cottage cheese meat loaf
directions: Combine the beef, cottage cheese, egg, rolled oats, catsup, mustard, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix lightly until well blended. Press the mixture loosely into a shallow baking pan (about 8-inch square).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 muffin cups.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar.
Separate biscuit dough in greased muffin cups, pressing dough to cover bottom and sides.
Spoon meat mixture into each cup.
Sprinkle each with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Loosen with spatula and remove from pan.
Serve immediately.

title: latkes(potato pancakes)
directions: Mix the ingredients in a bowl.
Drop the mixture by tablespoon into hot oil in an electric skillet.
Brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Stir grated potatoes immediately into milk. Add other ingredients. Drop by spoonfuls into greased frying pan and cook slowly until browned and crisp on both sides.

title: one-rise monkey bread
directions: Grease a 12-cup fluted pan (Bundt pan) or a 10-inch tube pan. In a large bowl, blend 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt, yeast, water, margarine and egg at low speed until moistened.
Beat mixture 3 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in remaining flour by hand.
Knead dough on a floured surface until smooth, about 1 minute.
Press or roll dough to 15 x 12-inch rectangle.
Using a sharp knife, cut dough into diamond shape pieces by cutting 2-inch strips diagonally both ways across dough.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat between each.
Add vanilla and lemon extracts.
Mix well.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda.
Add dry ingredients to mixture alternating with sour cream.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Crumble breads and add all ingredients except margarine. Pour into crock-pot and dot with margarine.
Cook on high 3 hours, or on low 3 to 4 hours.
Stir halfway through.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Slowly add other ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until it coats spoon, stirring constantly. Cool.
If you want to stretch it, add 1/2 cup Miracle Whip.
Pour over cold cooked cubed potatoes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Combine meat, green pepper, chili powder and oregano. Cook until meat browns.
Drain.
Remove from heat. Add soup, water, sauce and garlic salt.
In a 9 x 13-inch greased pan, layer tortillas, meat, cheese and end with meat on top.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with sour cream and taco sauce.
Let set for awhile.

title: patty's taco salad
directions: Brown ground turkey and add taco seasoning.
Drain and set aside.
Mix all ingredients together with meat and serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Mix half the flour and all the cinnamon; coat pork thoroughly with mixture.
Heat oil in electric skillet; brown pork and remove when browned.
Add water to reserved pineapple syrup to measure 1 3/4 cups; gradually stir into remaining flour.
Stir pineapple syrup mixture, vinegar, soy sauce and Worcestershire into fat in skillet.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 2 minutes.
Stir in sugar, salt, pepper and meat.

title: magnificent minestrone
directions: Saute onion, parsley, spinach, garlic and herbs in olive oil until tender.
Mix all ingredients except the wine, soy sauce and Parmesan cheese. Simmer covered for 1 hour, then stir in wine, soy sauce and Parmesan cheese before serving.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: Combine the first four ingredients.
Cut the Milky Way bars into small pieces.
Pour one cup of the milk mixture into the bowl of Milky Way pieces and put into the microwave to melt.
When the candy is melted, pour that mixture along with the rest of the milk mixture into the ice cream freezer.
Add the 1/2 gallon of milk to make 1 gallon.
Freeze.

title: haddock casserole
directions: Put shrimp over haddock in baking pan. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over shrimp.
Sprinkle flour, salt and pepper.
Dot with oleo or butter. Add milk. Sprinkle dry bread crumbs over top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sloppy joe biscuit bake
directions: In a large skillet, cook ground beef and onion over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain. Add Sloppy Joe mix, spaghetti and tomato sauce and heat. Transfer to a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with cheeses. Pull biscuit layers apart and place a thin layer over top of cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: saucy jello
directions: Heat applesauce to boiling.
Add lemon juice and simmer 10 to 15 minutes, until very thick.
Add cherry Jell-O powder and stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat and stir in walnuts.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan which has been rinsed with cold water.
Cool to room temperature and refrigerate until set.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Can be dusted with powdered sugar.
Makes about 64 squares.

title: steak soup
directions: Brown meat and drain off fat.
Place carrots, celery, onion, water, salt and pepper in a large kettle.
Boil 5 minutes.
Drain and save liquid.
Drain tomatoes and add liquid to vegetable liquid. Melt butter in the kettle. Stir in flour gradually. Add vegetable liquid, stirring constantly.
Add bovril, Worcestershire sauce, Accent and ketchup. Combine meat, vegetables and tomatoes with sauce.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Add frozen vegetables and simmer 10 minutes more.
Freezes well!

title: tex mex dip
directions: In large shallow dish, spread bean dip.
Mash avocados with small amount lemon juice.
Combine mayonnaise and sour cream with avocados.
Add taco seasoning.
Pour on top of bean dip.
Chop tomatoes and onions and layer on top of avocado mixture.
Top with remaining layers of olives, cheese and peppers.
Serve with chips.

title: knusezcyki(strip cakes)
directions: Add salt to eggs and beat until thick and lemon colored.
Add sugar and flavoring and continue to beat.
Add sour cream and flour alternately, mixing well after each addition.
Knead on board. Cut small pieces of dough.
Roll very thin and cut into strips about 4 inches long.
Slit each piece in center and pull one end through the slit.
Deep fry in hot fat until lightly browned. Drain on paper towel and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Mix together after browning meat and draining noodles.
Let set for 4 hours.
Cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: dip for fish or vegetables
directions: Beat milk and egg in glass or metal bowl.
Beat flour, shortening and salt in glass or metal bowl.
Then beat both mixtures together.
Roll fish or vegetables in flour and dip in batter.
Fry in hot oil.
You can refrigerate up to 3 weeks.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes; place in cold water.
Use equal parts of flour and cheese and salt to taste.
Put in a bag; shake to coat.

title: mayonnaise biscuit
directions: Combine all ingredients together. Fill muffin tins, bake at 400° until brown. Makes approximately 1 dozen.

title: strawberry stuff
directions: Combine strawberries and glaze and set aside.
Slice cake thin.
Mix topping of Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan in this order:
topping, strawberry mix, cake, topping and strawberry mix.
Continue until all is gone. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chicken and noodle soup
directions: Cook chicken legs in 1 1/2 quarts of water.
When done, remove skin and bones.
Put meat in pot, add seasoning salt, pepper and bouillon.
Cook celery and carrots separate from broth.
Drain water.
Add to stock.
Cook noodles until almost done.
Drain. Rinse in cold water.
Add to broth.
Serve.

title: electric skillet date nut balls
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients all together at 300° for 6 minutes. Pour over Rice Krispies and nuts.

title: sour cream dessert
directions: Cream together.
Press crust into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Melt butter or margarine in pan in oven. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add eggs and pulp.
Mix well.
Pour in melted butter or margarine and mix well.
Pour into 1 very large pan or 4 small ones.
Bake at 300° for 1/2 hour or longer.
Cool in pan. Cut in small squares or rectangles.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt
margarine in a deep casserole.
Sprinkle 1/2 package Pepperidge Farm cornbread stuffing mix in bottom of dish.
Add chicken (cut in bite size pieces),
chopped celery, peas and 1 can cream of mushroom soup.
Cover with the rest of the stuffing mix and pour chicken broth over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: clam-corn soup
directions: In large kettle, saute leeks and/or onions in butter until tender. Add celery, potatoes, chicken stock and dried corn.

Bring to a boil, then cover; reduce heat and simmer gently for 30 minutes or until corn is done. Add clams, seasoning, dry milk and whole milk. Heat to boiling point and gently simmer for a few minutes. Add hard-boiled eggs a few minutes before serving. Adjust milk to desired consistency.

title: cousin angie's fettucini alfredo
directions: Heat all ingredients until smooth and bubbling.
Serve over fettucini noodles.

title: pressed cookies
directions: Sift together the flour and salt; set aside.
Blend margarine and sugar.
Beat in egg yolk and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture. Put through cookie press.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.
Makes 50 cookies.

title: ham ball
directions: Dice 1/2 sandwich meat.
Cut green onions into small pieces. Mix thoroughly with cream cheese and shape into a ball.
Dice last 1/2 of ham and cover ball with it.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: apple cinnamon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend together cake, pie filling and eggs in a large bowl.
Beat 2 minutes.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 10-inch Bundt pan or tube pan. Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, water and oil in large bowl. Beat at medium speed with electric mixer for 2 minutes. Pour into pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan 25 minutes. Invert onto serving plate. Cool. Sprinkle powdered sugar on top of cooled cake.

title: russian tea
directions: *If unsweetened juice used, add another cup of sugar.

title: powdered sugar pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and eggs.
Add flour and then desired flavor of extract.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour and 25 minutes in greased and floured tube pan.
Cool 15 minutes in pan and then invert onto platter.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles per directions on box; mix tuna, green pepper, onion and celery.
Toss with Walden Farms fat-free Thousand Island dressing.
Serve chilled.
Less than 1 gram of fat in this recipe.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken breasts into small nugget sized pieces (deboning it).
Mix buttermilk and meat tenderizer together in a bowl.
Put flour in a separate bowl.
Wash chicken thoroughly.
Dip chicken in buttermilk mixture and then roll in flour (add salt and pepper to flour if desired).
Pour Wesson oil in frying pan and heat. Place floured chicken pieces in hot oil and fry until golden brown (turning as necessary).
Drain on paper towel and serve while hot. Serves approximately 6.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix above ingredients well.
Put in a 9 x 9-inch pan lined with the following:
1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/4 cup margarine (melted).
If desired, sprinkle the top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: apple raisin oven pancake
directions: Mix eggs, 1 teaspoon sugar and Bisquick; mix well.
In a 10-inch ovenproof skillet or casserole, saute apples and raisins in butter until tender.
Remove from heat.
Pour batter over apples and raisins.
Combine remaining sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over batter.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes at 450° or until set in center. Serve with syrup.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: taco mix dip
directions: Make layers in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sherry steaks
directions: Dredge steaks in flour.
Pan-fry in butter, then add mushrooms with liquid.
Cook 5 minutes, covered.
Add lemon juice and sherry and cook an additional 20 minutes or until steaks are very tender.

title: cheese-potato soup
directions: Heat potatoes, onions, carrots, bouillon and water to boiling. Cover and cook until potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes.
With potatoes, onions and carrots still in water, mash them with a potato masher.
Add cheese slowly, stirring until it's all melted. Serves 6 to 8.

title: fudge swirl cookies
directions: Stir yellow cake mix, egg, oil and water.
Take 1/3 of yellow mixture and swirl together with chocolate packet, then put back into yellow mixture.
(Don't stir too much, you want to maintain that swirled look!)
Fold in milk chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° on greased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes.
Should come out nice and gooey!

title: cranapple relish
directions: Quarter and seed orange and apples.
Coarsely grind cranberries, orange and apples in a food grinder or blender.
Add sugar, pineapple and pecans; mix well.
Refrigerate overnight. Yields 2 quarts.
Freezes well.

title: cauliflower-broccoli salad
directions: In a 2-quart bowl, break cauliflower and broccoli into bite size pieces.
Combine with green pepper and onion.
Stir together remaining ingredients and pour vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer the ingredients in order listed:
lettuce, celery, red or green pepper, red onion and peas.
Spread mayonnaise on top of peas to seal.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Top with shredded cheese. Cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight. Before serving, top with freshly made bacon pieces.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Fry meats and drain good.
Add seasonings and cheese.
Mix. Spread on small loaf rye bread (or plain) and bake at 350° until hot through and through.

title: vegetable barley salad
directions: In
a large saucepan bring water to a boil.
Add barley and bouillon
granules.
Return
to
boiling;
reduce
heat. Simmer, covered
for 10 to 12 minutes or until tender.
Drain well	and rinse
with cold water and drain again.
In a large mixing	bowl, stir
together drained barley, cucumber, red or green
pepper, green
onion
and
herbs.
In a screw top jar, combine
oil, lemon peel, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Cover and
shake
well.
Pour over
barley
mixture,
toss to coat. Season
to
taste
with additional salt and pepper.
Cover and chill in refrigerator several hours or overnight.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly and put in airtight container.
For a richer mix, add 1/3 cup powdered nondairy creamer and/or a tablespoon or 2 or malted milk powder to the mixture.
To use, put about 4 tablespoons of the mix (or to taste) into a cup of boiling water.
Add a dash of whipped topping or vanilla ice cream, if desired.

title: gourmet microwave popcorn
directions: Will need a microwave popping bowl (get at Wal-Mart).

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: If spices are too much for your taste, use 1/2 teaspoon of each.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: brenda's chicken and yellow rice
directions: Boil or pressure cook chicken with salt, pepper, garlic salt and onions until done.
Set chicken aside to cool, then take chicken off bones.
Boil yellow rice mixture in 3 cups of chicken broth for 15 to 20 minutes until rice is done.
Add jar of pimentos, then add deboned chicken and stir until well mixed. (Yields 10 servings.)

title: toodie nistler's cobbler
directions: Mix fruit with 1 cup of sugar.
Let stand.
Place butter in 2-quart casserole in oven at 325°.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk and pour over melted butter.
Do not stir. Spoon fruit over top.
Do not stir.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.

title: turtle candy
directions: Melt the chocolate morsels.
Add the nuts and raisins to the melted chocolate, until not much chocolate is left.
Drop onto wax paper by teaspoonfuls until set.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 2-quart casserole.
Lightly pepper mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour, stir occasionally.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine in the top of a double boiler.
Cook, covered, over boiling water until rice is tender and milk is almost absorbed, about 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: crustless crab quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute mushrooms in butter.
Drain on paper towels.
In food processor or blender, process next seven ingredients.
Pour mixture into large bowl and stir in mushrooms, cheese and crabmeat.
Fold into a 10-inch quiche dish and bake 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder and milk.
Add to margarine.
Spoon fruit on top.
Do not stir.
Sprinkle second cup of sugar on top.
If you desire, you can sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: linguine carbonara
directions: Saute onion in olive oil until soft.
Add garlic and saute again.
Add bacon.
Beat eggs in a small bowl and add cheese. Toss all in cooked linguine and simmer for 10 minutes before serving.

title: oat cake snacks
directions: Mix together oatmeal, flour, sugar, soda and salt in large bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add cold water to mixture, one tablespoon at a time, until mixture forms a ball and holds together.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Place a small amount of cornmeal or flour on a clean counter.
Divide dough into two balls.
Roll each ball of dough into a rectangle about 1/4-inch thick on the "floured" counter.
Cut each rectangle into 3-inch squares.
Place the squares on a cookie sheet and bake 15 to 20 minutes or until brown on top.
Store in an airtight container.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute peppers and onion in butter until tender.
In 1-quart baking dish, blend soup, sour cream and remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chicken in a pot
directions: Put half of carrots, onions and celery in bottom of crock-pot. Add chicken.
Top with salt, pepper, liquid and remaining half of the vegetables.
Sprinkle basil over top.
Cover and cook until done, either on low for 7 to 10 hours or on high for 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 hours.

title: plain cookies
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Sift into large bowl the flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add and mix well the shortening, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet and bake.

title: italian casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice sausage and brown in skillet.
Add tomato sauce, mushrooms, onion and spices.
Add 2 cups of water. Simmer until done.

title: carol's carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs well and mix in oil and sugar.
Mix together flour, soda, cinnamon and salt and add to egg mixture.
Add carrots and mix well.
Pour into three 9 x 1-inch greased cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until tests done.
Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Mix in large bowl and set aside.

title: meat sauce
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
Very good with beef.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and add sugar one cup at a time. Add flavoring and mix real good. Add eggs one at a time, then add flour, one cup at a time.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Brown hamburger and diced onion; drain grease.
Remove from heat and add 1 can tomato soup, rice and Parmesan cheese.
Split and clean out peppers; stuff.
Heat other can tomato soup, chili powder and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over stuffed peppers. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken & rice casserole
directions: Melt 2 sticks of butter, mix rice & water in butter with the can of soup. Place rice & chicken in a baking dish and pour soup and water on top of chicken and add onion soup mix on top. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water. Add cream cheese. Blend well with mixer.
Add crushed pineapple with juice. Fold in Cool Whip.
Best if chilled overnight.
Garnish with mandarin oranges.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Cook meat.
Add onion, pepper, tomato sauce and spices. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Cook noodles and put noodles in pan.
Pour meat mixture over noodles. Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with mushrooms.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Serve after 1 hour in refrigerator to blend flavors.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and flour together.
Add beaten eggs, milk, vanilla and coconut.
Melt butter and add to mixture.
Stir.
(Can refrigerate at this point.)
Pour into unbaked pie shells 2 deep-dish pie crusts.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300°.
Cook until golden brown and set.
Let cool.
Makes 2 pies.

title: chicken sauté
directions: Put everything in skillet and cook for about 30 minutes.
Can try with one can of mushroom.

title: brisket of beef mo
directions: Trim most of the fat from the meat.
Sprinkle meat generously with tenderizer, liquid smoke, salt and pepper.

title: golden glow salad
directions: In bowl dissolve Jell-O and water.
Stir in lemon juice and salt and add enough cold water to pineapple juice to make 1 cup, then add to mixture.
Chill slightly until set.
Stir in pineapple and carrots.
Pour into 4 cup mold (oiled).
Cover and chill until firm.
Unmold to serve.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased bread pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: ranch chicken breasts
directions: Whisk juice and dressing mix together.
Marinate chicken in half the juice mixture for 2 to 24 hours.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Combine cornstarch, water and remaining juice mixture in pan.
Heat to thicken.
Brush chicken with sauce.
Serves 4.

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
In medium saucepan, melt chocolate and shortening over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Mix sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Bake until brownies start to pull away from sides of pan, about 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Cut into 2 x 2-inch squares.

title: italian chicken marengo
directions: Heat 2 teaspoons oil in skillet; brown chicken on both sides. Remove chicken.
Add remaining oil, mushrooms, onion and garlic; saute until tender.
Add tomatoes, 1/2 cup broth, thyme, salt and pepper; return chicken to skillet.
Cover; simmer for 10 to 12 minutes, until chicken is cooked.
Whisk together the flour and remaining broth.
Remove chicken; keep warm.
Stir flour mixture into skillet until mixture thickens and boils.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Boil noodles 8 minutes; drain.
Grease dish.
Put noodles, tuna and beans in dish.
Pour soup over ingredients.
Add bread on top.
Pour oleo over bread.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie(from 1975 edition)
directions: Mix sugar, salt and flour.
Add egg yolks which are slightly beaten, buttermilk, margarine and vanilla.
Blend well.
Beat egg whites until they hold a peak.
Fold into custard mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 325° for 30 minutes or until pie is golden brown and knife inserted comes out clean.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel
potatoes and boil 20 minutes.
They should not be too soft.
Half in lengthwise; place in baking dish.
In a pan boil together
the butter, water, corn syrup and brown sugar. Pour syrup
mixture
over
potatoes and baste often.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until glazed.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Pull chicken off bones.
Grease bottom of baking pan.
Put chips in bottom of dish; place chicken on top of chips.
Add chopped onion.
Cover with both kinds of soups.
Top with pepper and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in their jackets.
Boil eggs.
Meanwhile, fry bacon and crumble.
After potatoes are cooked, saute onion in bacon grease until golden brown.
Blend in flour and seasonings. Remove from heat.
Pour in water and vinegar.
Place on medium heat and bring to a boil.
Pour sauce over sliced eggs, potatoes and bacon.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Precook chicken with onion and celery until almost done.
Cook broccoli and arrange in bottom of 11 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, milk, lemon juice, Miracle Whip and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Combine 1 cup bread crumbs and butter in blender and spread on top.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: meat shell potato pie
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 can soup, beef, onion, egg, bread crumbs, parsley and salt.
Press meat mixture firmly into 9-inch pie plate or 8 x 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Spoon off excess fat.
Frost with potatoes.
Top with remaining soup.
Mix together bacon and cheese and sprinkle over the top. Bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: barbecue sauce for spareribs
directions: Combine all. Baste meat while broiling or use for braising. Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix and sift flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and baking soda. Cut in butter. Add milk and egg. Knead until looks like coarse cornmeal. Stir in raisins. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Rinse and drain kraut.
Add all ingredients. Mix and let marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Improves with age.

title: pork-n-beans casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion in skillet; drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: molded cranberry salad
directions: In a small pan, heat orange juice to boiling; add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Stir in cranberries and stir until well combined.
Stir in celery and nuts.
Pour into a mold and chill until slightly firm.
Make the second layer by dissolving lime Jell-O in boiling water.
Blend in mayonnaise; pour over first layer and top with marshmallows.

title: fiesta corn bread salad
directions: Combine salad dressing mix, sour cream and mayonnaise; set aside.
Place half of the crumbled corn bread in bottom of a large serving bowl.
Top with half of chili beans.
Combine tomatoes, bell pepper and onions.
Layer half of mixture over beans.
Layer half of cheese, bacon, corn and reserved salad dressing mixture. Repeat layers using remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Serves 10.

title: tapioca and jello dessert
directions: Open up tapioca and Jell-O powders and put in saucepan.
Add 3 cups cold water. Bring to a boil, stirring frequently, until it thickens 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Fold in Cool Whip and drained fruit.
You can substitute different flavors of Jell-O as well as the fruit.

title: date pudding
directions: Cream shortening, sugars and eggs together. Put dates in a small bowl and sprinkle in the soda and add the hot water.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Pour melted butter into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix together milk, flour and sugar.
Pour into dish and top with peaches (undrained).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lois's beef stroganoff
directions: Saute garlic and mushrooms in margarine and wine.
Remove mushrooms and garlic; brown meat.
Add bouillon and water to meat and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in catsup; mix 1/3 cup bouillon mix and flour until smooth; stir into meat. Boil 1 minute to thicken; add mushrooms and garlic.
Stir in 1 cup sour cream; serve over noodles.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: Cook and bone 3 large chicken breasts; shred into 1-inch pieces.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients together. Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake 325° for 35-45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli until tender.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Saute onion and celery in butter.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add soup, mushrooms, cheese and 1/2 cup bread crumbs.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish over broccoli spears.
Sprinkle with remaining bread crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Serves 10.

title: fried rice
directions: Fry pork, beef or chicken in oil until brown. Add green pepper and onion. Stir and fry 2 to 3 minutes.
Add cooked rice and continue cooking 5 to 7 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add egg, green onions and soy sauce.
Stir into rice and cook until done, 3 to 4 minutes.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Combine
all ingredients into a large skillet and stir. Heat until carrots are glazed.
Can be done in oven.

title: amaretto bread pudding
directions: Break up bread into small pieces.
Place in a bowl and cover with the milk.
Cover bowl and let stand for 1 hour.

title: grandma's pound cake
directions: Beat yolks and whites of eggs separately; cream butter and cream sugar into it. Add egg yolks and mix well. Add stiff egg whites alternately with flour. Long beating of air into this mixture is the success of this cake according to Grandma. Grandma always beat the mixture by hand in a large wooden mixing bowl. Pour mixture into a greased cake pan and place into a moderate oven (325° to 350°) for 1 to 2 hours.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: To prepare, heat pan.
Add oil and garlic, Brown garlic and remove from oil.
Add steak and fry a few minutes.
Add ginger, salt and pepper then add green peppers and onion.
Mix well with steak, add 1 c of bouillon.
Mix together soy sauce, corn starch and water add to meat and onions.
When sauce thickens, remove from heat.
Serve with rice.

title: pineapple icebox cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Fold in eggs without beating.
Stir in pineapple.
Grind or crush vanilla wafers and alternate with pineapple mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts and place in refrigerator to harden.
Serve with whipped cream (optional).

title: taco salad
directions: Serve with cold poached salmon or other fish.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Grease an 8 or 9-inch deep dish pie plate.
Mix together, by hand, the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, margarine and egg. Pat half the mixture into the prepared pan.
Top with blueberries sprinkled with cinnamon and sugar.
By hand, make crumbs with the remaining mixture and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. When cool, add powdered sugar.

title: portuguese tortillas
directions: Slightly crush layer of chips in buttered shallow dish so it will not be too thick.
Put on Ro-Tel tomatoes (without juice) and then cheese.
Bake at 375° only until cheese melts and all is bubbly and hot.
Serve with salad for light meal.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta a required.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Rinse cilantro and remove large stems.
Finely chop cilantro leaves, tomatoes and onion; mix in a bowl.
Squeeze lemon or lime juice into mixture and add salt.
Add jalapeno, chopped fine, if desired.
Serve cold with grilled chicken or beef.

title: wassail punch
directions: Bring water and sugar to boil.
Put cinnamon and cloves in cheesecloth.
Add spices to sugar-water mixture.
Let boil 10 minutes.
Cool for at least one hour.
Add 1 1/2 gallons of apple juice or cider, 12 ounces orange juice concentrate and fifth rum. Heat, but do not boil.
Store in bottles.
Serve warm.
Do not heat or store in aluminum.

title: low-fat yogurt dill dip
directions: Combine ingredients in a bowl at least 3 hours before using. Store in refrigerator during this time to keep firm.

title: seven minute micro bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cukes medium thin.
Mix all ingredients and microwave on High for 3 1/2 minutes. Stir well and microwave for 3 1/2 more minutes. Cool in refrigerator until crisp.
Put in jars and store in refrigerator.

title: pinwheels
directions: Mix cream cheese and Ranch dressing.
Spread over flour tortillas.
Sprinkle with remaining ingredients as desired.
Roll and slice.
Secure with toothpicks.
Serve with salsa.

title: mexican driver
directions: Mix the first 5
ingredients
in a large pitcher.
Fill tall glasses with ice;
pour
orange
juice
mixture over ice. Garnish drinks with orange slices and serve.

title: low-fat cake
directions: Mix cake mix and drink with mixer for 2 1/2 minutes.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Bring milk, sugar, vanilla and butter to a full boil.
Turn heat back to medium or low and boil for 7 minutes, then add marshmallows and peanut butter with mixer until thick.
Pour into pan; don't stir much!!

title: tuna dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together and serve.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni and cook until done.
Drain.
Beat in 1 tablespoon margarine.
In separate dish beat 1 egg and fill saucer with milk.
Beat together and add macaroni and cheese.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: roasted onions and potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine all ingredients in large roasting pan.
Toss well.
Bake until potatoes are crisp and golden brown, stirring occasionally, about 1 hour and 10 minutes. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: party sandwich filling
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Use as filling between lightly buttered slices of sandwich bread.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water until tender; drain.
Add soup, egg, mayonnaise and onion.
Stir well and pour into greased casserole pan.
Spread crushed crackers on top.
Bake at 350° until heated completely.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients into a bowl and mix well.
Press together into a loaf the mixture and put into a baking dish.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool 5 minutes, then serve.

title: dutch cake
directions: Add all ingredients to egg and mix.
Grease a 9-inch layer cake pan with Crisco.
Bake at 375°.
Each time cake starts to rise, shake down.
Continue shaking and cooking until brown.

title: date orange balls
directions: Combine dates, butter and sugar in a saucepan.
Cook until blended well (about 5 minutes).
Mixture will become clear.
Let cool slightly.
Remove from heat.
Add orange juice, nuts and Rice Krispies.
When mixture is cool enough to handle, form into balls the size of walnuts and roll in coconut (Angel Flake).
Makes 24 balls.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add other ingredients and simmer on low for 1/2 hour.

title: tang pie
directions: Whip the
milk	and
Tang
until forms peaks.
Add Cool Whip and whip until set up. Mix in sour cream well with spoon. Spoon into
pie
crusts
and
chill before serving.
Makes two pies.

title: buttermilk cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan. Bake at 400° about 30 minutes.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix together all ingredients except the coconut. Form into small balls. Roll each ball in the coconut.
Place in a container and store in refrigerator.

title: roast chicken tacos
directions: Oven:
Warm chicken and tortillas in 325° oven for 15 to 30 minutes.

title: french potato gratin
directions: Peel and slice potatoes thinly.
Use a food processor, if available.
Lightly grease an ovenproof casserole.
Layer casserole dish with potato slices, sprinkling each layer with salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Press garlic over mixture.
Add cream and milk.
(You may prepare ahead of time up to this step.)
Bake at 400° for about 40 minutes or until potatoes are soft, creamy and golden brown on surface.

title: date nut bars
directions: Mix all together very well.
If using a 9 x 13-inch cake pan, double the recipe.
Line pan with waxed paper.
Pour mixture into pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn out of pan onto cooking rack and remove paper immediately.
Dust top lightly with powdered sugar.

title: stuffing
directions: Crumble bread. Mix other ingredients well with bread crumbs. Stuff turkey, chicken, etc...

title: orange-marinated pork tenderloin
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in baking dish.
Add pork and marinate in refrigerator at least 1 hour or overnight.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Drain pork, reserving marinade.
Place pork on baking sheet and season generously with pepper.
Roast until cooked through, about 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, bring reserved marinade to boil in small saucepan.
Slice pork tenderloins and serve, passing marinade separately as sauce.

title: ham and cheese french toast
directions: Beat eggs, milk, sugar and salt just to combine.
Makes 4 sandwiches with bread, ham and cheese.
Cut diagonally into quarters.
Place in single layer in shallow baking dish.
Pour egg mixture over top, covering completely.
Refrigerate overnight. Saute in hot butter until golden brown on each side and cheese is slightly melted.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Mix egg white and water.
Mix in pecans.
Sift together sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Pour over pecans and mix well.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Then mix together remaining ingredients by hand.
Spread on top of sweet potato mixture.

title: holiday fruit butter
directions: Combine water, apples and pears in 5-quart kettle.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until fruit is soft.
Stir in bananas.
Put fruit through food mill or sieve; return to kettle and stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until thick, about 1 hour, stirring frequently.
Cool, then pour into jars and refrigerate.
Makes 6 pints.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Combine soup, peas (with liquid), pimento, onion and lemon juice in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Set aside 1 cup noodles.
Fold remaining noodles and tuna into mixture. Arrange reserved noodles around edges.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Makes 1 quart of dry mix.
Use 2 rounded teaspoons of mix to 1 cup of hot water.
This mix makes a great gift during the holidays to someone that likes hot beverages.
Measure some into a Ziploc bag.
Place inside a pretty mug and tie it with a bow.

title: potato and egg casserole
directions: Generously
butter
a 2-quart casserole.
Wash potatoes and cook
until
tender.
Drain, then shake pan over low heat until potatoes are dry.
Peel potatoes and eggs, then cut into 1/4-inch slices
and
set aside.
Mix together sour cream and butter; reserve half the sour cream mixture for the top of the casserole.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix together the first 10 ingredients.
Pour into greased pans.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 to 50 minutes or 9-inch cake pans 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Mix together remaining ingredients and spread over cooled cake.

title: chimichangas
directions: Brown sausage with onion; drain.
Stir in salsa and cumin. Simmer 5 minutes or until most liquid has evaporated.
Remove from heat.
Stir in beans.

title: crazy cake
directions: Beat 4 minutes.

Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. While cake is still warm, punch all over with fork and slowly pour on mixture of 1 cup powdered sugar and juice of 1 orange.

title: grilled turkey tenderloins
directions: Pierce tenderloins with fork in several places.
Place in plastic bag.
Beat oil into remaining ingredients and pour over turkey.
Seal bag securely, pressing out air.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Place oiled or no-stick barbecue grill 4 to 6 inches over hot coals.
Remove meat from marinade and grill for 20 minutes or until meat is no longer pink, turning and basting often with marinade.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: surprise sweet potato balls
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in boiling water until done.
Peel and mash fine.
Add eggs; mix well.
Form into balls around marshmallows.
Roll in corn flakes.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt 4 candy bars and 1 stick oleo in a double boiler and set aside.
Cream sugar and 1 stick oleo.
Add eggs, flour, soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
Blend and add candy and nuts.
Bake at 325° in a Bundt pan for approximately 1 hour.

title: white eagle brand milk cake
directions: Bake one white cake according to directions.
Make holes in cake while hot and pour Eagle Brand milk and coconut cream over cake.
Cover and let stand overnight.
Pour pineapple over cake and cover with Cool Whip.
Top with the coconut.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix water and jello.
Add cream cheese (allow to melt).
Add crushed pineapple, nuts and 7-Up.
Chill in mold.

title: fish bouillon
directions: In large soup pot, combine onions, carrots and celery with water. Simmer with salt pork, barley and potatoes until tender. Season to taste. Add pieces of fish last. Simmer until fish is cooked through.

title: kringla(a norwegian cookie)
directions: *Instead of buttermilk, I use 2 tablespoons vinegar and fill the cup with 2% milk, less fattening.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding following package directions.
Stir Eagle Brand milk into pudding.
Fold Cool Whip in.
Add vanilla wafers and bananas.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: chicken "n" rice casserole
directions: Mix together rice, soups, mushrooms and parsley.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, cover bottom with melted butter.
Add rice mixture; layer chicken parts (use seasonings you prefer) on rice mixture. Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove foil to let chicken brown last half hour.
May be made the day before.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all dry ingredients in the pan, the cake is to be baked in the same pan as it was mixed in.
Stir with a fork until well mixed.
Make three depressions in the dry ingredients, one hole for oil, one for vinegar, one for vanilla, then pour 1 cup water over all the ingredients and stir with fork until well blended.
Bake 30 minutes.
Use 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: rocky mountain apple crisp
directions: Arrange apples in greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, lemon and orange rind and liquors.

title: sweet dough pie(syrup)
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Roll out and place in pie plates. Makes enough dough for 4 single pie crusts or two double pie crusts.

title: hummus
directions: Put all ingredients into food processor or blender.
Blend or process well, until a paste is formed; if mixture is too thick, add water until desired consistency is achieved.

title: basil peas
directions: Thaw frozen peas by pouring boiling water over them; drain. Melt butter; add onions and cook until tender but not brown.
Stir in peas and remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook about 5 minutes or until tender.

title: egg and cheese bake
directions: Place bread, cheese and ham in layers in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix the rest of the ingredients well and pour over layers in pan. Let soak overnight.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cranberry conserve
directions: Mix sugar and juice well.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 10 minutes.
Add mandarin oranges, cranberries and walnuts.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and boil gently 10 minutes.
Cool completely to room temperature.
Put in jars and store in refrigerator, covered.
(Do not put in freezer.)
Keeps well for several weeks.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on box and add flavoring to batter.
Bake cake in sheet cake pan.
Mix cream of coconut and condensed milk.
Punch holes in hot cake and pour mixture over cake.
Let cool.
Spread on Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut. Keep refrigerated.

title: seafood bake
directions: Mix soup and sherry.
Place half of thawed fish in bottom of a 10 x 6-inch casserole dish.
Cover with half of the shrimp mixture.
Repeat.
Sprinkle with breadcrumbs, cheese and salt.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: best of the meat loaves
directions: Chop onion and	green pepper in very small pieces. Beat eggs until creamy.
Chop
bread	into
small
pieces.
Mix all ingredients using
half
of
tomato
sauce.
Grease
a 2-quart Pyrex baking
dish.
Pour
ingredients into Pyrex dish. Shape, then pour remaining
tomato sauce over top of meat loaf.
Bake at 325° for 1	hour and 25 minutes or until well done.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: turkey roast
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix paprika, butter, garlic salt and pepper flakes; spread over turkey.
Place turkey on rack in rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Add onions to pan, dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Roast at 170° about 1 1/2 hours.
Place turkey on warm platter, keep warm.
Shake water, flour and cornstarch and 1 1/2 tsp. garlic salt in lightly covered container.
Place onions and pan drippings in saucepan, stir in flour mixture.
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring frequently, until mixture thickens and boils.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cut turkey into slices.
Serve with sauce.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: lime party salad
directions: In a double boiler melt the marshmallows with the milk.
Place the gelatin in a large bowl.
Pour the hot mixture over the gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add the cream cheese.
Blend with an electric mixer.
Add pineapple.
Cool.
Fold in Cool Whip and mayonnaise.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill completely.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in a baking dish.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.
This dish can be made the night before and baked later.
Good for a carry-in dinner.
No salt added.

title: never fail chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar and evaporated milk in heavy pot and boil rapidly for 9 minutes.
Remove from heat and add butter, chocolate chips, marshmallow cream, vanilla and walnuts.
Pour in buttered pan and place in refrigerator to cool.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: chicken cha-cha
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare Stove Top and set aside.
Cut up chicken bite-size.
Put in baking dish.
Pour chicken soup on top, undiluted.
Spread all over chicken.
Spoon stuffing on top. Bake for 1 hour.
Serve with cranberry sauce and vegie.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Line bottom of casserole with dried beef.
Wrap chicken with bacon that has been cooked slightly in microwave.
Place chicken on dried beef.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken. Cover with foil and bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Cream together cream cheese, Salad Supreme, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add onion flakes, dill and garlic.
Chill.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix eggs and cheese and add to other ingredients.
Bake in greased casserole 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 5.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheese come to room temperature.
Add Accent and Worcestershire sauce.
Blend.
Cut up onions and dried beef very fine.
Add to cheese mixture and mix well.
Roll into ball and refrigerate.

title: country spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly flour a 12-cup ring mold or 10-inch tube pan.
Measure flour and remaining ingredients into large mixing bowl.
With mixer at low speed, beat ingredients just until mixed, frequently scraping bowl with spatula.
Increase speed to high; beat 2 minutes, occasionally scraping bowl.
Turn batter into prepared pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes on wire rack.
Remove from pan; cool.
Makes 16 servings.

title: texas hash
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook ground chuck with onions, green peppers and seasonings in skillet until vegetables are tender, stirring frequently; drain.
Add rice and tomatoes.
Place in baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Lay cheese over casserole. Bake until cheese melts.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate, caramel and pecan sauce
directions: This sauce can be made to give as a present and is especially good over ice cream.

title: waikiki dessert
directions: Combine crumbs, margarine and sugar.
Press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan, reserving 1/4 cup crumbs.
Melt marshmallows with milk in double boiler over low heat.
Stir until smooth.
Add pineapple and lemon juice; mix well.
Chill thoroughly.
Fold in whipped cream; pour over crumbs.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs. Chill overnight.
Makes 12 servings.

title: "wimpies" meat sauce
directions: Fry onions in butter.
Add all remaining ingredients except meat.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Brown meat, separately skim off fat. Add to sauce.
Makes 2 quarts.
The longer it cooks, the better it gets.
Great on hot dogs or alone on buns.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine ingredients and boil for 1 minute.
Cut biscuits in fourths.
Butter a 9 x 11-inch pan.
Place cut biscuits in pan and pour mixture over them.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel, seed and thinly slice 4 cucumbers.
Mix with sour cream, Tabasco sauce, chives, salt and pepper.
Peel remaining cucumbers. Cut each into four slices 1 1/2-inches thick.
Scoop out center and fill with sour cream mixture.

title: chicken salad in tart shells
directions: Cook hen in 3 quarts water with 1
stalk
celery,
salt and pepper.
After chicken has cooled, bone
and
tear
into small pieces.
Combine 1/2 cup broth with
chicken and remaining ingredients.
Mix well and chill.	Spoon
tablespoons chicken salad into each tart shell.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients, except bacon and onion.
Put onion in mixture and place bacon on top.
Bake for 2 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: dressing for baked fish
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put a layer of it between fish fillets or stuff whole fish. Brush with oil; wrap in foil and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: health salad dressing
directions: Shake all ingredients together.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Melt butter and add last.
Put in an 8 x 11-inch casserole dish.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 425°. When edges begin to brown, take out and top with grated cheese (will melt without putting back in oven).

title: haystacks
directions: Beat sugar and margarine together.
Add eggs and vanilla and continue beating until fluffy.
Add flour, salt, baking powder and soda; mix thoroughly.
Add nuts and pineapple and mix well.

title: swiss steak
directions: Have required steak (1-inch thick). Beat in mixture of flour, salt and pepper (to your liking). Beat steak on both sides. Sear on both sides in greased skillet. Remove from fire; put into baking pan. Add tomatoes. Cover and cook in 350° oven for 2 hours.

title: one rise whole wheat bread
directions: Place flour into an ovenproof bowl and place in a warm (150°) oven for 10 minutes.

title: almond twists
directions: Sprinkle work surface lightly with sugar. Unfold 1 sheet of pastry and lay flat on surface.

Roll out to 12-inch square. Divide almond paste in half. Break half of paste into small pieces and dot over half of pastry sheet. Fold pastry in half over almond paste and roll out to 10 x 12-inch rectangle. Fold in half again and roll out to 10 x 12-inch rectangle. Cut pastry in half to make 2 rectangles, each 5 x 12-inches. Cut each rectangle into 12 strips, 1-inch wide. Twist strips into corkscrew shape and place on ungreased baking sheets about 1-inch apart. Repeat with remaining pastry sheet and almond paste. Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes or until puffed and golden brown. Remove from baking sheets immediately and cool completely on wire racks.

title: valerie's green beans
directions: Saute bacon until crispy.
Remove from skillet.
Saute onion in bacon drippings until clear.
Put bacon back in skillet.
Add green beans.
Heat thoroughly.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
(Or use microwave oven to melt cheese.)

title: caramel apple burritos
directions: Place apple slices in a saucepan. Cover and cook over medium heat 3 to 4 minutes or until tender. Reduce heat and add caramels. Cook and stir until caramels are melted. Spoon apple
mixture off center on each tortilla. Fold sides and ends over filling and roll up.

title: orange balls
directions: Combine wafers, juice, butter and sugar; mix well.
Blend in nuts.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in coconut.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: shoo-fly cupcakes
directions: Mix together flour, 1 1/2 cups brown sugar, baking powder and shortening.
Mix together the hot water, 1 cup brown sugar and baking soda

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Soak oats in buttermilk.
Mix all ingredients together.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: maw maw's squash casserole
directions: Cook and drain approximately 10 yellow squash.
Grease a large casserole dish and alternate layers of crushed saltine crackers, squash and grated cheese.
(Salt and pepper to taste and dot with butter each layer.)
Saturate with milk and bake for approximately 1 hour at 350° or until milk has absorbed.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Add melted butter and lemon juice and rind.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° until set.

title: best ever chicken soup
directions: Add all ingredients except noodles and ketchup to pot with water.
Cook on low heat for 3 hours until chicken is really tender.
Remove chicken, debone, and pinch up.
While doing this, cook noodles in broth, removing onion and carrot.
Dice up carrot and throw onion away.
Turn off heat.
Add carrot, chicken and ketchup.
Stir well.

title: butterscotch pie filling
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour and salt together.
Mix 2 egg yolks and 1/4 cup cold milk together.
Combine with sugar-flour mixture. Put remaining milk until it forms a scum; add this mixture and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add butter and vanilla. Cool; then pour into a pie shell.
Make meringue and brown in a 400° oven for 5 minutes.

title: apple knobby pudding
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg. Add apples, nuts and vanilla. Add sifted dry ingredients.
Bake in oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in an 8-inch square pan.
Serve with whipped cream or lemon sauce.

title: apple or potato salad dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, cream and vinegar.
Cook in double boiler until boil starts.
Cook on simmer 1 to 2 minutes until thickened.
Do not boil.
Add mayonnaise.
Mix with potatoes.

title: jan's squash casserole
directions: Cook onions and squash until tender.
Drain well.
While still hot, add breadcrumbs, eggs, milk, and 1-1/2 c of cheese. Mix well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Melt butter in large casserole dish.
Pour in squash mixture.
Bake at 375 for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with remaining cheese. Return to oven and heat until cheese melts.
Serves 6-8.

title: quick and easy sweet 'n' sour kielbasa
directions: Cut kielbasa, green peppers and onions into bite size chunks. Saute onions and green peppers in small amount of oil and set aside.
Combine ketchup, brown sugar, garlic powder and onion powder into small bowl and stir thoroughly.
Place kielbasa into large skillet and pour sauce over it.
Simmer until sauce caramelizes.
Place green peppers, onions and pineapple with juice into kielbasa and simmer.
(May serve over rice.)

title: holiday fudge
directions: Combine margarine, milk, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in marshmallows, morsels, nuts and vanilla.
Stir until marshmallows are melted.
Pour into 8-inch square, buttered pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: quick and easy beef and rice
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet. Drain. Add kidney beans and tomato sauce. Season with salt and pepper. Turn on low and simmer. Serve over rice.

title: donna's breakfast
directions: Line baking dish with 1/2 of crumbled bread.
Next layer 1/2 of cheese and then 1/2 of crumbled sausage and bacon.
Make another layer of each, ending with cheese.
Mix together eggs, milk, mustard, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Over layers, pour eggs and milk mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Combine soup and milk.
Lightly coat chicken with flour.
Dip in soup mix and coat with stuffing mix.
Place on baking dish. Dribble with oleo.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients together 3 times.
Place in an 8-inch square pan.
Make 3 holes.
In one, put the vinegar; in second, put the vanilla; in the third, put the melted shortening. Over all, pour the water.
Mix well.
Bake in the same pan for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: In large mixer bowl, place instant pudding, sour cream, milk and orange peel.
Beat at low speed, scraping bowl often, until thick and well mixed (1 to 2 minutes).
By hand, fold in whipped cream.

title: walnut, arugula and gorgonzola crostini
directions: In this easy starter, a mix of taney blue cheese, chopped, toasted walnuts and peppery arugula makes a delicious topping for baguette toasts. 6 servings.

title: pineapple nut salad
directions: Bring pineapple juice to a boil.
Add lime jello, stirring until dissolved.
Stir in sour cream.
Add pineapple and nuts. Put in 1 1/4-quart ring mold; refrigerate.
This will set in 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Put Bisquick into a bowl.
Make a well	in
center
and pour in milk.
Mix lightly with a spoon to a soft dough.

title: bacon breadsticks
directions: Take breadsticks and 1/2 piece of bacon; wrap bacon around the breadstick.
Roll in cheese.
Cook in microwave for 5 to 8 minutes until bacon is cooked and then cool.

title: red and blueberry delight
directions: In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, mix graham crackers, sugar, nuts and butter.
Press evenly in pan.
Beat cream cheese, 3/4 cup sugar, eggs and lemon juice until smooth.
Spread over graham cracker crust.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool completely.
Spread blueberry and cherry pie filing alternately in stripe pattern over cooled mixture.
Keep refrigerated until serving.
Top with Cool Whip when served.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except potato chips and Parmesan cheese.
Put in a greased casserole.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes covered.
Remove cover.
Add potato chips and sprinkle Parmesan cheese over this.
Cook 5 more minutes.

title: hawaiian fruitcake
directions: Mix the ingredients together and pour in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
After cooling, ice with the icing.

title: modeling clay
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine soda and cornstarch.
In a 2-cup measure, combine water and food coloring.
Pour colored water over soda mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Microwave at High for 4 to 8 minutes, stirring after every minute in the microwave until mixture is firm.
Cover with a damp towel until cool.
Knead until smooth.
Store in airtight containers or plastic bags.

title: english muffin pizza
directions: First you put tomato sauce on the English muffin.
Next, put the cheese over the sauce, then put in the toaster oven until brown.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and soups.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Brown ground beef.
Layer in casserole dish, starting with sauce, then ground beef and macaroni, ending with sauce.
Top with grated hoop cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: catfish stew
directions: Fry bacon and white and green onions on low heat for 10 minutes, then put in a big pot.
Add potato, stewed tomatoes and whole milk.
Stir it up and then add fried catfish.
Cook on low heat for 1 1/2 hours.
(Add hot sauce and soy sauce to Daddy's.)

title: sour cream pound cake i
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, and alternate with the flour mixture.
Add vanilla and lemon extracts; mix well.
Add sour cream; mix well, but do not overbeat.
Bake in a well-greased and floured Bundt pan at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes, or until cake tests done.

title: holiday punch
directions: Combine ingredients with orange sherbet.

title: champagne fruit punch
directions: Combine sugar and hot water together until sugar dissolves. Add juices.
Add soda and champagne just before serving.
Float strawberries and apple slices on top.

title: puffy eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant and boil 5 minutes.
Drain and season.
Mash. Mix with all other ingredients.
Put some of the crumbs in mixture.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle rest of crumbs on top.
Dot with butter and bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: dirt cake
directions: Blend cream cheese, margarine, sugar, pudding, milk and Cool Whip (will thicken upon standing).
Grate cookies twice in processor (until of soil consistency; blender will do).
Layer in a 10-inch flower pot, starting with cookies and ending with cookies.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Place trowel and plastic flowers and set out before guests arrive.

title: steak in foil
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Place 24 x 18-inch piece of aluminum foil in baking pan.
Wrap meat tightly.
Stir mushroom soup and onion soup mix.
Spread over meat.
Top with vegetables.
Sprinkle water and steak sauce over meat.
Secure tightly.
Bake about 1 to 1 1/4 hours until tender.

title: springtime potatoes
directions: Wash and scrape potatoes; cook until tender in boiling salted water.
Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Heat, but do not boil.
Pour sour cream mixture over hot potatoes.
If desired, garnish with parsley.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: turkey breast strips in broccoli cream
directions: In a saucepan, bring chicken stock to a boil.
Add onion, garlic, broccoli and cream; simmer for 10 minutes.
Melt butter in a large skillet.
Saute turkey strips; season with salt and pepper.
Drain grease.
Pour broccoli cream mixture over meat; cook for 2 minutes over low heat.
Remove from heat; adjust seasoning and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tuna crunch casserole
directions: Stir together milk and soup; add tuna, peas and eggs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with potato chips. Return to oven and bake 5 minutes, uncovered.

title: canned grapes
directions: Divide equally into 2 quart jars.
Fill jar with water.
Cold pack 10 minutes, let stand in hot water 20 to 30 minutes.
Can also use this recipe for blackberries or other berries.
These do not store as well as grapes.

title: chicken livers with onions and bacon
directions: Cook bacon in large frying pan until crisp.
Drain on paper towel.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons bacon fat.
Crumble bacon. Chop onions.
Heat reserved bacon fat.
Add onions, salt and pepper.
Stir, cover and cook over medium heat until softened. Remove onions; set aside.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Heat oil over high heat.
Toss livers in flour mixture and cook, stirring constantly, until crisp and brown outside but still slightly pink inside, about 5 minutes.
Toss the cooked livers with the bacon and onions; serve.

title: recipe for happiness
directions: Rise up early and greet the Lord, "Good Morning, Father", then thank Him for His son Jesus who bore your sins on the cross so that you may have eternal life thru trusting Him as your Savior; and thank the Holy Spirit for guiding your life in the right path. Next, ask the Lord to help you to be sensitive to the needs of those around you and your fellowman and be sure to share Jesus with them in your thought, word or deeds.
Be diligent on your job, work or play; thank God for these opportunities to serve Him.
End your day in the same manner by spending more quiet time with God and thank Him for allowing you to live in His wonderful world.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Pour into pie pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°, or until brown.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain juice from asparagus and mix juice with soup.
Fix in following layers:
crumbled crackers, asparagus and soup mixture; do another layer.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lynda's cheese squares
directions: In large bowl, mix the two cheeses together.
Place in a 9 x 13 pan.
Whisk the eggs and milk until well blended.
Pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into bite-sized squares after cooling slightly.

title: aunt betsy's quiche
directions: *Cooked ham, sausage or bacon may be substituted to make a breakfast quiche.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix all dry ingredients. Add milk and oil. Dip wieners in mixture. Coat well and drop in hot shortening until brown.

title: peach dessert
directions: In a large bowl, put the can of peaches (do not drain the juice.)
Set aside.
In large saucepan, put the 6 cups of water, jello, pudding and 12 marshmallows.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until all the marshmallows have dissolved.
Then pour this mixture into the bowl of peaches.
Stir.
Put in refrigerator.
Chill.
Serves 10.
Serve with whipped cream on top.
This is a good dish to make the night before you need it. Serves 10.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix ingredients together well and pour into crust.
Chill in refrigerator for 1 hour or until firm.
Makes 1 pie.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Evenly spread 1 cup of sauce in a 17 x 12-inch baking pan.
In a large bowl, combine cheeses, eggs, parsley and pepper.
Fill shells with mixture and arrange in single layer in pan.
Evenly top with remaining sauce.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 8.

title: homemade ice cream
