directions: Beat eggs and sugar until thick; add vanilla and salt.
Stir in half and half and milk.
Follow directions on "homemade freezer" for making into ice cream!

title: carolyn's spiced tea
directions: In small pan make tea with 6 cups water and 6 small tea bags. In large pan, add 6 cups water, 1 stick cinnamon, 1 1/2 teaspoons whole cloves and sugar.
Let boil slowly for 5 or 10 minutes.
Add pineapple juice, orange juice, lemonade or lemons and the tea mixture.
Store in refrigerator and use as needed.
Heat before serving.
Be sure and stir before using because it settles to the bottom.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Cook together hamburger, tomato sauce, salt and garlic powder.
Mix together cream cheese, sour cream and mushroom soup.
On bottom of casserole dish, place noodles, hamburger and then cream cheese mixture.
Top with slices of Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese melts, approximately 1/2 hour.

title: crawfish jambalaya in rice cooker
directions: Wash raw rice and drain.
Place all ingredients in Hitachi rice cooker with drained rice.
Do not add any water.
Taste for seasoning.
Add salt and red pepper, if needed.
Put rice cooker on cook cycle.
After cook cycle is completed, keep on warm cycle for at least 1/2 hour.
Good with garlic bread and green salad. Must be cooked in 8 to 10 cup rice cooker.

title: crock-pot chocolate covered peanuts
directions: Layer in order in a crock-pot and heat for one to two hours. Stir and mix.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: shari's banana bread
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and butter.
Mix until well blended.
Blend in eggs and bananas.
Mix all together until just moistened.
Pour into a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: betty crocker brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate over hot water.
Stir in Wesson oil and beat in sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour; mix in baking powder and salt.
Mix in nuts.
Spread in a well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch oblong pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Slight imprint will be left when top is touched lightly for testing. Cool; cut into 32 squares or smaller, if desired.

title: caesar dressing
directions: In mixing bowl, using a wire whisk, whip eggs and mustard for 5 minutes.
Slowly add oil; whip until absorbed before adding more.
Thin with vinegar.
Add anchovy paste and remaining ingredients with Parmesan cheese last.
Cover and refrigerate. Don't keep longer than three weeks.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix thawed hash brown's, butter, salt, onion, sour cream, soup and cheese.
Place in a lightly greased 9 x 13 inch pan. Sprinkle with crushed corn flakes or Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: shrimp sauce
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Make 2 or 3 days ahead of time; shake well before using.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Saute one stick butter or margarine, onion, pepper and mushrooms.
Add mayonnaise when liquid is absorbed.

title: changeable casserole
directions: *Cream of celery soup can be substituted.

title: annie's meatballs
directions: Put everything into a large mixing bowl and using your hands, mix ingredients thoroughly.
The mix should be pretty moist
(but you can adjust breadcrumbs if needed).
Roll meatballs about the size of golf balls.
In large frying pan, fill vegetable oil about 1 inch deep.
Heat oil and add meatballs.
Carefully brown on all sides until done.
If there are any left after everyone has sampled them fresh from the frying pan, you can add them to your sauce.
This recipe was obtained by carefully observing Grandma making these and writing it all down!

title: apple cake
directions: Pour sugar over apples and let stand.
Beat eggs; add oil and vanilla.
In another bowl, mix flour, soda, salt and cinnamon. Add the flour mixture and the egg mixture alternately to apple mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: salted peanut crunchies
directions: Cream together butter, shortening and peanut butter.
Beat in sugars gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in sifted dry ingredients.
Stir in chocolate pieces and peanuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto buttered cookie sheet.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for about 15 minutes. Makes about 8 dozen.

title: meringue cookies
directions: Beat vigorously for 15 minutes.
Stir in 1 1/4 cups chopped pecans.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Drop mixture onto greased cookie sheet.
Cut off oven.
Put cookies in and leave for 45 minutes. Do not open oven door until time is up.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Mix soup and sour cream. Add chicken and put into 10 x 10-inch baking dish.
(Spray dish with Pam before.)
Mix melted margarine, crushed crackers and poppy seed.
Spread over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp victoria
directions: Saut onions, pepper, garlic and celery gently in margarine until wilted and tender.
Add shrimp and cook about five minutes, or until shrimp turns pink.
Add mushrooms and cook five minutes longer.
Add sour cream, stirring until blended and heated, but do not boil.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over hot rice.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Add cake mix, pudding mix, water and oil; beat 10 minutes at medium speed on an electric mixer.
Pour into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Using 2-tined fork, prick holes in top of cake.
Drizzle Lemon Glaze over top and spread on sides of cake.
Cool completely.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Mix the soup, sugar, vinegar, oil, Worcestershire sauce, pepper, mustard and salt together and add to the vegetables.
(I use blender to mix.)

title: christmas cookies
directions: Sift flour and soda and add cinnamon together.
Cream butter and sugar, add eggs.
Add milk and flour mixture slowly.
Chop candied fruit fine.
Add to batter.
Mix together well.
(Will be heavy.)
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: twenty-four hour salad
directions: Combine well drained fruits.
Add marshmallows and nutmeats. Beat eggs until light; gradually add sugar, light cream and lemon juice.
Mix. Cook in double boiler until smooth and thick, stirring constantly.
Cool; fold in whipped cream.
Pour over fruit mixture and mix lightly.
Chill for 24 hours.
Do not freeze.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Place thawed potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix 1/2 cup butter, soup, cheese, sour cream, salt, pepper and onion.
Pour over potatoes in casserole dish.
Mix. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with corn flakes and drizzle with butter; bake until golden brown (10 to 15 minutes).

title: ground meat and corn
directions: Crumble and thoroughly brown the meat. Add chopped onion and brown. Then add the corn and cook for several minutes, until all is well mixed and the corn is tender.
Serves 6 or 8. Can freeze. Can do ahead.

title: easy enchiladas
directions: Brown beef.
Add beans and half jar of sauce; simmer.
Put meat mixture and sliced Velveeta on tortillas.
Roll and place on cookie sheet.
Cover and heat.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Break the cauliflower in small pieces.
Chop celery and green pepper.
Slice the stuffed
olives and ripe olives.
Mix together. Toss with Wish-Bone Italian dressing.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken sour cream casserole
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Mix in bowl sour cream, mayonnaise, water and lemon juice.
In separate bowl combine remaining ingredients; place in casserole dish.
Pour sour cream mixture on top; cover.
Place in oven and bake for 30 minutes.

title: great cole slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, pepper, onion and carrot together.
Pour oil and vinegar over all.
Mix and let stand for 10 minutes.
Drain. Whish together salt, pepper, sugar and mayo.
Pour over slaw and mix well.
Serve.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Add egg to drained fruit and dry ingredients.
Pour in well-greased pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Beat partially thawed lemonade with milk.
Fold in Cool Whip. Add a few drops yellow food coloring, if desired.
Pour into pie crust and chill.
May garnish with whipped topping and lemon slices.

title: okra pickles
directions: Wash okra and pack firmly in hot sterilized jars.
In each jar, put a clove of garlic and hot peppers if you wish.
Make a brine with the vinegar, water, dill seed and salt.
Boil.
Pour boiling brine over okra, leaving 1/4-inch headspace at top.
Seal. Process for 10 minutes in a boiling water bath.
Let ripen several weeks before using.
Makes 6 pints.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt in crock-pot or double boiler until smooth.
Add peanuts. Mix and drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Put flour in mixing bowl.
Add eggs and beat mixture with a wooden spoon until dough is elastic.
Gradually stir the milk into the mixture, then whisk until smooth.
Pour an inch of oil into pan and put in 450° preheated oven until oil is smoking.
Pour mixture onto oil.
The oil should come up the sides which will seal the top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until brown.

title: chinese noodles and tuna salad
directions: Combine the tuna, onions, green pepper, olives and pimiento. Blend mayonnaise, lemon juice and cream.
Pour over tuna and mix. Chill.
Add noodles and mix just before serving.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Mix flour, sugar and oleo together to form dough.
Pat half of dough into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bring dough up sides about 1 inch.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cook zucchini, 1 cup sugar and lemon juice until soft.
Add cinnamon.
Mash cooked zucchini mixture and pour onto baked shell.
Sprinkle with remaining dough mixture.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: seafood gumbo file(fee-lay)
directions: Brown flour in oil on medium heat until dark brown (very important), stirring constantly.
Add onion (not green onion), bell pepper, garlic and celery.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes until tender.
Stir in water or stock.
Add Cajun seasoning, green onion, okra, tomatoes, bay leaf and cayenne pepper.
Bring to boil; reduce heat to medium.
Cover.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: yankee pot roast
directions: Cut slits in beef. Take 1 medium clove of garlic and cut it in slits. Put it in slits of beef. Brown the roast on both sides. Cover in water. Pour in 1/2 cup of Heinz "57" sauce, Worcestershire sauce, A.1. steak sauce, oregano, parsley, Italian seasoning, bay leaf, salt and pepper and diced onions. Cover and simmer until meat is done. When meat is done, remove from pan. Strain the liquid into a another pan and make gravy from strained liquid.

title: georgia fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken.
Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Roll chicken in mixture.
Cook in 350° oven for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chipmunk bars
directions: Cream together the first 2 ingredients.
Sift together the next 5.
Add beaten egg and vanilla.
Cool the boiling water and chopped dates and add to the batter.
Place mixture on a jelly roll pan.
Add chocolate bits and nutmeats (may be omitted).
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage into small pieces.
Put in buttered baking dish, sprinkle with salt and pepper and add the white sauce.
Lift cabbage with fork, that it may be well mixed with sauce.
Cover with buttered crumbs.
Bake until crumbs are brown.

title: delicious dessert
directions: Mix butter, 2 tablespoons sugar, pecans and flour with hands. Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until light brown.
Beat until smooth cream cheese, 4x sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Mix the instant pudding and milk.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top with rest of Cool Whip.
Top with cherries or coconut.

title: chocolate cake icing
directions: Melt butter on medium heat and add all other ingredients. Mix well. Continue to cook on med-high heat until mixture comes to full rolling boil.
Cool slightly before frosting cooled cake.

title: morning shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in electric blender.
Cover and whirl until smooth and thick.
Serve immediately.
Makes 2 servings.

title: macaroni cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions. Brown ground beef and onion. Add tomato paste, salt, pepper and soup. Mix all ingredients together. Top with cheese slices and put in 325° oven long enough to melt cheese.

title: chicken roll ups
directions: Mix soup, milk, and 1/2 cup of cheese over medium heat until cheese is melted. Mix chicken and onions, 1/4 cup of cheese and enough soup mixture to moisten. Roll up chicken mixture in crescent rolls. Pour soup in bottom of pan. Keep some mixture to put on top of rolls before serving. Place crescent rolls in soup. Cook at 375° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle remaining cheese over rolls and return to oven until it melts.

title: chocolate bonbons
directions: Mix in large mixing bowl.
Roll in walnut size balls.
In top of double boiler, melt 1/4 pound paraffin and 2 large packages chocolate chips.
Dip balls in chocolate and drain on wax paper.

title: corn casserole
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter.
Add flour, sugar and salt; blend well.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly until sauce is thickened.
Stir in corn.
Beat eggs until frothy and stir into corn mixture.
Pour into well-greased 3-quart casserole.
Bake in oven at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Serve hot.

title: blueberry pineapple cream
directions: In a bowl, combine the graham cracker crumbs, butter and sugar. Press into the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool completely.
Meanwhile, drain pineapple juice into a saucepan.
Set pineapple aside.
Add marshmallows to juice; cook and stir until melted.
Remove from heat and cool for 10 minutes.
In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add marshmallow mixture; beat well.
Fold in the pineapple and whipped topping.
Spread half over crust.
Cover with pie filling.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with additional graham cracker crumbs.
Chill for 30 minutes.

title: cocoa almond cut-out cookies
directions: In large bowl, beat butter, condensed milk, eggs, vanilla and almond extract until well blended.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and baking soda.
Gradually add to butter mixture, beating until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Divide dough into 4 equal parts.
Wrap in plastic wrap, chill until firm, about 2 hours. Remove one part of dough at a time.
Roll to about 1/8-inch thickness on floured surface.
Cut to desired shapes.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes or until set.
Cool completely.
Drizzle chocolate glaze over to.

title: quick and creamy potatoes
directions: Cook and dice potatoes.
Set aside.
In large skillet saute butter and scallions until softened.
Add half and half.
Bring to a boil.
Stir frequently, as not to burn.
Add sour cream.
Bring to a boil (approximately 1 minute).
Reduce heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients except parsley.
Cook mixture until thickens, stirring frequently (approximately 1 to 3 minutes).
Serve with parsley garnish.
Optional:
Serve over slice of toast.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix cocoa and food coloring.
Set aside.
Mix vegetable oil, sugar, eggs, salt, vanilla, buttermilk and flour. Mix well.
Add cocoa and food coloring and mix well.
Add soda to vinegar.
Do not beat.
Fold into batter.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes in greased and floured 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake in covered, greased casserole in moderate oven (350°) for thirty
minutes.
Uncover and continue baking for another 20 to 30 minutes.

title: mulled cider
directions: Mix all ingredients in a crock-pot and add a couple of orange slices.
Cook. Simmer low to medium at least two hours.

title: 1-hour rolls
directions: Mix flour with baking powder, soda, sugar and salt.
Cut shortening into dry ingredients.
Soften yeast cake in warm water and add buttermilk to this, then stir yeast and buttermilk to dry ingredients to form a soft dough.
Turn onto floured board and knead for a minute before rolling.
Cut 1/4-inch thick.
Put on well-greased baking sheet and let stand 1 hour and then bake in a 425° oven for 12 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except cheese) in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 45 minutes at 350°.
Spread cheese on the top for the last 5 minutes of baking time.

title: christmas cranberry bread
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder, soda and sugar together into bowl.
Stir in
eggs,
butter,
orange
juice
and hot water.
Mix well.
Fold
in cranberries, nuts and orange rind. Spoon batter into 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove bread from pans.
Cool, wrap and store for at least 24 hours.

title: dutch oven chicken
directions: Cook in Dutch oven pan at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or more. Stir once or twice.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Use 2 tablespoons to one cup of boiling
water.
Add
a drop or two of vanilla and a small pinch of salt.
Float a marshmallow on top.

title: chicken strata
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Put in 8 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle more cheese on top before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Peel potato; cut in small chunks.
Cover with water.
Boil until soft enough to mash.
Mash; add milk.
Then add flour to make dough.
Make size biscuits desired.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: garlic butter croutons
directions: Liquify all but the last 3 ingredients until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Briefly whiz in sesame seed and herbs.
Spread thickly on bread, sliced, and broil until crusty and beginning to brown. Yields about 2 1/2 cups.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: Add all ingredients to crock-pot and stir well.
Cook on low all night or high all morning.
Great over rice.
Serves 8.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add mashed bananas, soda, salt and vanilla. Mix nuts with flour and add. Stir only until flour disappears. Bake in 2 greased loaf pans for 1 hour at 350°.

title: meat and cheese strudel
directions: Thaw bread dough and divide into 2 equal portions.
Roll out each portion to 12 x 24-inches.
Make 3-inch slices from outer edge towards center, leaving center intact, approximately 1-inch apart the entire length of both sides (strudel style).
Have ready peppers that have been sliced lengthwise and fried on low heat until tender.
Layer Provolone and pepperoni.
Sprinkle grated cheese, hot ham and peppers down center of dough.
Repeat layer. Fold dough to center (strudel style).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Slice into desired widths and serve.
Great finger food for get-togethers.

title: egg bread
directions: Cut bread into cubes and brown in melted butter.
Beat eggs. Add milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over bread and fry until brown. Serve at once.

title: cajun cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, pineapple and juice, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: classic pound cake
directions: Grease and flour one large or 2 small loaf pans. Cream butter. Gradually add sugar. Beat in vanilla. Add eggs one at a time. Sift flour and salt and add all at once. Beat until smooth. Pour into prepared pan. Bake about 90 minutes at 350°.

title: holiday cheese ring
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Sprinkle 1/4 c. pecans into greased 7 c. ring mold and press cheese into mold; chill until firm.
Remove cheese ring onto platter and pat remaining pecans into cheese ring.
Place jam or preserves in the center of ring.
Serve with crackers, makes 6 cups.
Great!!

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Mix butter, 3 tbsp. sugar and pretzels into a 9 x 13 inch pan; bake 10 minutes at 350°F. Let cool. Mix cream cheese and remaining sugar and cool whip
together, spread over cooled pretzel bottom. Mix jello and water; add the strawberries and let partially gel, then pour over cream cheese. Refrigerate. Serve after jello is set.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Beat egg.
Mix cornstarch and garlic.
Heat the oil; dip wings into egg, then put in the cornstarch and garlic mixture.
Fry in oil.

title: busy day individual meat loaves
directions: Mix beef, salt, crumbs and milk; let stand until crumbs are soft.
Mix in egg, onion flakes, sage, thyme, nutmeg and black pepper.
Shape into loaves.
Place on foil lined baking sheet about 3 inches apart.
Mix the brown sugar, catsup, ginger, soy sauce and mustard; spread over tops of loaves.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, or until done.
Garnish with green pepper, if desired.

title: el grande guacamole
directions: Blend tomato and the sliced avocados.
Add chili peppers, onions, white vinegar, salt, pepper and cilantro.
Mix and chill for one hour in the refrigerator.
Serve with chilled vegetables.

title: birthday cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and Crisco together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix all dry ingredients together and sift.
Add flavorings. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
If you have a very hot oven at 325°, bake at 300° until done.
Do not open door during the first hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an oven dish (size as desired). Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into an oven dish.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: In a large pot, boil potatoes until tender on stove.
Then in a large baking dish, cut potatoes into halves and arrange in baking dish.
Put the ham, butter, salt, pepper and onions on top of potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and add grated cheese, sour cream and bacon bits.
Serve hot.
Serves 10 people.

title: chili 'n' cheese enchiladas
directions: In a large ovenproof skillet, cook ground beef and 1/2 cup onion until tender.
Drain.
Stir in chili seasoning, tomato sauce, tomato paste, chili beans and water.
Simmer uncovered for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine 2 cups cheese and remaining 1 cup chopped onion.
Divide cheese mixture in half.
Arrange one half of the cheese mixture evenly on the tortillas.
Roll up each tortilla and arrange, seam side down, on top of the chili mixture. Top with Picante sauce and remaining cheese mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 - 25 minutes or until heated through.

title: party eggplant parmesan
directions: Combine crumbs, milk, salt and pepper.
Add beef and veal; mix well.
Shape into 8 patties.
Brown on both sides in a small amount of cooking oil.
Remove from skillet.
Peel eggplant.
Cut into 8 thick slices.
Brush lightly with oil; coat with flour. Brown eggplant slices in same skillet.

title: pineapple cherry nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Bake in tube pan.
Will make 1 large cake and 2 small ones.

title: individual cheesecakes
directions: Blend softened cream cheese with sugar, eggs and lemon juice. Place vanilla wafer in bottom of each baking cup (use midget foil baking cups).
Top with blended mixture and bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
When cool, top each cake with 1 teaspoon cherry pie filling.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Steam the cauliflower until it is tender.
Cut it in half. Press one half through a sieve & keep the other half warm.	In a saucepan melt the butter & cook the onion until it is transparent, but not brown.
Carefully stir in the flour & cook until it bubbles, stirring constantly.
Add the chicken stock, stirring constantly.
Mix the scalded milk with the sieved cauliflower, & stir it into the stock.
Season with salt, pepper & a dash of nutmeg.
Let boil up until it thickens slightly, stirring to prevent lumps.
Break the other half of cauliflower into small flowerets & add to the soup.
Heat thoroughly & serve immediately with croutons.
Serves 6 or 8.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Sprinkle chicken with garlic powder.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch dish: broccoli, chicken, cheese, thin coating of soup, onion rings and remainder of soup.
Bake 1 hour uncovered at 350°.

title: banana nut cake(not bread)
directions: Cream sugar and
butter;
then add eggs and Wesson oil. Sift dry ingredients
together.	Add
raisins
and nuts to dry mixture, then add this dry mixture to the creamed ingredients. Mash bananas and fold with the mixture.	Cook for 7 minutes on 400° and then reduce heat to 350° and bake for 1 hour.

title: granny bonnie's mashed potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Boil with margarine until soft.
Pour water off.
Mash with blender and mix.
Add milk; mix well.
Add mayonnaise and salt.
Mix well or until smooth and serve.

title: cabbage rolls - garbage rolls
directions: Mix hamburger, egg, salt, pepper and garlic.
Add enough tomato sauce to moisten.
Add rice and a little more tomato sauce. Place hamburger mixture in cabbage leaves and roll up.
Secure with a toothpick.
Continue until all hamburger is used.
Place in ovenproof dish.
Cover with remaining tomato sauce.
Bake until done, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake in a greased pan at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Cook spaghetti noodles; drain.
Mix spaghetti, Parmesan cheese and egg; spread in bottom of cake pan or glass pan (large).
Cook sausage and drain.
Mix sausage, pepperoni, mushrooms, onion and green pepper.
Spread over spaghetti.
Top with Mozzarella cheese. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: vegetable ranch salad
directions: Combine cauliflower, broccoli, onion, mushrooms and black olives.

title: baked turkey
directions: Rub turkey inside and outside with salt.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Put cover on roaster and cook at 500° for 1 hour. Turn oven off and leave overnight.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Add flavoring. Pour in pie shell.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cook mixed vegetables; drain.
Add beans, celery, onion and green pepper.
Cook and stir sugar, flour, vinegar, mustard and salt and pepper until thick and clear.
Cool.
Mix vegetables and sauce together.
Refrigerate for 8 to 24 hours.

title: ground beef and potato casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, salt and pepper until crumbly; drain.
Place in casserole dish.
Layer next 3 ingredients over ground beef.
Top with soup.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Line bottom of pie shell with 1 cup cheese.
Cover cheese with all broccoli, then cover with the other cup of cheese.
Beat eggs, salt and milk together and pour over top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until golden and firm.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Bring water to boil in a 5-quart pot.
Add broccoli; let come to full boil.
Add soups.
Reduce heat; stir frequently.
Cook until creamy over medium heat for 30 minutes.

title: shoo-fly pies
directions: Add to the crumb mixture and beat.
Makes one 9-inch pie. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes and then 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chewy cake(cookies)
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar.
Add eggs.
Add flour.
Add vanilla, nuts and coconut.
Pour into greased large pan (15 x 10-inch at least).
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sugar and spice pecans
directions: Combine everything except nuts.
Stir in pecans and evenly coat.
Pour onto a foil-lined, sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes at 275°.
Stir occasionally.
Put on waxed paper to cool.
For extra coating, use same amount of pecans and double mixture.

title: chili
directions: Brown half of the ground chuck. Add onions, herbs, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, tomato juice, garlic and mustard. Bring to a rapid boil, stirring often. Add bay leaf. Turn down to a simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add sausage and remaining beef. Boil for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Stir often. Simmer for 2 hours. Add kidney beans the last 15 minutes.

title: two-tone pie
directions: Prepare pastry shell.
Cool.
In saucepan, combine pudding mix and milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Pour 2 cups pudding mix into bowl and add peanut butter chips.
Stir until smooth.
To remaining hot pudding, add chocolate chips.
Stir until smooth.
Pour chocolate mixture into baked pie shell.
Gently pour peanut butter mixture over top. Press plastic wrap directly on top.
Chill several hours.
Garnish. Makes 8 servings.

title: taco soup
directions: Cook chopped onion in a small amount of oil until soft.
Add ground meat and cook until no trace of red remains.
Add the seven cans of vegetables (including juices) and the two packages of seasoning mix.
Bring to a boil, then simmer until ready to serve.

title: standard roll recipe
directions: To water, add next 4 ingredients, then yeast mixture.
Stir well and add 2 cups flour; stir well.
Add shortening; stir.
Add remaining flour and knead well into a ball.
Let rise until double, knead and for crescents, take a portion of the dough and roll as for pie crust.
Cut into triangles, brush with melted butter and roll up, starting with wide side.
Place on greased sheets and let rise again until light.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: easy eggplant  parmigiana
directions: Peel and wash the eggplant.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice the eggplant sideways so that you come out with 12 to 15 "patties". Cut more if you want thinner slices, fewer if you want thicker slices.
Break open the eggs and beat.
Dip the eggplant "patties" into the egg.
Pour breadcrumbs into a separate bowl.
Dip eggplant with egg into bread crumbs.
Brown the patties in the olive oil. Burner should be high to medium-high.
Eggplant does not have to be cooked through just browned.
Cover the bottom of a Pyrex baking dish with eggplant patties.

title: scalloped broccoli or spinach
directions: Cook broccoli or spinach.
Mix soup, eggs, mayonnaise and cheese.
Add to cooked broccoli or spinach.
Salt slightly.
Bake in casserole for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown ground chuck; drain.
Add onion, salt (to taste), pepper, Italian seasoning and tomato sauce.
Blend well.
Roll out crescent rolls slightly and place in 9-inch pie pan to make pie shell.
Place meat mixture in pie shell and top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with sauce.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; beat in eggs, salt and flavoring. Stir in flour.
Blend thoroughly.
Chill.
Roll small portions on floured board to 1/8-inch thickness and cut in shapes with cookie cutters.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 2 to 4 dozen.
Decorate with colored frosting.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Beat margarine, brown sugar, egg and vanilla until blended. Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in zucchini and nuts.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Bake potatoes.
Scoop, mash and mix with all ingredients. Bake until soft (about 35 minutes).
Top with marshmallows and heat until melted.

title: russian tea
directions: Pour 1 pint of boiling water over Jell-O and sugar.
Pour 1 pint of boiling water over tea, cinnamon and cloves.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Strain and mix pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Add 3 quarts of water.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: spicy baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes.
Cut potatoes, unpeeled, into large chunks. Preheat oven to 450°.
Place all ingredients in large plastic bag or bowl. Close and shake or toss until potatoes are evenly coated. Empty potatoes into shallow baking dish or roasting pan.
Bake, stirring occasionally, 40 minutes or until tender and golden brown.

title: peanut butter chocolate kiss cookies
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter; gradually add sugar and brown sugar until fluffy.
Add egg, milk and vanilla, beat well. Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to cream mixture.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls; then roll in 1/4 cup sugar.
Place balls 2 inches apart on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Press a kiss on each cookie. Return to oven for 2 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Put one layer of sauce, then noodles, then meat, then cheeses; repeat one more time.
Make top layer of cheese thick.
Bake at 350° until cheese is brown.

title: candied squash rings
directions: Cut squash into 1-inch thick ring slices; discard seeds. Place in single layer on shallow baking dish.
Season with salt and pepper and bake at 350° for 40 minutes, until almost tender. In saucepan, combine brown sugar, butter and water; cook and stir until bubbly.
Spoon over squash.
Continue baking, uncovered, until squash is tender, about 15 minutes more, basting often.

title: corn pudding(a southern tradition at christmas or anytime)
directions: Mix ingredients (except cinnamon) together and turn into a 2-quart casserole; sprinkle nutmeg or cinnamon on top (or both). Bake at 350° for 1 hour (or until firm in the center).
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: mama's hot breakfast syrup
directions: Cook to a light syrup. Don't overcook and get it too thick.

title: bean hot dish
directions: Fry bacon and add all ingredients, except beans.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Pour over beans and bake covered 60 to 70 minutes at 350°.
Drain juice from beans.
Serves from 15 to 20 people.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Bring water to boil; add oleo.
Remove from heat.
Add flour and salt, then beat in one egg at a time.
Add the cheese.
Put in 1 dozen greased muffin pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Prick each puff with a fork.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: orange pork tenderloin
directions: Mix butter, thyme and cayenne pepper.
Spread evenly over tenderloin.
Place tenderloin in shallow roasting pan.
Pour orange juice over meat.
Roast at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes (150° to 160° on meat thermometer).
Baste during roasting.
Remove tenderloin to serving platter and keep warm.
Measure basting liquid (add additional orange juice if necessary).
Add flour, sugar and bitters.
Cook and stir until mixture boils and thickens.
Cut meat into 1-inch slices.
Serve with sauce.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly peanut butter, margarine, sugar and eggs. Sift and stir in flour, baking pwd. and soda.
Roll in balls and place on greased cookie sheet and mash with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 8-10 min.

title: slush
directions: Freeze and when frozen add 7-Up in glasses.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes very fine.
Mix other ingredients with potatoes.
Fry in olive oil in hot skillet until brown.
One tablespoon of batter makes nice sized pancake.
Serves five. Leftover pancakes can be frozen and reheated.

title: shrimp-crabmeat casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery and green peppers in butter until tender but not brown.
Add remaining ingredients except bread crumbs; stir well.
Spoon mixture into 2 lightly greased 2-quart casseroles. Sprinkle each with 1/2 cup bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until bubbly.
Yields 20 servings.

title: old fashioned fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa, add milk, 1/2 cup at a time, until combined.
Bring to a rolling boil, reduce heat to medium.
Cook until mixture forms a soft ball when dropped from a spoon into a cup of cold water.
Remove from heat, add margarine and vanilla. Beat on high speed with electric mixer until fudge starts to thicken.
Pour into lightly buttered plate or glass dish.
Cut into squares after it has set for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and beat well.
Mix cocoa and water; add to egg mixture; blend.
Sift together dry ingredients; add small amount alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Add vanilla and blend.
Drop onto lightly greased cookie sheet by rounded teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool and frost with chocolate or vanilla frosting. Top with colored sprinkles.

title: ima's cherry yum-yums
directions: Mix crumbs with butter. Spread half of this mixture in bottom of a large pan.

Cream together the cream cheese and sugar. Fold in Dream Whip. Beat until very stiff, then spread half of the mixture on the crust. Spread the cherry pie filling on cream cheese mixture. Add rest of Dream Whip mixture and top with rest of crumbs. Chill for 24 hours.

title: beef jambalaya
directions: Add oil to Dutch oven.
Cook chopped onion and bell pepper to tender.
Add water, rice, tomatoes and spices.
Cube beef sausage. Add to Dutch oven.
Cover with water.
Simmer until water is almost gone.

title: nugget cake
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lazy pie
directions: Melt oleo in pie pan.
Make batter with dry ingredients and milk.
Pat into pan with oleo.
Pour fruit on top (this is juicy). Bake at 350° until brown.

title: pineapple-coconut pie
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add crushed pineapple and coconut.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° until firm, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Mix together and pour into 3 cake pans. Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes. Check for doneness.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Day before:
In deep kettle, place chicken, water, 2 teaspoons salt, onion salt and celery salt.
Simmer, covered, until chicken is tender, 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
As chicken cooks, add a little water, if necessary.
Remove bird to bowl and reserve broth.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix the tuna and mayonnaise.
Boil the noodles until soft and tender.
Drain the noodles and rinse.
Boil the peas, adding a little butter and salt until tender.
Drain and rinse peas.
Mix all the ingredients together.
Enjoy.

title: layered fruit salad
directions: Rinse grapes; cut in half and remove seeds.
Place in bottom of glass serving bowl.
Peel and slice bananas; layer over grapes. Drain peaches well; layer over bananas.
Rinse raspberries; sprinkle over peaches.
Peel oranges; place on top of raspberries. Peel and slice kiwi to garnish salad.
Pour orange juice over salad.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: tuna stuffed tomato
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients. Stuff tomato with mixture and garnish with pimento. Serves 1.

title: citrus cream punch
directions: Combine lemonade, orange concentrate and water in large pitcher.
Place sherbet and ice cream in punch bowl.
Pour liquid over ice cream.
Stir until fairly well dissolved.
May add a bottle of ginger ale if desired.
Makes about 5 quarts.

title: bread and butter crisp pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in pickling lime, in water to cover, for 24 hours.
Rinse two times and drain.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk and vanilla.
Add jam and beat well.
Bake in a greased and floured pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients (except bread).
Cut hole in center of bread, pulling out bread from inside to make hollow.
Fill with dip and arrange bread pieces for dipping.
Chill dip before serving, 2 to 3 hours.
Better overnight.

title: moss rose cake
directions: Heat milk to boiling and cool.
Break eggs over sugar and beat for 12 minutes.
Sift flour twice.
Add to egg and sugar mixture. Add warm milk slowly to batter and beat 3 minutes.
Bake in 2 layers at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: finger jello
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Cool, then add Knox gelatine.
Chill in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut in bars.
Yum!

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatine in cold water.
Add hot water, sugar and salt.
Dissolve.
Add lemon juice and the pineapple and put in refrigerator for about 45 minutes.
Take out of refrigerator and mix with large Cool Whip.
Add mixture to broken angel food cake. Pour into long dish and spread out.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Soften margarine and cream cheese; blend until smooth.
Add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour and baking powder together and add to creamed mixture, 1/3 cup at a time.
Add flavorings.
Bake in a well-greased 10-inch tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: "veggie casserole"
directions: Mix together the first 7 items and pour into casserole dish. Mix Ritz crackers and melted butter or oleo together; spread on top of the casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Happy eating!

title: roast chicken dressing
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Use as a dressing to rub into chicken before roasting.

title: golden brown oven-fried chicken
directions: Combine
first
ingredients;
mix well.
Dip chicken pieces in sour cream mixture.
Dredge in stuffing mix.
Place chicken in
a
lightly
greased
13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Drizzle with butter and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a tube pan or 3 small loaf pans.
Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Gradually add oil; then add sugar, vanilla, zucchini and pineapple.
Gradually mix in dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts.

title: onion topped green beans
directions: Place beans (drained) in 2-quart glass dish (covered). Microwave on High 7 to 8 minutes.
Add water chestnuts.
Spread soup over beans.
Top with onions.
Cook on High 5 minutes.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes.

title: sunny day salad
directions: Bring orange juice to a boil.
Add jello
and stir until dissolved.
Add cold water and oranges; stir until well mixed. Pour into 8 or 10-inch square dish.
Refrigerate until set.
Top with Cool Whip when served.
Add sherbet just before pouring into square dish.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray angel food pan with Pam or any cooking spray.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat 2 to 3 minutes until bananas are blended with cake mix.
Pour into pan and bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Serve plain or with ice cream.
I like it best fresh from the oven with a cup of hot tea.

title: healthful punch
directions: Mix together all ingredients except ginger ale and freeze. Take out about 3 or 4 hours before serving.
Add ginger ale and mix well.
This should be a good, slushy drink.

title: nanny's chocolate pie
directions: Scald milk; mix sugar, flour, chocolate, salt and milk.
Cook until thick.
Add beaten egg yolks, vanilla and butter.
Cook slowly until very thick.
Pour into baked pie shell and chill.

title: vidalia onion relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions in food processor.
Combine vinegar, sugar and pickling spice; boil for 10 minutes.
Add peppers and onions.
Cook until they change colors.
Pack into jars and seal.

title: carolina style barbecue sauce
directions: In a medium saucepan combine the vinegar, mustard, sugar, water, chili powder, pepper and Tabasco. Simmer for 25 minutes. Add the soy sauce and butter and simmer for 5 minutes longer. Use as
you would any barbecue sauce. Great for grilled chicken or pork.

title: microwave casserole italiano
directions: Crumble beef into 3-quart microwavable casserole.
Cook at High (100%) power for 3 minutes.
Stir; break up meat.
Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients (except cheese); blend well. Cover and cook on High (100%) power 12 minutes.
Stir. Cover and cook on Medium (60%) 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover; let stand 10 minutes.

title: sweet beets
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat, stirring occasionally. Serves 6.

title: delicious oatmeal bread
directions: Pour boiling water over the oats and let stand 30 minutes. Add molasses, soft butter and salt. Dissolve yeast in real warm water and add to oat mixture. Beat and work in enough of the flour to make a medium soft dough. Turn onto a floured board; knead until smooth, about 10 minutes. Place dough in a clean, well oiled bowl. Turn to grease the top; cover and let rise until double in bulk, about 40 minutes.

title: layer salad
directions: Cut (or break) lettuce in bite sizes and place in a 9 x 12-inch container.
Add all other ingredients in order given, over lettuce, layer upon layer.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: rum cake
directions: Dump all ingredients in a bowl.
Mix 3 minutes. Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sourdough starter and bread
directions: Combine flour, yeast and 1 tablespoon of sugar in a nonmetal mixing bowl.
Combine 3 tablespoons of instant potatoes with 2 cups of warm water and stir into flour mixture.
Cover with loose aluminum foil and let stand in warm place for 48 hours.
Take out 1 cup and store in refrigerator.
Discard the rest or share with a friend.
Keep Starter covered with foil for 3 to 5 days.

title: cherry nut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In 3-quart mixer bowl, combine flour, oats, sugar, pecans, soda and butter. Mix at low speed, scraping sides of bowl often, until crumbly (2 to 3 minutes). Reserve 1 1/2 cups crumb mixture for topping. Press remaining crumb mixture evenly into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake near center of 350° oven for 15 minutes or until lightly brown at edges. Gently spoon pie filling evenly over partially baked crust; sprinkle with marshmallows and then reserved crumb mixture. Return to oven for 25 to 35 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool. Cut into bars.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook hen or fryer in a small amount of water until tender. Do not cover chicken completely for too much flavor will leach out.
The chicken will add juices.
A hen could take 2 hours, a fryer much less.

title: double chocolate chip cookies
directions: Pour 1/2 box of cake mix in bowl.
Add eggs, vanilla and melted butter; stir.
Add last of cake mix.
Chips and nuts can be added if you want.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 12 minutes.

title: antipasto
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Serve on crackers.

title: easy mexican casserole
directions: Place onions and corn chips in 2-quart casserole.
Add beans, chili and water; put cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mints
directions: Mix.
Roll into small balls and press with fork.

title: pecan pie
directions: Prepare pastry.
Heat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, salt, butter and syrup.
Beat with rotary beater until blended.
With a wooden spoon or spatula, stir in the pecan halves. (Do not chop them.)
Pour into a pastry lined pan.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge of pan comes out clean.
Use an 8 or 9-inch pan.

title: italian sausage soup
directions: Brown sausage and onion in skillet.
Combine sausage, onion, chicken broth, tomatoes and spices in a kettle.
Cook for 1 hour. Add rosamarina and cook for another 20 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and add margarine.
In a 2-quart baking dish, grate 3 ounces Cheddar cheese.
Pour half of the macaroni over cheese.
Grate 2 ounces more cheese over macaroni.
Now add remaining macaroni and grate 3 ounces cheese over top of this.
Pour sweet milk over the casserole until it is covered.
Place in a preheated 370° oven and bake until bubbly and brown on top.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach and drain.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Form into walnut-size balls.
Bake at 325 degrees for 20 minutes. Serve warm.
Makes 50 to 60 balls.

title: extra good pot roast
directions: Place roast, soup mix and mushroom soup in crock-pot on high for 30 minutes.
Turn down on low.
Cook all day.
Add vegetables last hour, if desired.

title: pound candy
directions: Mix all ingredients but the nuts and vanilla.
Cook, cook, cook until soft ball stage; cook on low (will burn easy) until melted, then on high.
Be careful, will scorch.
After reaching soft ball stage, remove from stove and let cool.
Beat with beater as long as you can, then beat with spoon.
Add 2 cups English walnuts (more nuts used makes it better) and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Pour into buttered pan.
Slice into squares when cool.

title: favorite pancakes
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Bake on hot, lightly greased griddle.

title: melon-mint medley
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Chill 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Serves 6.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Saut onion in butter. Add ham, corned beef and garlic; heat. Stir in 6 tablespoons flour and egg. Cook, stirring, until well blended. Drain sauerkraut and put through food chopper. Add to meat mixture with salt, Worcestershire sauce, parsley and stock. Cook until mixture forms a thick paste. Spread on a platter; chill. Shape into 1-inch balls. Dip balls in batter made of milk and remaining flour. Roll in crumbs. Fry in deep 375° fat until brown. Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: apricot glazed chicken
directions: Spray large baking pan with Pam.
Mix oil, dressing, preserves, salt and soup mix.
Pour over chicken which has been placed in a single layer, skin up, in a baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour, until tender.
Baste occasionally.
Good served with rice.

title: braised string beans
directions: Cut off ends of beans and wash in cold water.
Cut into pieces or slice lengthwise.
In medium saucepan, saute onions in oil until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer. Cooking time is 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat together oil and honey. Add eggs, vanilla and zucchini. Sift dry ingredients and add to liquid mixture.
Stir in optionals. Bake in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Eat warm or refrigerate or freeze.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix and freeze in Pyrex dish.
Take out 1 hour prior to serving.
Refreeze and so on.
Keeps a long time.

title: confetti dip
directions: Cream the cream cheese and margarine.
Add other ingredients. Add Tabasco and Season-All.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Drain shrimp. Mash shrimp in a medium size bowl with a fork. Mix in horseradish and cocktail sauce.
Pour mixture over cream cheese in a serving dish. Serve with your favorite choice of crackers (Triscuits, Wheat Thins, etc.).

title: beef barbecue
directions: Place in large kettle the chuck roast, 1 large onion, (chopped), salt and enough water to cover the meat.
Cook several hours until meat falls apart.
Shred meat with fork or use a blender (set aside).

title: all bran yeast bread
directions: Dissolve yeast cake in warm water.
Pour boiling water over All-Bran.
Add oil, sugar and salt.
Let set long enough to cool. Add yeast, eggs and 3 cups flour and beat well.
Add 3 more cups flour, or enough to mix.
Knead dough; let rise 1 1/2 hours or until doubled.
Knead dough.
Shape into 3 loaves and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: pizzaghetti
directions: Cook and stir sausage in oil in 10-inch skillet over medium heat until light brown, about 6 minutes.
Drain.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, basil, salt, garlic powder and pepper. Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally for 10 minutes.
Cook spaghetti as directed on package; drain.
Stir corn (with liquid) and olives into sausage mixture.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti; top each serving with a cheese slice.
Makes 5 servings.
tags: whole kernel corn with sweet peppers

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Brown bacon and drain most of grease off.
Add onion and brown.
Add 3 cups water, sugar, vinegar, bouillon and salt. Bring to boil.
Blend cornstarch and cold water and add to hot mixture.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over lettuce salad or spinach salad.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients together, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° until pie is golden brown.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; beat well.
Add eggs. Beat again. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop small balls of dough on cookie sheets and flatten slightly with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: easy meat and potatoes
directions: Crumble beef into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with chopped onion.
Cover with grated cheese.
Spread soup (undiluted) over the top.
Cover with Tater Tots.
Do not stir.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.
Serves 4.

title: creole shrimp dip
directions: Melt margarine.
Add chopped shrimp and saute until pink. Allow to cool.
Blend all other ingredients (except chives) until smooth.
Add chives and chill.
Serves 24.

title: taco mac and cheese
directions: Brown meat. Drain. Stir in 2 3/4 cups water, salsa and chili powder. Bring to a boil; stir in macaroni. Cover. Simmer 10 minutes or until water is almost absorbed. Add Velveeta; stir until melted. Top with crushed tortilla chips, chopped green onions and tomatoes. Makes 6 servings.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic with fat in hot skillet.
Stir in meat, flour and seasonings.
Cook about 5 minutes, until meat is browned.
Add mushrooms and soup.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and gently heat.
Season to taste.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat, onion and green chilies in large skillet; drain fat off if necessary. Place meat mixture in a large pan; add rest of ingredients. Heat and simmer about 30 minutes. Makes 4 to 5 quarts and can be frozen.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Sift flour 3 times.
Add to batter in three additions.
Stir in vanilla and orange rind.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Cream together sour cream and cream cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add to sour cream mixture.
Place in center of relish tray.

title: garbage breakfast eggs
directions: Combine eggs and 1 cup cheese.
In skillet, cook potatoes and ham in hot oil for 8 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Add egg mixture.
Cook, stirring occasionally until eggs are cooked. Put on serving plate and top with remaining cheese.
Serve!
Serves 2 people.

title: tea cakes
directions: Melt butter.
Sift the flour.
Cream balance of ingredients until smooth.
Roll thin and place on cookie sheet at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Place dry milk and oatmeal in a bowl. Add peanut butter and honey. Mix well and shape into balls, then they are ready to eat. Store in airtight container.

title: apple balls
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute. Add 3 cups rolled oats (quick cooking) and 1 cup chopped nuts. Mix well. Drop on wax paper. Then roll in balls and coat in powdered sugar.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into greased 2-quart dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir after 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned banana pudding(low-fat)
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar and cornstarch in heavy pan.
Gradually stir in water, milk and egg substitute.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Fold in sour cream and vanilla.

title: pineapple chicken bake
directions: Brush chicken with margarine; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Place chicken in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes.
Combine next six (6) ingredients; stirring well.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake for 20 minutes longer, basting occasionally.
Serve over rice.

title: tonnarelli
directions: Saute ham in margarine.
Cook noodles as directed and drain when done.
Heat peas.
Toss peas, ham and cheese into noodles and serve.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice
tomatoes;
salt
and pepper, then coat with corn meal. Fry slowly in hot fat until brown, turning once.

title: bean salad
directions: Blend all vegetables together.
Bring sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper to a boil.
Let cool.
Pour over vegetable mixture and chill for 24 hours.

title: baked brisket(4 pound brisket)
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over brisket, then wrap in foil. Marinate overnight.
Bake at 300° for 3 1/2 hours.
Add 1 cup barbecue sauce and bake 1 hour longer.
Recipe may be doubled for larger brisket and increase baking time 2 hours.

title: coconut dream cake
directions: Make cake by directions on box.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan. While hot, punch it full of holes with a toothpick.
Mix milk and cream of coconut.
Pour over hot cake.
Cool.
Spread drained pineapple over cake.
Now, spread Cool Whip on top of pineapple. Sprinkle coconut on top.
Store in refrigerator.

title: nanny's meat loaf
directions: Mix the first five ingredients; form into a loaf in a baking pan.
Squeeze a layer of ketchup over the top; smooth out. Sprinkle a desired amount of brown sugar over ketchup layer.
Cut slices of bacon in half and lay the slices across the loaf.
Bake in a moderately hot oven (350° to 375°) for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: ginger ale punch
directions: Dissolve 3 packages strawberry jello in 9 cups boiling water. Bring 4 cups water and 4 cups sugar to fast boil.
Add jello mixture and let cool.
Add lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Stir well and put in plastic containers to freeze.
Scrape frozen mixture into punch bowl; add cold ginger ale to make slush.
Will serve approximately 50.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Combine until smooth the cream cheese, egg, 1/3 cup sugar and 1/8 teaspoon salt.
Add chocolate chips; set aside.

title: no crust fudge pie
directions: Melt butter in pie pan.
Beat eggs, then mix sugar, flour, cocoa and salt.
Add to eggs and then add vanilla.
Pour margarine out of pie pan into mixture.
Beat well and then put mixture back into the pie pan.
Cook at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: 7 layer bars
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Dust with crumbs. Sprinkle on coconut, chocolate and butterscotch.
Pour milk evenly over top and sprinkle on nuts.
Press lightly into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Makes 40 (1 x 2-inch) bars.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Add other ingredients and cook on low heat or put in a crock-pot.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add water and heat.
Mix beaten egg yolks with a small amount of filling and stir into filling mixture.
Cook, stirring continually, until mixture thickens.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in 325° oven until meringue is evenly browned.
Makes 2 pies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix 1/2 cup cheese (saving 1/4 cup to sprinkle on top) and chicken in a small bowl.
Separate rolls.
Put 2 tablespoons of chicken mix on each roll.
Roll up short end first.

title: sea breeze salad mold
directions: Heat remaining beef broth to boiling.
Pour over softened gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Cool slightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold or 9 x 9 Pyrex dish.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Drain. Combine with rest of ingredients in large pan.
Simmer for 3 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: "not so sweet" homemade ice cream
directions: Add 1 pint peaches, strawberries or whatever fruit you prefer or leave as plain vanilla flavor.
Churn for 20 to 30 minutes. Makes 1/2 gallon of ice cream.
For a sweeter ice cream, use a pint of strawberries or peaches from your freezer that have been sweetened to your taste.

title: mushroom casserole("a favorite from the '76 cookbook.")
directions: Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Slice the mushrooms.
Add to the casserole.
Melt the butter and add all the other ingredients, except cream.
Mix until blended.
Then add the cream.
Pour mixture over the mushrooms.
Bake at 375° for 55 minutes.

title: grilled pineapple
directions: Shuck corn; wash and cut thusly:
Barely tip the kernels and rub back of knife over cob to get all the juice.
Put a good amount of oil (not butter) in heavy pan.
Saute onions, green pepper and a little garlic a few minutes.
Add corn mixture and a lot of water. Cook on medium heat with lid partly on.
Stir occasionally.
Add more water if needed.
Do not add salt until dish is finished because it will make it tough.
About halfway done (30 or 40 minutes), add some sugar to taste.
Later add a good amount of butter.
It is cooked when oil forms around the edges, about an hour.
Add green onions and parsley if desired.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Remember, plenty of water, oil and butter.
Good luck! Keep lid partly on.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.
Makes enough for 1 head of cabbage.
This dressing is tangy, not sweet like most others.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs, vanilla and sugar.
Stir in rice and milk until well mixed.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: banana bread
directions: Grease a loaf pan or line bottom with wax paper; grease paper. In a large bowl, cream shortening with sugar, sift flour, measure and sift again with soda and salt. Add alternately the flour with eggs and bananas to the cream mixture. Add vanilla and nuts. Place in loaf pan. Bake in 325° oven for 1 hr and 20 min or until golden and a wooden pick inserted in middle comes out clean. Loosen around edges with knife and turn out onto rack. Peel off waxed paper. Let cool completely.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Mix cornstarch, beef broth and soy sauce; set aside.
Heat oil in wok or skillet until hot.
Add meat and garlic.
Stir-fry until meat is no longer pink.
Add onion and peppers; stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in cornstarch mixture. Stir-fry until sauce thickens slightly.

title: quick orange bread
directions: Sift the dry ingredients.
Add milk, butter and beaten egg; beat well.
Add orange peel; mix.
Place in a greased loaf pan and let rise for about 15 minutes.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: crab cakes
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl and mix gently with fingers so that the lumps of crab are not broken up.
Make into cakes and broil until well browned.

title: the sun ball
directions: Beat cream cheese with mustard, garlic powder and wine until smooth.
Beat in olives, Cheddar cheese and parsley.
Form into a ball, wrap in waxed paper and chill.
Roll in sunflower seeds. Garnish with whole olives and parsley, if you wish.

title: sausage roll puffs
directions: Roll pastry into 15 1/2 x 9-inch rectangle and cut into 3 strips (3-inches wide each). Divide sausage meat into 3 sections. Roll each section in a "snake" the length of the pastry strips. Roll the pastry around the sausage. Wet edges with water and press to seal. Chill 1 hour. Heat oven to 400°. Cut sausage rolls into 1/2-inch slices and put them on parchment-covered baking sheets. Bake until golden, 12 minutes. Can be frozen.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: On each chicken breast, place a piece of cheese and ham. Sprinkle with basil.
Roll up the breast, starting with small end. Secure with a toothpick.

title: chili in a wok
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper in wok.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, kidney beans and water.
Season with garlic, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Makes 4 servings.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Sift flour, then measure.
Heat milk.

Put sugar, shortening and salt in a large bowl. Add hot milk. Stir until shortening is melted. Cool to lukewarm, about 15 minutes. Add crumbled yeast. Mix well. Add flour. Stir until dough leaves sides of bowl. Cover bowl with damp cloth.
Let stand and rise in warm place until light and double in bulk, about 2 hours.
Punch down.
Place on lightly floured board.
Knead until dough is smooth.
Mold into desired shapes.
Place on greased pan. Cover with damp cloth. Let rise in warm place until double in bulk, about 30 minutes.
Brush with glaze mixture of 1 part sugar and 2 parts milk. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until done.
Makes 3 dozen rolls.

title: dang good pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add pineapple, slightly beaten eggs, coconut and melted butter.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 60 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: bacon-cheese potatoes(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Place potato slices in a large baking pan; cover with onion slices.
Season with salt and pepper; dot with butter.
Sprinkle bacon over vegetables and cover with cheese slices.
Seal foil tightly.
Bake about 1 hour at 350° or until potatoes are done.

title: sugar free orange delight
directions: Gently fold cottage cheese, crushed pineapple and dry gelatin into whipped topping.
Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled.

title: macaroni salad
directions: In large mixing bowl, stir together mayonnaise, milk, vinegar, salt, sugar and pepper.
Add cooked macaroni, celery, onion and eggs; toss to coat well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: tea-cake cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs with fork.
Melt and stir in butter and vanilla.
Blend in sugar.
Mix flour and baking powder into mixture.

title: chicken wiggle
directions: In large pot, boil chicken until tender in good amount of broth.
Remove chicken broth and cool, then bone and cut up into small pieces.
Cook noodles in broth until done.
Add cut up chicken and other ingredients and let simmer until flavor mixes well.

title: crazy cake
directions: Measure all the dry ingredients into an 8 or 9-inch square or round cake pan.
Blend together thoroughly with a fork.
Mix wet ingredients and pour directly over everything in the pan.
Stir with fork until everything is well blended.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mini quiches
directions: Grease 2 dozen (1 3/4-inch) muffin pans.
Separate each dinner roll in half; press into muffin pans to make shell.
Place 1 shrimp in each shell.
Combine egg, cream, brandy, salt and pepper.
Divide evenly among shells, using about 2 teaspoons for each.
Slice the cheese into 24 small triangles and place one atop each appetizer.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool; wrap in foil and freeze.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in mixer. Fold in Cool Whip. Fill crusts and freeze. Makes 3 pies. Serve frozen. Drizzle with chocolate syrup before serving.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple and dry pudding mix in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix completely.
Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: *ginger cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and molasses.
Add egg and beat.
Sift together flour, spices, soda and salt.
Add to mixture.
Mix well. Shape into size of a small walnut and roll in granulated sugar. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: pasta fagioli
directions: In a saucepan, fry the garlic and onion in the oil until golden brown.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Let cook 10 minutes. Add beans (with juice); stir gently and continue to simmer.
Cook macaroni al dente; drain.
Add to bean mixture.
Stir.
If too thick, add a little more water.
Add parsley, salt and pepper. Serve immediately or else the pasta will absorb all the liquid. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Al dente means firm.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.
Drop balls on a cookie sheet from a teaspoon.
Make crisscrosses with a fork.
Bake until done.

title: tabbouleh
directions: Pour 4 cups boiling water over burghul.
Drain and squeeze through cheesecloth to eliminate all water.
Mix burghul, onions, salt and pepper together, crushing onion juice into burghul with fingers.
Add remaining ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: canned pork sausage
directions: Season sausage to taste (or follow directions on Old Plantation seasoning).
Make patties, fry until brown and pack into jars within 1-inch from top.
Seal.
Process 75 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.

title: midnight brownies
directions: In saucepan mix pudding mix and milk.
Cook until thickened. Remove from heat.
Add dry cake mix and half the chocolate chips. Mix well.
Turn into greased brownie pan.
Sprinkle remaining chocolate chips and nuts over the top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the potato chips, and put in a shallow casserole.
Sprinkle the crushed potato chips over the top.
Bake at 350° for an hour (until firm and browned).
Serves 6 or 8.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine pepper, onion, carrots and water in pan and simmer 5 to 7 minutes until crisp tender.

title: meat ball soup
directions: Mix all ingredients well; form into 1-inch balls.
Chill.

title: cheese dip
directions: Put all 3 ingredients in crock-pot, mixing occasionally until all melted and blended together well.
Serve with nacho chips, salsa, jalapeno peppers or olives.

title: spicy punch
directions: Steep tea 10 minutes with cinnamon.
Remove and add sugar. To serve pour into 2 gallon punch bowl and add 2 quarts ginger ale.
Freeze ginger ale ice cubes.
Slice lemon and tuck in mint leaves and float on punch.
I used pineapple sage leaves in hot tea and lemon balm.

title: orange-cheese spread
directions: Blend cream cheese, salt, grated onion, grated orange peel and minced pulp of orange.
Cut bread with small biscuit cutter. Spread cream cheese mixture on bread.
Garnish with walnut halves.

title: sweet pickle sticks
directions: Wash and cut fresh, firm, medium size cucumbers into sticks. Pour boiling water over them and let stand 4 to 5 hours.
Drain and pack solidly into jars.
Make a solution of ingredients.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Pour boiling water over the cucumbers in jars. Seal and process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.
Makes 9 pints.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine cinnamon, brown sugar, pepper, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, onion, salt, water, catsup, vinegar and nutmeg.
Heat to boiling.

title: etta's macaroni and cheese
directions: Alternate in deep baking dish layers of macaroni, cheese, butter, pepper, and saltines.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Cover with milk.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Put in pan with just enough water to cover potatoes.
Add salt, pepper and onions.
Simmer until tender.
Add milk and butter and heat for 5 minutes.

title: cranberry orange muffins
directions: Into bowl, sift together flour, the 2 tablespoons sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make well in center.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir just until moistened.
Spoon half the batter into 12 (2 1/2-inch) greased muffin cups.
Top each with 1 teaspoon cranberry-orange relish, then fill with remaining batter.

title: vegetable meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, potato, carrots, onion, salt, pepper, and cheese together in a large bowl.
Roll into meatballs 1-2 inches in diameter.
Place in baking dish and bake at 350° until almost done (approximately 20 minutes).
Drain.
Pour soup over meatballs. Place back into oven, and bake until meatballs are finished (15 minutes).
Crackers, eggs, chili powder, garlic and cumin make good additions to this recipe!

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water until mixture will spin a little thread.
Add peanuts and cook, stirring constantly, until light brown.
Remove from heat.
Add paraffin and soda, stirring fast and well.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat shortening; add brown sugar and mix well.
Add white sugar and mix well.
Add eggs and vanilla; stir in flour, soda and salt.
Add oats and raisins (nuts optional).
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Shape into balls before baking.

title: quick curry of chicken
directions: Prepare chickens for saute.
Heat butter in a large skillet until bubbly and add cut up, salted and peppered chicken.
Brown well on both sides.
When nicely browned, add 1/4 cup dry white wine, reduce the heat and continue cooking.

After 10 minutes, add the white onions, put through the grinder or chopped very fine. To this, add a tablespoon, or more if you like strong flavor of curry, of good curry powder, mixed with 2 tablespoons of white wine.
Cover and cook for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove the cover and test for tenderness, turning the chicken again so that all sides of the pieces are bathed in the curry sauce.
When the chicken is tender, remove the pieces to a hot platter to keep hot.

title: mincemeat
directions: Mix together.
Wait 3 hours.
Let cool down for 1 hour.

title: apricot salad
directions: Add to Jell-O and congeal until hard.

title: butterfly pork chops
directions: Brown the pork chops in oil in frying pan.
Pour off drippings.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add water.
Cover tightly and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour, or until done.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: italian frozen dessert
directions: Dip each cookie on varigated side in rum quickly and place in cake pan; then add a layer of marshmallows, syrup, nuts, ice cream, cherries and whipped cream.
Freeze.

title: zucchini drop cookies
directions: Mix zucchini, baking soda, sugar, shortening and egg.
Sift in flour, cinnamon and salt.
Stir to blend.
Stir in nuts, chips, etc.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: tamale pie
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine corn muffin mix, egg and milk just until moistened.
In 8-inch square baking dish, combine ground beef, sausage, onion and garlic.
Microwave at High (10) 6 to 9 minutes, until meat loses pink color; stir after 3 minutes. Drain.
Stir in tomatoes, corn, tomato paste, chili powder, salt and onions.
Spread corn muffin mixture over meat mixture.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken; season to taste.
Use broth to cook your spaghetti in.
Cut chicken up into pieces.
While this is boiling, melt cheese down and add Ro-Tel tomatoes (drained) and chicken pieces.
Add all this to the spaghetti.
Put in a large dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until it thickens.

title: peppered cheese ball
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Roll in seasoned pepper.

title: pickled beets
directions: Boil beets until tender; cool and peel.
If too large to leave whole, cut into pieces.
Mix all the ingredients together; add beets.
Bring to a boil and simmer 20 minutes.
Put in hot jars and seal.
I put mine in hot water bath for 15 minutes.

title: italian loaves
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; stir in salt.
Add 2 cups flour; beat on low with electric mixer 1/2 minute.
Beat for 3 minutes at high speed.
Stir in remaining flour to make a very stiff dough. Cover and let rise until double.
Turn onto lightly floured surface.
Knead 10 to 12 times.
Halve the dough; cover and let rise until double.
Punch dough down.

title: orange drop cookies
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients; beat in eggs.
Slowly beat in buttermilk, peel, juice and vanilla.
Stir together flour, baking powder, soda and salt; blend into batter.
Stir in chopped nuts. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Pecan half may be placed on each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: gumdrop fruit cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs and applesauce and beat together. Sift dry ingredients together. Mix soda with water. Add to creamed mixture. Add vanilla. Fold in raisins, gumdrops and nuts. Bake in 3 greased loaf pans (4 x 18-inch) for 2 1/2 to 3 hours in slow oven (250°).

title: canollis
directions: Mix together and add to canollis shells.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: curried chicken and vegetable salad dish
directions: In a large bowl, blend together first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients; toss and serve.
Makes 4 servings. Approximate calories, 300/serving.
Approximate fat per serving, 12 grams.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix by directions on the box.
Pour over coconut and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Turn out on cake dish.
Mix sugar, margarine and cream cheese together. Spread over top of cake.

title: yogurt-cool whip pie
directions: Fold yogurt into Cool Whip.
Spoon into pie crust.
Freeze 4 hours.
Remove from freezer 30 minutes before serving.

title: poultry dressing(serves 10)
directions: Mix all ingredients together; put in pan. Bake in 350° oven until done.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Cook raisins in 2 cups of cold water for 15 minutes.
Add shortening and sugar; dissolve.
Add cold water and baking soda. Mix dry ingredients.
Add raisin mixture to dry.
Mix well.
Place in a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mozzarella cheese sticks
directions: Slice the Mozzarella into flat wedges or strips. Prepare 1 bowl with flour, 1 bowl with beaten eggs and 1 bowl with bread crumbs. Take each Mozzarella strip and coat with flour, beaten egg and then bread crumbs. Immediately after coating, fry each stick in hot oil (about 1/4-inch deep) for 1 or 2 minutes on each side until breading is golden brown and cheese is melted.

title: pea casserole
directions: Add salt, pepper and flour to meat.
Cook and drain noodles. Then alternate a layer of noodles followed by a layer of meat, etc.
Top with peas.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together and then refrigerate until able to roll into a ball and then roll into crushed nuts or parsley. Makes 1 large or 2 small balls.

title: crab quiche
directions: Mix all the ingredients and put in pie shell.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let stand at least 5 minutes before cutting.
Serve with a fruit or vegetable salad.

title: pecan-snowball cookies
directions: Cream margarine and 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Add vanilla. Blend flour and salt into creamed mixture.
Add nuts and blend well.
Shape dough into 1-inch diameter balls.
Place onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until set but not browned, about 10 minutes.
Remove from oven; place on cooling rack with waxed paper under rack.
Sift powdered sugar over cookies.
Yield: 50.

title: range burgers
directions: Mix pork and beans with barbecue sauce.
Spoon over burgers on buns.
Sprinkle with chopped bell pepper and onion.

title: penuche
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add sugar and milk; stir until dissolved.
Boil until the soft ball stage.
Remove from heat. Leave undisturbed until cool.
Beat as for chocolate fudge.
Stir in nuts.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Geese and ducks have a strong flavor and are improved by stuffing the craw and body with cored and quartered apples.
The apples absorb the strong flavor, therefore should not be eaten. Celery and onions are also placed in the duck to improve the taste.

title: butterscotch oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and add eggs and then hot water.
Add flour, soda, salt, nuts, oatmeal, chips and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: pecan topping
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a small bowl.
Cut in butter with a pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add water; add shredded cabbage and cook covered for a 1/2 hour.
In separate pan, prepare noodles (your choice).
After noodles are cooked, add to cabbage and cook for 5 minutes.

title: can of biscuits
directions: Open can and put in pan!

title: goop
directions: Stir table salt and 2/3 cup water over low heat to medium heat for 4 to 5 minutes.
