Remove from heat.
Mix cornstarch with 1/2 cup water and add to first mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Return mixture to low heat and continue to stir.
The "goop" will thicken quickly.
Use for modeling.
Does not tend to crumble when unfired.
Store unused portions in plastic bag or airtight can.

title: diet golden crumb crust
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine crumbs, Sugar Twin and cinnamon.
Blend in margarine.
Press firmly in 9-inch pie pan. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes until edges brown slightly.
Cool and fill with any type of filling.

title: marshmallow creme meringue
directions: Beat eggs and salt until they peak.
Gradually add Marshmallow Creme.

title: tofu banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender, except the bran.
After apples are blended, in small chunks, pour into bowl and mix in bran. Pour mixture into Pam-sprayed loaf tin.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Turn out onto a rack.
Cool.

title: french glace pie
directions: *You can use strawberries, raspberries, blackberries, blueberries or pitted sweet cherries.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Cook and bone chicken; reserve 2 cups of broth.
Melt margarine and mix with dressing mix.
Dilute cream of mushroom soup and cream of chicken soup with 1 cup of broth.
Layer in large baking dish, beginning with dressing, then chicken.
Add remaining dressing and pour the other cup of broth over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: dr. murphy's famous cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix together all these ingredients.
Add chocolate chips, Hershey bar and nuts.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix well and pour over chicken, pork chops or ribs, beef or ribs. Bake according to kind of meat and thickness.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup; cook in microwave on High 5 minutes.
Add peanuts.
Cook 3 minutes more on High.
Remove from microwave and stir in butter and baking soda.
Pour on greased cookie sheet. When cool, crack into pieces.

title: sausage and rice casserole(great to take to a potluck)
directions: Fry pork, breaking up lumps; drain off fat.
Mix all ingredients and add to sausage; mix well.
Pour mixture into a large casserole, cover and bake for about 2 hours at 325°.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until fine.
Add buttermilk and yeast; work together. Cover and refrigerate. Roll out as many as needed for each meal. Bake in ungreased pan at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: barbecue
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cook in pressure cooker for 1 hour.

title: fruit kabobs
directions: Cut fruit into chunks.
Put on skewers.
Dip in orange juice. Roll in coconut.
Eat and enjoy.

title: company strata(make today, bake tomorrow!)
directions: From 12 slices of white bread, cut 12 doughnuts and holes. Remove crusts.
Put scraps in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with cheese.
Cook and drain broccoli.
Layer broccoli and ham over cheese.
Arrange doughnuts and holes on top.
Combine eggs, milk, instant onion, salt and dry mustard; mix well.
Pour mixture over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 55 minutes or until bread is browned and eggs are set. Let stand for 10 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.
Freezes well!

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Combine Cool Whip and cake cubes
in large bowl, mixing well. Spread
in 9 x 13-inch
pan.
Top	with
pie
filling. Chill until serving time.
Yields 20 squares.

title: broiled chicken
directions: Cut up 5 onions into wedges and put in bottom of broiler pan. Put whole chicken on top of onions.
Cover chicken with 1 tablespoon margarine and season with garlic salt, pepper and paprika.
Cook under broiler, turning on all sides for 20 minutes. Then cover with foil and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: peach pie (1)
directions: Melt marshmallows and milk in double boiler.
Let cool. Prepare dream whip, add to above mixture, then add the peaches. Can be put in graham cracker crust or regular crust, baked.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in greased casserole.

title: baked beans and hamburger
directions: Heat beans while frying hamburger. Add onion soup mix. After this is well blended, add catsup, vinegar and mustard. A pinch of brown sugar may be added if desired. Mix all together and put in baking dish. Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 300°.

title: soda cracker pie
directions: Combine crackers, baking powder and walnuts and set aside. Gradually add sugar to beaten egg whites.
Add vanilla.
Fold egg mixture into cracker mixture.
Put in greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Top with whipped cream and refrigerate 24 hours.

title: harvest apple stuffing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat a large skillet with nonstick cooking spray.
Add apple juice, carrots, celery and onion; cook until tender.
Stir in nutmeg.
Lightly coat a 3 to 4-quart casserole dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Place cornbread cubes, apple, walnuts and wheat germ in casserole dish and toss lightly.
Add onion mixture.
Drizzle with enough broth to moisten and toss lightly again.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine salt, sausage, pork and rice; shape into 1-inch balls. Brown balls gradually in skillet.
Add 1 cup water; simmer for about 1 hour or until water has evaporated.
Remove balls from skillet; blend flour into pan drippings.
Stir in milk and spices gradually.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Return sausage balls to skillet; heat through.

title: mim's hot crabmeat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with Fritos.

title: quick broccoli and rice casserolewoodland park, colorado
directions: Follow directions and cook broccoli.
Combine with all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover with lid or vented plastic wrap and microwave on high for 6 minutes or until rice is tender, stirring once.
Serves 2.

title: fried cheese melt-a-ways
directions: Heat 2-inches of oil in deep fat fryer or saucepan to 375°. Beat 1 cup baking mix, the milk and egg with hand beater until smooth. Coat cheese cubes lightly with baking mix. Insert a wooden pick in each cheese cube. Dip into batter. Cover cheese completely. Fry several cubes at a time, turning carefully, until golden brown. Drain on paper towel.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well.
Serve with a variety of vegetables, raw.

title: calvin's pecan patties
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until soft ball forms when dropped in water. Cool and beat slowly. Drop on waxed paper by spoonfuls.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
In a greased 2-quart casserole, put half of the macaroni.
Cover with 1/2 can of cream of mushroom soup and 1/2 can (8 ounce size) of tomatoes.
Sprinkle with thyme and 1/2 can of tuna.
Repeat layer and sprinkle with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, covered, then 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Note: Ingredients are used according to number of servings needed.

title: high fiber bread
directions: Dissolve baking soda in molasses.
Add milk, flour, bran, wheat germ and raisins.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: bubbe sandy's potato pancakes
directions: Peel and grate potatoes and onion into a bowl.
Stir in eggs. Add salt, pepper and flour to thicken batter slightly.
Heat 4 tablespoons oil in a medium shallow skillet.
Drop mixture into heated oil by tablespoonfuls.
Fry until brown and crisp, turning once.
Add more oil as needed.
Remove pancakes from skillet; drain on paper towels.
Keep warm in a 200° oven on foil or foil lined baking pan.

title: orange whip
directions: Prepare jello according to directions on package using the drained orange juice.
When jello is set, whip jello and fold in Cool Whip, fold in oranges, pineapple and bananas.
Chill.

title: all vegetable spaghetti sauce
directions: Process (in food processor) onions and green peppers until very finely chopped or to your liking.
Heat in a large (like Dutch oven size) saucepan, stirring occasionally, on the stove over medium heat.
Wash and cut off ends of zucchini.
Cut and process until pureed.
Add to the cooking vegetables.
Mince the fresh mushrooms and add them to the vegetables.
Add garlic and cook until onions are translucent, 5 to 10 minutes.

title: coconut cream candy
directions: Melt butter and add all ingredients, except chocolate chips and paraffin wax.
Work in with your hands.
Roll into balls and put in refrigerator overnight.
Take 1 large bag chocolate chips and 1/2 bar of wax; melt in double boiler.
Place toothpick in the balls and dip in melted chocolate.
Place on wax paper.
Remove toothpick and dot with chocolate (with a spoon) where toothpick was.

title: microwave brownies
directions: In small bowl
at
medium speed on mixer, beat together eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla for about 1 minute, until light. Add melted
butter; continue beating until thoroughly blended. Mix in flour
and	cocoa
at low speed.
Stir in nuts.
Spread evenly in greased
8-inch square dish.
Microwave at High 5 to 7 minutes.

title: lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slightly grease 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cut up pineapple, oranges and grapes.
Add 1 cup sugar.
Let stand overnight.
Before ready to serve, drain and add apples, cherries (cut in 1/2) and bananas (cut in chunks).

title: cheese bread
directions: Slice bread nearly through.
Place in foil "boat" on cookie sheet.
Insert cheese between slices.
Melt butter.
Add onion. Pour over bread and cheese.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: tipsy dogs
directions: Combine sugar, bourbon and ketchup; bring to a boil.
Cut each hot dog into 6 pieces.
Add to sauce. Simmer uncovered for one hour.
Serve in a chafing dish.
Yield: 60 pieces.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken in 1 1/2 quarts of water until done.
Save 3/4 cup of broth.
Let chicken cool.
Remove skin from chicken, debone
and
cut up 2 cups of chicken.
Place chicken and broth in 2 quart casserole dish.
Add sour cream, soups, salt and pepper.
Stir well.
Crumble one package of Ritz crackers into mixture
and stir.
Place other crumbled package of Ritz crackers on
top
and bake in 300° oven for one hour or until brown.

title: speedy pan rolls
directions: Mix water, shortening, salt and sugar . Add 2 packages of yeast and mix.
Then add eggs and flour.
Mix and blend until dough is soft.
Pour in pan and spread out over bottom of pan. Dip knife in butter and cut into squares.
Melted butter may be spread over the top.
Put in warm place for 30 minutes, or until doubled in size.
Bake at 425°
for 20 minutes.
Makes 25 rolls.

title: mom's dinner rolls
directions: Heat scalded milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add beaten egg.
Then add egg-yeast mixture to heated milk mixture.
Add 2 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Add rest of flour.
Turn onto a floured board and knead until smooth and elastic.
Put in greased bowl.
Grease top.
Let rise in warm place (80° to 85°) for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Layer in shallow dish:
Refried beans, 2 mashed avocados (with lemon).
Mix 1 cup sour cream, 1/2 package Lawry's taco seasoning and 2 teaspoons mayonnaise.
Layer on top of mashed avocados. Next, add Cheddar cheese, Jack cheese, green onions, chopped olives and chopped tomatoes on top.

title: egyptian chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Squeeze juice of whole lemon over chicken.
Smash and squeeze tomato over chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in 350° oven until done.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Add eggs and beat on slow speed, then add last 3 ingredients and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until light brown, about 45 minutes.

title: scotchies
directions: Smash graham crackers until crumbly.
Add rest of the ingredients; mix well.
Put into a well-greased 11 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown on top, approximately 30 to 40 minutes.
Cut into squares and remove from pan while still warm.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cook until onion is clear.
Use on chicken, beef or ribs.

title: buck's chicken wings
directions: Mix until heated the margarine, hot sauce, dressing mix and tarragon.
Wash and pat dry the chicken wings.
Deep fry until golden brown (no salt needed).
Pour mixture of other ingredients over chicken while hot.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Place in 4 1/2 x 8-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Drain.

title: cheese mold
directions: Mix well and chill.
Spray a mold with nonstick spray.
Place chilled mixture in the mold. Will slide out when ready to use. Serve with strawberry preserves and Ritz crackers.

title: herb partridge's hot cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl in order listed.
Heat griddle and cook.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving liquid. Add cold water to this liquid to measure 1 cup.

Stir boiling water into jello in a large bowl, 2 minutes or until completely dissolved. Stir in measured liquid. Refrigerate 1 1/4 hours or until slightly thickened (consistency of unbeaten egg whites).
Stir in whipped topping with wire whisk until smooth.

Refrigerate 10 minutes until mixture will mound. Stir in oranges, pineapple, marshmallows and coconut. Spoon into mold. Refrigerate 4 hours until firm. Can be prepared with sugar-free jello and Cool Whip lite.

title: cheese ball 1
directions: Let the cheeses reach room temperature.
Mix together, adding the onion, Worcestershire sauce and 1/2 cup of the pecans.
After mixing well, place in the refrigerator until firm enough to handle, then form into a ball and roll in a mixture of the remaining 1/2 cup of pecans and parsley.
Let cheese ball reach room temperature before serving.
Makes 1 large ball or 2 small ones.

title: roman-style italian bread
directions: Sprinkle 1 package of active dry yeast in lukewarm water; stir.
After the yeast is dissolved, add 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1 1/4 cups warm (not hot) water.
Mix in about 5 cups flour and intermittently add a little water (up to a total of 1/4 cup) to make a soft, not sticky, dough.
Allow the dough to rise, covered, in a warm place for 10 minutes.
Then knead for another 10 minutes.
Place dough in a buttered, cloth covered bowl in a warm place and let it rise to double its size, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: holy smoke
directions: 1st Layer:
Combine pancake mix, butter and nuts; mix well. Press into an oblong dish.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: cranberry loaf
directions: Add 2 tablespoons oil to orange juice and boiling water; let stand.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Add egg; mix slightly.
Add liquid mixture; mix again.
Add nuts and cranberries; mix and pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chewy oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Mix sugar and egg, then mix in peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Mix well.
Drop in teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: snicker doodles
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix 1-1/2 c. sugar, margarine, shortening and eggs in large bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Shape dough by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Mix 3 TBSP sugar and the cinnamon; roll balls in mixture.
Place about 2 in. apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until set, 8-10 min.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix onion soup mix, rice, butter, hot water and mushrooms together in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place chicken pieces on top of mixture.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover and continue baking another 10 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in frying pan.
Add onion, salt, chili powder, paprika and tomato paste.
Cook macaroni.
In a casserole, layer macaroni and sauce until casserole is full.
Grate cheese on top. Cook in 350°
oven for 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin cheese cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Add slightly beaten eggs.
Add sweetened condensed milk.
Cut up cream cheese and add to batter.
Use electric beater until cheese blends in.
Add pumpkin and pumpkin spice; blend well.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in the melted butter, lemon peel and lemon juice.
In another bowl, beat egg yolks until well beaten.
Add milk to beaten yolks and stir together.
Pour yolk mixture into lemon mixture, mixing well. Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold whites into the lemon mixture.
Pour batter into an ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan on oven rack; place the batter-filled pan in the 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Carefully pour hot water into the larger pan to a depth of 1 inch.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Serve warm or chilled in dessert dishes.
Serves 9.

title: oatmeal peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon. Set aside. Combine butter, peanut butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla. Beat until light and fluffy. Gradually add flour mixture. Stir in oats and morsels.
Drop onto cookie sheets and bake 7 to 8 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen cookies or spread into a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan and bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: amaretto cheese ball
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, 1/2 cup chopped apricots, 1/2 cup nuts and Amaretto. Divide and roll into 2 balls. Mix remaining nuts and apricots in bowl. Roll each ball with nut-fruit mixture. Serve with apple slices and crackers.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Mix rhubarb, pineapple and sugar.
Let stand for 30 minutes. Bring slowly to boil and cook 30 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; add jello.
Stir until dissolved.

title: creamed corn casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Combine jello with boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Fold in strawberries with juice.
Add drained pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Turn half of mixture into dish; refrigerate until firm. Spread with sour cream or Dream Whip.
Spoon on the rest of the jello mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Place all ingredients in saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Turn down heat; simmer for about 15 minutes.

title: meatballs with mushroom sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Soften crumbs in milk.
Combine meat, crumbs, Worcestershire sauce, onion, egg, salt and pepper.
Mix well; make into balls.
Place in casserole dish.
Pour 2 cans mushroom soup over and bake 45 minutes or simmer in electric skillet until done.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix all together and put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 30-45 minutes at 350°.
Deep Dish pie crust works best.

title: oatmeal muffins(4 grams fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin tins with vegetable spray or use paper liners.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and oats.
In separate bowl, combine oil, egg whites and milk.
Pour over dry ingredients all at one time.
Stir until mixed.
Fold in raisins.
Do not overmix.
Spoon batter into muffin cups filling 2/3 full.
Bake 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 18 large muffins.

title: georgia ice cream
directions: In heavy pot, bring grits and 3 cups of milk to boil, stirring constantly.
Beat eggs and 3/4 cup milk.
Add this to grits and cook an additional 3 minutes.
Add cheese, salt and oleo.
Pour in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 45 minutes in 325° oven until browned and puffed.

title: deviled crab(my mother-in-law's recipe)
directions: Mix together egg, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper, Accent, mustard, sherry wine and bread crumbs.
Add mayonnaise to desired consistency.
Add crab meat; blend well.

title: easy apple pie
directions: Dice apples. Place in water. Sprinkle with salt. Let sit. Cut crust from bread. Cut up bread in long pieces about 1-inch wide. Drain apples and place in casserole dish. place bread strips on top of apples. Mix butter, sugar, flour and egg together and pour over bread and apples. Bake at 350° until brown, approximately 45 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together; sift.
Store in an airtight container until ready to be used.
Fill cups half full of mixture. Add boiling water.
Stir and enjoy.
Good with marshmallows.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix and pour into ice cream freezer.
May add 1/2-2/3 cup sugar.

title: mazetti
directions: Cook ground beef, peppers and onions.
Boil medium noodles. Mix soups.
Add chili powder into meat.
Pour in noodles.
Cover with Cheddar or shredded cheese.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes, covered with foil.

title: brownies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add other ingredients, mix well.
Bake at 350 25 - 30 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli and onion.
Shred cheese.
Fry bacon; drain and crumble.
Toss together gently.
Mix the last 4 ingredients; pour over broccoli.
Chill and serve.

title: vangie's coconut cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in coconut and nuts.

title: westville gingerbread
directions: Beat
the
eggs,
sugar and butter.
Add syrup and stir. Sift dry
ingredients together and add to the mixture.
Add the boiling water
last.
Bake
at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Test for doneness; it should spring back from your finger.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli in a small amount of boiling water until almost done; drain well.
Blend all other ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Fold in broccoli.
Spoon into buttered casserole dish and sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients together.
Sift the flour and add the rest of the dry ingredients.
Slowly mix the flour into the creamed mixture and stir until well blended.
Make balls the size of walnuts and roll each in granulated sugar.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.

title: cheese soup
directions: Chop vegetables as fine as you have patience for.
In a large pot, add water, bouillon and vegetables; bring to a boil, then simmer until vegetables are cooked. Add the canned milk and cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted. Add mixture of melted margarine and flour to thicken. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: baby food cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well. Pour into a bundt pan. Spray with Pam. Bake at 350° till a toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: corned beef and cabbage mold
directions: Take 1/2 cup hot water and gelatin and melt completely. Mix all other ingredients. Place in greased mold. Refrigerate overnight. (All vegetables are raw.)

title: harvest pumpkin bars
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add remaining and mix until smooth.
Pour into a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: pumpkin patch ice cream oreo
directions: Split 15 cookies, leaving filling on 1 side of each cookie. Finely crush plain split cookies and 5 whole cookies.
Mix crushed cookies, butter and sugar in small bowl.
Sprinkle on bottom of 9-inch spring form pan, pressing gently to form crust.
Stand remaining 15 split cookies on edge around side of pan.
Spread chocolate ice cream evenly on prepared crust.
Coarsely chop remaining 12 cookies; stir into vanilla ice cream and spread over chocolate layer.
Cover freeze 3 hours or until firm.
Remove side of pan.
Spread whipped topping on top of dessert.

Decorate with Halloween candies and colored sprinkles to form pumpkin patch. Using decorator gel, make pumpkin faces on the orange filling on split cookies around edge and, if desired, on additional split cookies.
Stand the additional cookies on edge on top of dessert. Serve immediately.
Prep time:
30 minutes.
Freeze time: 3 hours. Makes 15 servings.

title: polynesian beets
directions: Drain beets and pineapple, saving liquid.
Cook liquid over medium heat to boiling point.
Mix last 5 ingredients into a smooth paste.
Stir a small amount of hot juices into paste, then mix with the rest of the juices, stirring until thickened.
Add beets and pineapple, mixing well.
Add butter or margarine. Simmer 20 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: killer brownies
directions: Mix together in double boiler caramels and evaporated milk. Mix together oleo, condensed milk and cake mix.
Spread half of cake mixture in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Spread caramel mix over and then add chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop rest of cake mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix well.
Place mixture in a buttered casserole dish and cover with toasted bread crumbs; then drizzle with remaining butter.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately.
Beat egg whites and add last.
Bake in 4 tins, greased and floured, at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: miss bailey's special pasta dish
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions and drain.
Mix together spaghetti, rose beans, spaghetti, mushrooms and 1/2 can of onion rings.
Put in a microwavable dish.
Dot top with margarine.
Cover with plastic wrap and heat on High in microwave for 10 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with rest of onion rings and put back into microwave for 1 minute.

title: party mix
directions: Mix all together.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; beat until fluffy.
Beat in ice cream.
Pour into crust and freeze until firm.
Garnish with hot fudge and chopped peanuts, if desired.
Serve 8 to 10.

title: spinach madeline
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain well and reserve 1/2 cup liquid.
Melt butter in saucepan over low heat. Add flour, stirring until blended and smooth.
Add onion and cook until soft, but not brown.
Add liquid and stir constantly.
Cook until smooth.
Add seasoning and cheese.
Stir until melted.
Add spinach.
Can be served immediately or frozen or let flavors blend in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: roast beef
directions: Line pan with foil.
Put dry soup mix on top of roast, then brown sugar, ketchup and garlic powder.
Seal in foil and bake at 300°
for 3 hours, or until tender.

title: roasted red pepper soup
directions: Roast and peel peppers as follows:
Preheat oven to 500°.
Cut the peppers in half lengthwise and remove the stems, seeds and ribs.
Lay the peppers, cut side down, on a baking sheet.
Place under the broiler.
Broil or roast until the skins blister and blacken.
Remove from the oven and cover with aluminum foil.
Let steam until cool enough to handle, 10 to 15 minutes.
Then, using your fingers or a knife, peel off the skins.
Chop the peppers into medium pieces; set aside.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Start with 2 1/2 cups flour.
Add sugar, oil and beaten egg. Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add to flour mixture.
Add hot water; mix well.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour, a little at a time, to make a stiff dough.
Pour out onto a floured board for 15 minutes. Knead and put into greased bowl until it doubles.
Knead and roll out.
Cut and put on greased pan.
Let rise again.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: barbecue polish sausages
directions: Cut sausages in 1-inch pieces and place in crock-pot.
Add sugar and hot sauce; let simmer until tender.
You can also add a can of beer to the barbecue sauce, if desired.

title: california portuguese sweet bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Scald the milk and cool to lukewarm by cutting in margarine and shortening.
Beat the eggs well and add the sugar, salt and anise.
When milk is lukewarm, add it to egg mixture.
Stir in yeast.
Stir in flour and beat well after each addition.
Turn dough out on floured board and add more flour if necessary.
Knead dough about 10 minutes until elastic. Put dough into two greased bowls and turn dough to grease top.
Let rise in warm place until double in bulk, at least 4 hours.
Punch down and shape into rolls or loaves.
In greased pans, set dough to rise again, at least three hours.
Brush tops with butter or egg white for a glossy look.
Bake at 300° for about 40 to 45 minutes. Remove from pan immediately and cool on rack.
Wrap well to store.

title: sawdust salad
directions: This salad has 3 layers and should be made in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.

title: pepperoni cheese wheel
directions: Mix together cream cheese, Mozzarella cheese, pepperoni and milk.
Flatten, roll and pat into cheese wheel.
Mix paprika and cayenne pepper on a plate; roll cheese wheel until covered.
Chill until firm.
Serve in wedges on crackers.

title: peanut butter kiss cookie
directions: Mix shortening, peanut butter, sugar, brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla well. Add flour, soda and salt. Shape into balls and roll in sugar. Bake 8 minutes at 375°. Remove and place Kiss in each immediately.

title: yogurt praline candy
directions: Spray wax paper with Pam.
Combine sugars and yogurt.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Do not stir.
Boil 2 to 3 minutes to 232°.
Remove and stir in pecans and vanilla.
Spoon on wax paper.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Place warm water in bowl; add dry milk and mix well.
Add sugar, mix until smooth.
May set bowl of mix in pan of hot water to dissolve sugar.
Use in recipes calling for sweetened condensed milk.

title: sandies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add water and vanilla.
Blend in flour and nuts.
Chill, then shape in balls.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Remove from pan and roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: easy lemon yogurt pie
directions: Mix yogurt, Cool Whip and lemon rind.
Pour into pie crust. Refrigerate overnight.
Garnish with kiwi slices before serving.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash about 15 minutes or until tender; drain.
Saute carrots and onion in butter until tender.
Add soup, sour cream and 1/2 cup croutons.
Combine with squash.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup croutons on top and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: lady baltimore cake
directions: Sift flour once.
Measure;
add baking powder and salt. Sift again
together.
Cream
butter
thoroughly;
add
sugar gradually until
light and fluffy.
Add flour alternately with liquid, a small
amount
at a time.
Beat after each addition until smooth. Add
flavoring.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in 2 greased 9-inch layer pans in a 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Cool and frost.	Double recipe for 3 (10-inch) layers.

title: cranberry mold vigil
directions: Drain pineapple and add water to juice to make 2 cups.
Add gelatin to juice and cook to dissolve.
Add cranberry sauce and pineapple. Allow cranberry to dissolve.
Put in lightly greased ring mold and chill.
Serves 8.

title: vinegar and egg pie crust
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
In separate bowl, beat remaining ingredients and combine with flour using fork until all is moist. Chill 15 minutes before rolling.
Makes 2 double crust pies and 1 pie shell.
Freezes well.

title: easy pumpkin bars
directions: Mix flour, butter and brown sugar until crumbly and spread onto cookie sheet.
Do not pat down.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix pumpkin, evaporated milk, eggs, sugar, salt, cinnamon, ginger and cloves together and pour over warm crust. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares and top with Cool Whip or whipping cream.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place green beans in 2-quart casserole dish.
Melt cheese with 1/4 cup milk, pour over beans.
Stir in French fried onions. Cover with crushed crackers.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: mrs. baur's impossible pie
directions: Place all ingredients into blender for 30 seconds.
Pour into slightly greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake for 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: lorraine's quick punch
directions: Place all ingredients into large punch bowl with ice cubes or an ice ring.
Stir.
Serves about 30 (6 ounce) cups.
Favorite liqueur may be added.

title: vegetable stir-fry with beef or chicken
directions: In a medium skillet or wok heat 3 tablespoons oil over medium-high heat.
Add broccoli and mushrooms; stir-fry 1 minute or until crisp-tender.
Remove from skillet.
Add remaining 3 tablespoons oil to skillet and heat.
Add beef or chicken; stir-fry 1 to 3 minutes.
Return vegetables to skillet.
Add Oriental Sauce Mix.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute or until beef/chicken is cooked through.
Stir in tomatoes and heat through. Serve over rice, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Prepare frozen noodles as per package directions. Cut meat into thin slices and dredge in flour.
Brown quickly in skillet with 2 tablespoons margarine.
Remove meat, add remaining margarine and saute the onions.
Add meat, sprinkle all with salt and pepper.
Add enough water to barely cover; simmer until tender.
Add mushroom soup, sour cream and sherry.
Heat thoroughly; add cooked, drained noodles; stir.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken dish in wine
directions: Place chicken pieces in flat baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt. Combine flour with 1/4 cup sour cream, stirring until smooth. Add remaining sour cream, soup and sherry.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with almonds and pimento over top.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken divine
directions: Cook chicken and remove bones.
Cut chicken into long thin pieces.
Blend flour and butter in small saucepan.
Stir in broth. Cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Blend in salt, pepper and 1/4 cup of Parmesan cheese.
Cook broccoli per directions.
Arrange broccoli in shallow casserole dish.
Cover with chicken slices and sauce.
Top with remaining 1/4 cup cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: mongolian beef
directions: Trim fat from beef steak.
Cut strips into 1/8-inch slices. Toss beef, the cornstarch, 1 tablespoon vegetable oil, salt, sugar, 1 teaspoon soy sauce and white pepper in medium glass or plastic bowl.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Cut green onion into 2-inch pieces.

title: russian fluff
directions: Cut up bacon and fry.
Chop onion and add to bacon.
Add celery and green pepper; cook to brown bacon and cook celery. Brown hamburger.
Cook rice.
Place all ingredients in a casserole dish with the undiluted tomato soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Cook fruit without sugar 3 minutes; add 3 cups sugar and cook 3 minutes.
Then add 2 cups sugar and cook 3 minutes or a little longer.
Pour into an earthen crock and stir occasionally.
In 3 days, put in jars and seal with wax.

title: mother's day(any flavor)
directions: Blend well the first 3 ingredients, then pour slowly into the willing heart, stirring constantly.
Now add alternately the next six ingredients.
When all of these have been thoroughly blended, add the caring spirit.
Just before serving, garnish with faith.

title: lemon whippersnaps
directions: Combine cake mix, Cool Whip (thawed) and egg.
Stir until mixed.
Drop by teaspoon into powdered sugar.
Roll to coat well. Place 1 1/2-inches apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove to cooling rack.
(Cookie dough will be soft and sticky.)

title: breakfast burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into 2-inch patties.
Cook in skillet over medium heat, about 2 to 3 minutes on each side. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: bit-o-honey candy
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cream and vanilla, in saucepan over medium heat and bring to a boil.
Let boil 10 minutes at a rolling boil, stirring occasionally.
Add cream and mix.
Add vanilla and mix.
Pour hot into buttered pie plate.
Chill until set.

title: red cabbage
directions: In a 6-quart kettle or Dutch oven, melt the butter over low heat and to it add the sugar, salt, vinegar and water.
Add the cabbage to the kettle. Cover and simmer over low heat for 1 hour or more.
Just before serving, add the currant jelly and the cloves, if desired.
Serve piping hot as an accompaniment to a pork roast or pork chops.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients; spread on tortillas.
Roll up and chill for a few minutes.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Dip in picante sauce.

title: broccoli raisin salad
directions: Cover raisins with hot tap water and soak until plump; drain. In large bowl, combine broccoli, onion, bacon, sunflower seeds and raisins. Set aside.

title: chocolate mess
directions: Mix a devil's food cake mix according to directions on package.
Bake in 2 round cake pans; cool.
Place 1 layer in a large, glass bowl.
Looks best in glass stem dish.
Mix chocolate pudding, using only 3 cups of milk.
When firm, put half of pudding mixture over the layer of cake in the bowl.
Next, place another layer of cake on top of the pudding.
Put rest of pudding over the cake.
Sprinkle broken up pieces of Heath bar or Symphony chocolate bar on top of the pudding.
Top with lots of Cool Whip. Decorate with chocolate sprinkles and maraschino cherries. Chopped nuts can also be used on top, if desired.

title: cinnamon bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add yolk.
Add flour, sifted with cinnamon.
Mix well.
Put in jelly roll pan, 10 x 15-inch.
Pour unbeaten egg white over surface and spread with hand.
This gives shiny look.
Drain excess.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Press into dough.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into bars while hot, 2 1/2 x 3/4-inch.
These freeze well.

title: custard bread pudding
directions: Grease a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Put bread cubes in dish. Beat eggs; add sugar, salt, vanilla, nutmeg and butter.
Add milk and blend.
Pour over bread cubes.
Set baking dish in pan of warm water.
Bake at 350° for 75 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serves 6 to 8.
Serve warm or cold.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and peel.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add to cream mixture alternately with milk.
(Fold in nuts.)
Pour into greased floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until pick comes out clean.
Remove from oven; cool for 15 minutes.
Dissolve 1/3 cup sugar in lemon juice.
Pour over bread while still warm in pan.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: carrot drop cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients at once.
Drop by teaspoon onto an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Frost with Orange Icing:

title: "verne's" bread pudding
directions: Whip together the eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla with a whisk. Mix the scalded milk with the sugar and egg mixture and pour over buttered bread in baking dish. Sprinkle cinnamon and nutmeg on top. Bake in pan of water 35 to 45 minutes at 350° or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: baked ziti delmonico
directions: Grease baking dish with butter.
Boil water for ziti.
Brown ground beef.
Simmer onion.
Add spaghetti sauce to drained ground beef.
Let simmer 10 minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Pour rest of batter in pan.
Sprinkle remaining mixture over dough.
May add nuts.
Swirl knife through batter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: seafood dip
directions: Mix all together and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: cream of mushroom soup(low fat and low sodium)
directions: Combine mushrooms, onion, water, bouillon, garlic powder, onion powder and pepper.
Cook over medium heat until mushrooms and onion are tender.
Add 1/2 can of milk.
Mix remaining milk with enough flour to thicken soup.
Add butter sprinkles and milk and flour mixture to soup.
Stir until thickened.

title: stuffed potatoes with shrimp
directions: Bake potatoes at 375° until tender.

In saucepan, combine shallots, onions, bell pepper and butter; saute until tender. Add shrimp and 1/2 pound cheese; let cook until cheese is melted, then add 1/2 cup milk. When potatoes are done, cut in half and core out, being careful not to break up skins.
Put potatoes in large bowl and mix with mixture until blended together.
Stuff into potato skins.
Top with rest of cheese and bake in oven until cheese is melted at 325°.
Sour cream may be added, if you wish.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Brown ground beef, onion and peppers. Drain.
Add sauces and mushrooms to meat and simmer.
Layer twice, noodles, meat, sauce, cheese and pepperoni, in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: robin's fantasy pie
directions: Bake the brownie mix in a round cake pan.
Sprinkle on 1/2 cup chocolate chips before baking; let cool.
Spread on chocolate fudge pudding (4 containers equals 1 whole package).
Spread on chocolate Cool Whip.
Serve.

title: dip for apple slices
directions: Mix this together and serve with apple slices.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Refrigerate at least overnight.
Gets better as it sits.
Can also be frozen.

title: mango breakfast bread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar. Add eggs. Stir in dry ingredients, mangos and lemon juice. Pour into two 8-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until loaf tests done. Cool in pans 10 minutes. Remove from pans and cool thoroughly.
For best results, wrap in foil and serve the following day.

title: butterscotch pecan pound cake
directions: Cream
margarine,
Crisco, cream cheese and sugar well; add eggs alternately with flour-baking powder mixture, reserving about 1/4 cup flour mixture for mixing butterscotch chips and nuts.
Add
morsels
and
nuts;
bake in well-greased and floured pan at 325° for one hour and fifteen minutes.

title: texas cole slaw
directions: Chop or shred cabbage and place it in a bowl with one finely chopped onion and green pepper.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar and toss lightly to blend.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well with mixer and put into casserole dish.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour over melted butter.
Pour 1 quart fruit over this mixture; bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until browned.
Do not mix or stir after all mixtures are in baking dish.
Dough will rise to top and make a flaky top.

title: eggs florentine
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Thaw spinach and drain well.
Blend spinach, cream cheese, salt and pepper; press into bottom of 2 small casserole dishes.
Crack 1 egg on top of each spinach bed. Top each dish with 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese and bake on rack above center of the oven for 10 minutes.
Garnish lightly with cayenne pepper, if desired.
Serves 2 people.

title: italian rice
directions: Put oil or margarine in skillet or kettle and heat.
Add onions (chopped up fine) and pepper.
Brown until light golden brown.
Add rice; keep stirring so rice will not burn (low heat). Cook for 2 minutes until heated through, then add liquid, about 1 cup at a time.
As rice absorbs liquid, add more and keep stirring.
When rice is done and liquid absorbed by rice, season with salt, pepper and paprika.
If you desire to use tomato juice and saffron, cook it until it is absorbed.

title: grandma's slow-cook veggie chili
directions: Place all ingredients in a slow cooker on high at least 2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese, eggs and 1 1/2 cups sugar until smooth. Pour mixture into greased spring-form pan; bake at 325° to 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake springs back.
Mix together sour cream, 3 tablespoons sugar and vanilla; pour over cool cake and bake for 10 minutes at 325°.
Let cool.
Combine strawberries and Jell-O with hot water; pour over top of cake and refrigerate until set.

title: lucille's crab stew(serves 12)
directions: First, make a roux with 1 heaping cooking spoon of flour and 1 spoon of oil (per dozen crabs).
Have chopped and ready to add to the roux:

onion, celery, green onions, bell pepper and parsley. Cook the roux mixture slowly while you clean the scalded crabs. Remove the debris and legs; then add the claws, fat and the crab bodies, cut in half, but with the crabmeat left in the shell. Season the stew with salt, red and black peppers and Creole seasoning.
Cook down until it thickens and serve over rice.

title: corn casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to instructions on package.
Add margarine; stir until melted.
Add corn and soup.
Grated 1 cup or more cheese.
Combine with mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle some cheese on top; sprinkle paprika for color.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix
cornmeal,	flour,	baking	powder, sugar, salt and black pepper.
Add
eggs, milk, red onions, and green peppers. Use beer to	thin
the mixture.
Consistency should be thick. Heat deep fryer.
Drop
batter
by the spoonful into hot oil. They should drop
to the bottom of pan then float to the top. For a
little added
taste,
you	can add 3 cans of bite size (tiny) shrimp. Brown to taste.

title: edith's pot roast
directions: Put roast and veggies in large pot.
Tenderize meat.
Mix 1 cup of water with soup mix.
Pour over meat and veggies.
Shake Nature's Seasons over everything.
Cover tightly with foil.
Cook in oven at 300° for 3 hours.
Baste occasionally.

title: nane shirini(persian cookies)
directions: Sift together flour and baking powder.
Cream together shortening and sugar.
Blend in egg yolks, vanilla, almond and lemon extract.
Mix well.
Add gradually the dry ingredients, mix until well blended.
Roll dough into round balls using about 1 teaspoon for each.
Place on ungreased baking sheet, flatten slightly.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: barbecue hamburgers
directions: Mix
ground beef, onion, salt and pepper and shape into patties.
Add
fat	to
skillet
and fry patties brown on both sides.
Combine
catsup, onion, vinegar, sugar and mustard and pour over hamburgers.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: chicken elegante
directions: In a baking dish, make 8 mounds of dried beef, 2 pieces per mound.
Form chicken breasts into round patties.
Put chicken over or around dried beef.
Put 1/2 strip bacon over each breast. Blend sauce and pour over chicken.
Cook uncovered for 3 hours at 300°.
Makes 8 servings.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Combine buttermilk and soda.
Cream margarine, shortening and 1 3/4 cups sugar.
Beat egg whites and 1/4 cup sugar until stiff. Add egg yolks, one at a time, to the shortening and sugar mixture, alternately with sifted flour.
Stir in vanilla.
Fold in egg whites.
Gently stir in chopped pecans and coconut.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) greased and floured pans at 325° for 25 minutes or until cake tests done with toothpick.

title: spicy mixed nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spray cookwell with cooking oil.
Add peanut oil and heat for 5 minutes.
In a large mixing bowl, combine nuts. Set aside.
Stir light corn syrup, sugar, teriyaki sauce, Worcestershire sauce and mustard until smooth. Add hot pepper sauce, if desired.
Pour mixture over nuts. Coat well. Spoon into hot oil.
Cook 15 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes. Spoon nuts onto cookie sheet to cool, stirring occasionally to keep from sticking.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: banana cream cake
directions: Follow directions on box for baking cake.
Combine and heat orange juice and honey.
Use toothpicks to poke holes on top of cake.
Pour hot orange juice and honey over holes slowly.
Spread pudding on top of cake.
Lay slices of bananas over pudding, and spread Cool Whip over bananas as frosting for cake.

title: herb potatoes
directions: Slice onions thinly; cut into halves crosswise.
Cut potatoes into 1/2-inch slices, cutting to but not through bottom.
Place on pieces of foil.
Saute celery in margarine in skillet until tender.
Stir in oregano, salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Drizzle half the mixture into slices in potatoes.
Insert onion slices. Drizzle remaining celery mixture.
Wrap potatoes in foil; seal securely with double fold.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes, or until tender.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Mix eggs and milk together.
Thaw spinach souffle.
Add to egg and milk mixture.
Stir in onion and mushrooms.
Cook sausage, drain.
Add to egg mixture.
Mix all.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients and pour in 9 x 13 greased pan.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute in
shortening,
bell
pepper,
onion and celery. Add tomato
sauce,
water,
chili powder, bay leaves, vinegar, salt and pepper.

Let this mixture cook slowly while you brown about 1 cup of flour in shortening real dark (almost burn it). Add to other mixture stirring constantly.	Add shrimp and cook 20 minutes after this	has come to a boil.
Stir occasionally. Serve over cooked rice.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Beat at low speed. Mix dry ingredients together and add gradually.
Fold in apples and pecans.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: russian rocks
directions: Cream the sugar and butter together.

Add beaten egg yolks. Mix soda with warm water and add to creamed mixture. Sift flour and spices together and beat into butter-egg mixture. Add pecans, chopped dates and chopped candied fruits. Fold in beaten egg whites. Drop onto baking sheets. Bake in preheated 300° oven for 20 minutes.

title: chicken almond casserole
directions: Combine first 11 ingredients.
Spoon into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch lightly greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: pizza flavor casserole
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 30 minutes.

title: velveeta vegetable bake
directions: Cook and drain your vegetables.
Mix cubed Velveeta cheese all through vegetables.
After you have mixed your cheese through the vegetables, sprinkle your Ritz crackers on top.
Dot the top with butter.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in a crock-pot or simmer several hours. (May add 1 can of water.)

title: old fashioned chocolate cookies
directions: Combine.
Drop on sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: corn dogs
directions: Combine pancake mix with next 4 ingredients.
Add water and beat well.
Dip wieners into batter and drain off excess.
Fry in deep hot fat at 375° for 1 to 2 minutes.
Drain and serve with mustard.

title: peanut butter cookies 1(no bake)
directions: Melt sugar and corn syrup.
Add peanut butter and cereal; mix. Form into 1-inch balls.
Place on wax paper.
Cool.

title: million dollar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars; add egg and vanilla.
Sift and add dry ingredients.
Then add nuts, finely chopped.
Form into balls and roll in sugar.
Press flat with bottom of a glass.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: shrimp fra diavolo
directions: Simmer all ingredients for 15 minutes.
Serve over hot pasta.

title: frozen peanutty banana
directions: Insert popsicle stick lengthwise into banana.
Spread peanut butter on banana and roll it in granola.
Freeze bananas until ready to eat.

title: cinnamon candy salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add red hots in 1/2 cup boiling water to dissolve.
Add enough water to make 1 cup.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: spuds ala kyle
directions: Slice the baked potatoes lengthwise and lay on bottom of baking pan.
Baste with melted butter.
Bake at 350° until crisp and golden.
Cover with shredded cheese and top with bacon bits or chives.
Bake just until the cheese bubbles.
Serve.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars and oils; add eggs and vanilla.
Add soda and cream of tartar to 1 cup flour.
Put with rest of flour and stir into creamed mixture.
Chill.
Make into balls; roll into sugar and flatten.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Watch carefully and do not overbake.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together and keep refrigerated.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Spray bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans over bottom.
Mix cake mix by box directions. Pour over coconut and pecans.
In another bowl, mix cream cheese and oleo.
Add powdered sugar and cream together.
Drop by spoonful into cake mix randomly.
Bake 45 minutes.
It will run over.
Put pan of water below cake before baking to prevent coconut from burning.
This will also catch overspill.

title: "haystacks"
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels over low heat.
When completely melted, stir in nuts and Chinese noodles.
Drop by spoonful onto waxed paper.
Place in refrigerator for about 10 minutes.
Makes a quick and easy dessert or candy.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Cook and drain hamburger.
Mix in tomato sauce, taco mix and green chilies.
Add Tabasco to season as desired.
Press biscuits in greased pie pan to form shell.
Fill shell with can of refried beans.
Allow hamburger mix to thicken over low heat.
Add any further spices and chili powder during simmering.
Pour and press hamburger mix over beans.
Either sprinkle cheese before or after baking at 375° for 18 to 22 minutes.
Serve with lettuce or tomato.
Makes 5 servings.

title: easy meal casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in refrigerator overnight.
Take out of refrigerator 1 hour before baking.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in greased pan.

title: gourmet pork chops
directions: In skillet, melt fat.
Coat chops with 2 tablespoons flour and salt and pepper.
Brown chops, then place in a cooking dish. Combine mushroom soup, water, ginger and rosemary.
Pour over chops and sprinkle 1/2 can of fried onions on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle rest of onions on top and bake 10 more minutes without cover.
Add 1/2 cup sour cream, if desired.

title: grandma's boiled cake
directions: In a large pot, boil 4 minutes all ingredients except nuts and flour.
Cool mixture.
Add flour and 2 teaspoons baking soda. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: sesame cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in extract.
Add flour and salt; mix well.
Shape rounded tablespoonfuls of dough into balls; roll in sesame seed.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Indent centers; fill with preserves. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes approximately 3 dozen.

title: sloppy chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Beat eggs with fork until frothy.
Pour into cake pan with all wet ingredients. Mix with large spoon until thoroughly combined.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all five ingredients in large bowl and chill before serving.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: teriyaki marinating sauce(for any meat or fish)
directions: Mix all together.
Marinate beef, pork or chicken cubes for at least 4 hours (overnight is best).
Skewer meat with your choice of vegetables and bake or barbecue to pretested doneness.

title: big pan of chili
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and celery.
Add rest of ingredients. Simmer for 1 hour, then add beans at the last minute.

title: peach congealed salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, crushed pineapple and peach pie filling.
Add 1 cup of boiling water and 1 cup of cold water (use pineapple juice drained from crushed pineapple for cold water).
Let gel. Mix sour cream, cream cheese and sugar.
Spread on top of gelled mixture. Top this with nuts.

title: barbecue time baked beans
directions: Place the beans in a bowl.
Cover with cold water and soak overnight. Drain and rinse beans very well under cold water. Place the beans in a large, heavy pot.

Add enough water to cover the beans by 2-inches. Bring water to a boil, reduce heat to a simmer and cook for 45 minutes or until beans are tender but not mushy. Skim off any foam that rises to the surface. Drain the beans.
Place the oil in a large, heavy ovenproof casserole. Add the onions and wilt over medium-low heat until translucent. Remove from heat and stir in the beans.
Stir in the tomatoes and reserved juices along with all remaining ingredients except the salt and pepper.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 30 minutes more.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: potato soup
directions: Brown bacon until crisp.
Drain.
Save bacon grease.
Cook potatoes, onion and bacon grease in the boiling water until potatoes are tender.
Add milk, salt, pepper and crumbled bacon. Heat until almost boiling.
Mix cornstarch with just enough cold water to smooth.
Add to hot mixture, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Serves 8.

title: e z veggie bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook vegetables according to package directions.
Let cool after cooking.
In a large bowl, mix cheese, egg whites, onions, mushroom soup, mayonnaise and vegetables. Grease baking dish with Pam.
Spread mixture into greased baking dish evenly.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let cool for about 5 minutes and serve.
Serves 4 to 6 as side dish or add browned pieces of chicken for a main dish.
This is a low calorie/low-fat meal that tastes great with a preparation time of less than 15 minutes.

title: sherried fruit
directions: Drain fruit well.
Arrange in layers in a buttered casserole. In double boiler mix brown sugar, flour, butter and sherry.
Cook until smooth and thick. Pour over fruit.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.
Prior to serving, bake uncovered at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: chicken-ghetti
directions: Mix chicken broth, cream of mushroom soup, bell peppers, onions, mushrooms and olives.
Layer chicken, spaghetti noodles and soup mixture.
Top with cheese.
Cover and cook 1 hour at 350°.
This can be prepared ahead and frozen before cooking.

title: raisin-apple sticky buns(dietetic)
directions: Remove dough from plastic package.
Let dough defrost until soft, pliable and starting to rise.
Divide into halves.

Flatten one half into rectangle about 1/3-inch thick. Spread with half of margarine (save some to lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish). Mix apples, cinnamon, 2 tablespoons nuts, raisins and 2 tablespoons apple juice concentrate.
Pour remaining concentrate into lightly greased baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining nuts over apple juice in dish.

title: german pecan brittles
directions: Cream
shortening
in a large mixing bowl; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each
addition.
Sift
together
flour, baking powder, soda and salt in
a
medium mixing bowl; add cereal and pecans, stirring to coat
well.
Stir
flour
mixture
and
vanilla into creamed mixture,
mixing
well.
Drop
dough
by
teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto greased and floured cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes and cool on wire racks.
Yields 11 dozen.

title: pan roasted garlic potatoes
directions: If desired peel potatoes.
Cut into 1-inch cubes and set aside in bowl with water to cover until ready to cook.
When ready, drain potato cubes and pat dry with paper towels.
In large skillet over high heat, heat olive oil with butter until very hot. Add garlic cloves and potato cubes and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cover; reduce heat to low and cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove cover; raise heat to high and cook, stirring occasionally until potatoes are golden and crisp, about 5 minutes longer.
Discard garlic, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Mix mushroom soup and milk in large casserole dish.
Cook and drain noodles until tender; add to dish and stir.
Add rest of ingredients and stir to blend.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: copper carrot pennies
directions: Cook carrots in salt water until tender, cool.
Alternate carrots, green pepper and onion in a dish.
Combine remaining ingredients with salt and pepper to taste, and blend well in a blender.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate overnight.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: cherry crumb cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour; sift with baking powder and salt.
Cut in the butter; add egg and mix to make crumbs.
Place 1/2 of the crumb mixture in the bottom of a greased 9x13 pan.
Pour cherries over the crumbs in the pan.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake in a moderate oven 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream, ice cream or plain.

title: pineapple sauce cake
directions: Beat butter until creamy.
Add sugar gradually, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg; beat well.
Add nuts and fruit.
Add remaining ingredients to flour.
Add flour mixture alternately with pineapple sauce, beating after each addition.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans (8 x 4 x 3-inch).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: plain butter cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Blend thoroughly. Beat eggs and add to mixture. Add sifted flour, salt and baking powder. Combine with milk. Add vanilla. Bake in buttered tins 25 minutes at 375°.

title: golden wassail
directions: Place juice in percolator.
Place spices and brown sugar in basket.
Allow to go through perk cycle or put apple cider, brown sugar and spices in saucepan.
Bring to boil; simmer 10 minutes. Add juices and heat.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients together.
Fold in the Cool Whip. Pour into a graham cracker or chocolate crust.
Freeze before cutting.
Drizzle chocolate syrup on top.
(Hold knife under hot water to cut pie.)
Makes 3 pies.

title: hungry boy's casserole
directions: Sprinkle celery, onions and green pepper in bottom of 8-inch baking dish.
Crumble ground beef on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 420° for 20 minutes; remove from oven.
Stir in baked beans, catsup, water, salt and garlic salt until well blended.
Reserve 1/2 cup of bean mixture.
Return casserole to oven for 10 minutes while preparing biscuits (see biscuit recipe).

title: linguine and shrimp
directions: Prepare linguine as package directs.
Drain.
In medium skillet, heat Italian dressing.
Add shrimp, vegetables that have been julienned, garlic, parsley, lemon peel, salt and cayenne pepper.
Cook and stir 8 to 10 minutes.
Add linguine; toss and garnish.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: johnny marzetti
directions: Melt oleo in skillet; stir in onion and celery.
Saute.
Add ground beef and ground pork; brown.
Season with salt and pepper. Add tomatoes, tomato soup and sugar.
Cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Cook noodles in salted water.
Drain and rinse with hot water.
Combine noodles and tomato sauce.
Grease casserole; alternate noodles and sauce and add cheese between and on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bread dressing(stuffing)
directions: Toast bread and break into small pieces.
Place in a large pan and add all remaining ingredients.
Place in a greased roaster. Bake at 350° until done, approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
This makes a large amount.
Ideal for a large get together, otherwise you may 1/2 the recipe.
Makes more than one roaster.

title: dynamites
directions: Chop celery, peppers and onion.
Cover with water.
Cook until tender.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, browned hamburger and tomato paste.
Add 2 or 3 shakes of crushed red pepper seed.
The more shakes, the hotter the taste!

title: shortribs in beer
directions: Brown shortribs in cooking oil on stove.
Place shortribs in 13 x 9-inch cake pan, 2 to 2 1/2-inches deep.
Place sliced onion over ribs.
Pour soup mix over ribs.
Pour beer over top of ribs. Cover with aluminum foil and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Uncover for the last 1/2 hour.
Serve with plain rice, using the juice of ribs to pour over rice.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream together the first 4 ingredients.
Mix in flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Add vanilla.
Stir in oatmeal. Add chocolate chips, coarsely chopped candy bar and nuts. Roll into golf ball size balls. Bake at 400° for 6 to 10 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: In skillet in oil, cook beef strips until brown, stirring often; set aside.
Cook onion and green pepper with garlic powder until tender, stirring often.
Stir in gravy and Worcestershire sauce; heat to boiling.
Return beef to skillet.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: cheesy pork chops and potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt Cheez Whiz in microwave and pour into 8 x 12-inch baking dish.* In large skillet, brown pork chops in oil; drain.
Sprinkle pork chops with seasoned salt; set aside. Using fork, stir milk into melted cheese until well blended.
Stir in potatoes and 1/2 can onions into cheese mixture.
Arrange pork chops over potatoes.
Bake, covered, for 35 to 40 minutes.
Top pork chops with remaining onions and bake, uncovered, 5 minutes.

title: herb butter
directions: Put butter in blender container, add remaining ingredients, cover and blend using spatula to guide ingredients to center.

title: hot dogs rolled in biscuits
directions: Roll the biscuits.
Cut hot dogs in half.
Halve slices of cheese.
Roll 1/2 hot dog and 1/2 slice of cheese in a biscuit and bake.
Great little snacks.

title: quick tomato sauce
directions: Saute onion, garlic and celery slowly in butter about 5 minutes.
Add tomato paste and water and mix well.
Add all other ingredients and simmer gently approximately 30 minutes.

title: gingerbread dough
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Stir molasses into sugar mixture.
Sift flour, baking soda, salt and ginger together.
Gradually add flour mixture to sugar mixture until blended.
Heat oven to 350°.
On lightly floured surface, roll 1/4 of dough to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut dough into desired shapes.
Place 1/2-inch apart on cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 minutes or until crisp and light brown.
Cool slightly and remove from rack.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Crush and mix together the chocolate wafers and margarine. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat the milk into the pudding. Spoon in softened ice cream.
Pour into pan.
Cover with whipped topping and chocolate chips.

title: corn fritters
directions: Put dry ingredients together.
Blend milk and egg.
Add gradually to dry ingredients.
Stir in corn.
Drop by tablespoons (or like pancakes from cup) into hot fat.
Fry 2 to 5 minutes until brown. Drain on paper.

title: okra gumbo
directions: In a wide, deep skillet, heat oil.
Spread okra out in skillet and brown on both sides.
(Turn carefully.
Do not stir okra.) Add onion and bell pepper and simmer until onion is no longer crisp.
Add shrimp, corn and tomatoes and continue to cook on low heat until shrimp is tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine kraut, sprouts, celery, green pepper and onion.
In a small pan, heat sugar, oil and vinegar.
Pour on salad and refrigerate overnight.
Toss and serve.

title: low-fat baked fish
directions: Spray pan with cooking spray.
Mix 1/4 cup of corn meal with 1 teaspoon dressing mix.
Spray both sides of filet and coat with the corn meal mix on both sides.
Heat oven to 350° and bake for 35 minutes or until done.
If fish isn't frozen, bake for 15 minutes.

title: pizza soup
directions: Saute mushroom and onion in oil for 2-3 minutes, until tender.
Add in water, pizza sauce, pepperoni, tomatoes, sausage, and italian seasoning.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Just before serving, stir in parmesan cheese and top with the shredded mozzarella cheese.

title: pork 'n bean sandwich
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in saucepan and mix well.
Heat until well mixed and hot.
Spread butter on both sides of bread and heat in oven until slightly toasted.
Makes a delicious sandwich.

title: straw ba nut ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar; beat well and add Eagle Brand condensed milk and vanilla.
Combine strawberries, nuts and bananas.
Fold in whipped topping.
Mix gently and pour in ice cream freezer.
Add milk; freeze and let stand 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole ii
directions: Boil chicken and cut up in small pieces.
In a casserole dish, add chicken pieces, mayonnaise, pimentos, onion, cream of mushroom soup, mushroom slices and crushed potato chips.
Mix all together. Smooth over top and sprinkle additional crushed potato chips on top.
Place in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Yummy and quick!

title: world's best cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.

Cream together butter and sugars until light and fluffy. Add egg, mixing well, then salad oil, mixing well. Add oats, cornflakes, coconut and nuts, stirring well. Then add flour, soda and salt. Mix well and form into balls the size of small walnuts. Place on an ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with
fork dipped in water. Bake for 12 minutes. Allow to cool on cookie sheets for a few minutes before removing. Yield: 8 dozen.

title: frozen banana milkshake
directions: Peel banana and slice into large chunks.
When frozen, combine in blender with skim milk, sweetener and nutmeg.
Blend just until mixture is thick and frothy.
Serve immediately.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Add the garlic and salad oil just before using.

title: tangy fruit salsa topping
directions: Stir together ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate topping about 1 hour or until chilled.
Stir topping before serving.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Wash and cut tips of zucchini; cut lengthwise and scoop out inside.
Leave 1/4-inch shell (save.).
Cut squash very fine. Saute garlic in oil until golden brown; add squash and cook approximately 2 minutes.
Remove from pan and mix squash with bread crumbs and grated cheese.
Oil outside of zucchini shell and put in baking dish.
Put mixture inside of shell and bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.

title: golden punch
directions: Dissolve sugar and water, add juices and then add the cold Ginger Ale.

title: joanne's cream cheese pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese with a little bit of the milk until smooth.
Add pudding and the rest of the milk.
Mix until well blended and begins to thicken.
Pour in the cooled baked graham cracker crust.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
In a
large bowl, toss the rest of the ingredients.
Pour dressing over and toss until thoroughly covered.
Chill.

title: brownies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix white and brown sugar, butter, salt and milk together. Bring to a boil and cook until it forms a soft ball in cold water. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and marshmallow cream and beat until it starts to thicken.
Pour into a well-buttered pan and cool.

title: summer salad
directions: Chop both kinds of lettuce into bite-size pieces.
Layer the carrots, mushrooms, cucumber, tomatoes and oranges.
Put sliced, cooked chicken on top or serve on the side.
Top with almonds. Serve with salad dressing.

title: prune muffins
directions: Mix and pour in greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Makes 12.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: tangy potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except potatoes and mix well.
Add potatoes and toss gently to mix.
Place in serving bowl and smooth top of salad.
Garnish with sliced eggs.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: black-peppered maple cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a heavy saucepan whisk together cream and flour until smooth.
Add maple syrup, butter, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring over medium heat for 10 minutes or until thickened.
Do not let boil.
Pour filling into pie shell and bake for 30 minutes or until bubbling.
Cool on a rack, then refrigerate until thoroughly cooked before serving.

title: apple cheese cake
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour. Spread in bottom and sides of spring-form pan.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine
vegetables, salt and water.
Boil.
Add bouillon cubes.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add oleo and milk. Bring to a boil.
Season with pepper.

title: sausage cups
directions: Saute sausage, green pepper and onion together in skillet over medium heat until sausage is done. Add next eight ingredients and reduce heat to low. Stir until mixture thickens. Flake each biscuit into five parts and place in miniature muffin tins that have been sprayed with vegetable spray. Fill pastry shells with sausage mixture and bake at 375° for 10-12 minutes or until crust is brown. Remove to cooling rack.

title: baby squash
directions: Combine cheese and garlic salt.
Wash vegetables and roll wet vegetables in cheese mixture.
Place on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: salsa dip
directions: Take cream cheese and with bottom of spoon, spread evenly over 10-inch glass pie dish. Pour and spread salsa.
Sprinkle cheese on top of salsa.
Bake at 375° for approximately 25 to 30 minutes, until cheese is bubbly.

title: nachos supremos
directions: Crumble beef and chorizo into a skillet.
Add onion; cook until meat is browned.
Drain well.
Add hot pepper sauce.
Spread beans in a 15 x 10-inch or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread meat on top; sprinkle on chiles and cheeses.
Drizzle green chili salsa over all.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: favorite fresh fruit pie
directions: Fill the pie shell with fresh sliced fruit.
In a saucepan, stir cornstarch (dry) into sugar and slowly add the water.
Bring to a boil.
It will turn clear in consistency.
Remove from stove and quickly stir in the appropriate flavored jello.
Stir well. Pour mixture over the fresh fruit and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Serve with whipped cream if desired.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add the sugar; beat until stiff. Add chocolate chips and nuts, plus vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon onto foil covered cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 350° for 15 minutes.
Place cookie sheet in oven; turn off oven and forget. They're scrumptious!

title: seven layer casserole
directions: Spray 10 x 10-inch casserole dish with Pam

title: sue's chicken noodle soup
directions: Simmer all ingredients about 3 to 4 hours.
When chicken is tender, remove bones and skin, unless chicken tenders are used, then cut or tear chicken into small pieces.
Add noodles about 30 minutes prior to serving.

title: fake lasagne
directions: Layer zucchini, onions, green pepper and sausage.
Pour Ragu sauce over layers.
Top with shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: harry's oink stew
directions: Soak beans overnight in water.

Cook stock, meat, onions, celery and garlic. Add beans to stock; do not overcook when beans are tender. Add diced potatoes; cook for about 1/2 hour. Dice ham and hocks; add to finished soup. Let stand for 1/2 hour and then serve with homemade rolls and butter.

title: fudge
directions: For Chocolate/Peanut Butter Fudge:
Add 3 tablespoons cocoa.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, pour water over quick oats.
Allow to stand for 10 minutes.
Stir in granulated sugar, brown sugar and margarine.
Add eggs.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: homemade mayo
directions: Put egg, seasonings and vinegar plus 1/4 cup oil in blender. Blend briefly, then with blender operating, slowly pour in remaining oil; stop.
Stir mixture around blades and complete blending.
Use with raw veggies.
Bon appetit!!

title: french-fried onions
directions: Slice onion 1/8-inch thick, using only large middle slices. Separate rings and cover with ice water sweetened with sugar.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain thoroughly and wipe dry.
Combine flour, salt, oil and the 2/3 cup water.
Add oil and fold in beaten egg white.
Dip each onion ring in the batter and fry in deep, hot fat until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels and sprinkle with salt to taste.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together, except apples.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Put a light layer of batter and a layer of apples.
Sprinkle with lots of cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Repeat until all apples and batter are used.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: thing-ease
directions: Wrap 1/3 of slice of bacon around half of a water chestnut and secure with a toothpick.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Drain.

title: mini chip pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla in a large mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternating with milk to sugar mixture, beating just until smooth.
Stir in chips.
Pour into a well-greased and floured Bundt or 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Use only 1/2 cheese.
Blend soup and milk. Add all ingredients.
Pour in greased casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Roll out in small balls. Place on cookie sheet; press down with fork.
Cook for 12 to 15 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in water until tender.
Cut up cooked chicken and place in casserole dish.
Cook rice in broth from chicken.
Pour cooked rice over chicken.
Pour canned gravy over rice.
Mix margarine and stuffing mix; layer over top of gravy.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until hot.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add buttermilk; then nutmeg and butter. Pour in unbaked crust and bake together.
Best when hot.

title: cocktail beef bits
directions: Combine ground beef with all ingredients.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Saute in a small amount of oil in a skillet until well browned on all sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Combine ingredients for sauce and heat in a saucepan for 5 to 10 minutes, stirring gently.
Pour sauce over meatballs.
Serve hot.

title: cucumber pickles(sweet)
directions: Soak brined cukes in several changes of warm water to remove excess salt.
Use a large needle to puncture each cucumber near the end and at the center.
Cover with 1 part water and 3 parts vinegar.
Let it stand a week.

title: white chocolate candy
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave. Stir in cereal and peanuts. Drop with teaspoon on waxed paper. Allow to cool completely.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly; shape into 1-inch meatballs. Cook in 1/4 cup shortening until brown.
Remove; drain pan.

title: nutty banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together dry ingredients into large mixing bowl.
In separate bowl, mix oil, bananas, buttermilk and eggs.
Blend wet ingredients into dry ingredients and beat thoroughly.
Add orange peel and nuts.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix Nabisco Bran, boiling water and raisins.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and stir in buttermilk and soaked bran mixture.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt into mixture.
Add All-Bran and mix well.
Place in a large, covered container. Refrigerate.
Will keep for a month.
Dip out and place in greased muffin pan (do not stir!).
Fill pans 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: orange-poppy breakfast muffin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line twelve 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups with paper baking cups; set aside.
In small mixing bowl, sift together flour and baking powder; stir in poppy seed and orange peel and set aside.
