Using mixer, beat together eggs and granulated sugar until light and fluffy; add margarine and beat. Stir in flour mixture until moistened.
Spoon equal amount of batter into each cup.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes. Sift confectioners sugar over cupcakes.
Weight Watchers:
1 fat; 1/4 protein; 1/2 bread; 40 calories.

title: caramel kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rub cookie sheet with butter or margarine.
Beat the egg whites with the salt until stiff.
Sift the sugar and gradually add it to the beaten eggs, beating until smooth and thickened.
Fold in the vanilla and chopped nuts. Drop the mixture with a teaspoon about 1-inch apart onto the cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes until browned.

title: rice cake(puto)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Steam for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: scallop and cod casserole
directions: Cut scallops in half. Cut cod into bite size pieces (1 to 1 1/2-inch).
Drizzle fat-free margarine in bottom of casserole dish or in individual serving dishes.
Arrange cod and scallops in layers.
Sprinkle fish with lemon. Salt and pepper lightly (optional).
Cover bottom of dish with milk. Cover fish with a light layer of crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet 'n sour hot dogs
directions: Cut hog dogs into bite size pieces.
Separately heat the jelly, mustard and ketchup until the jelly melts.
Add hot dogs. Heat for 20 minutes.
Garnish with pineapple chunks and serve in chafing dish.

title: salsa
directions: Stir together all ingredients and refrigerate. Serve with corn chips or tortilla chips.

title: skillet chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients in iron skillet.
Beat egg yolks and add eggs and milk to dry ingredients.
Cook over medium to low heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour in already baked pie crust.
Top with meringue.
Bake in oven at 350° for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato
directions: Mix together the sweet potatoes, sugar, vanilla, eggs and 1/2 cup of the butter.
Place the mix in a 13 x 9 pan.
Mix the topping together of brown sugar, flour, pecans and the remaining 1/2 cup of butter.
Place the topping on top of the mix that is in the 13 x 9 pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add
egg
and
beat
well. Sift flour and cocoa.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour milk and water.
Add
vanilla.
Pour
into	2 floured and greased 8-inch cake pans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk.
Stir in flavorings.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan.
Set cake into cold oven.
Set temperature to 325° and bake 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger; add onion and green pepper, cook until tender. Add bacon and cook until limp.
Add remaining ingredients.
Do not cook.
Let sit overnight to develop best flavor.
Next day heat thoroughly.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 9 x 13-inch pan.
While hot, punch holes in cake with wooden spoon handle. Spread coconut cream and Eagle Brand over cake while hot.
When cool, spread Cool Whip and coconut on top of cake.

title: homemade ice cream (basic)
directions: For a 6-quart freezer, put 1 cup cream, eggs, 1 cup sugar and vanilla in blender.
Add 1 cup half and half.
Turn on lowest speed and blend until sugar is dissolved and creamy.
Add enough milk in freezer can until 2/3 full or up to full line.
Pack with ice and salt.
For 4-quart freezer, reduce amounts to 2 cups.

title: grandmother's corn pudding
directions: In a bowl, beat eggs and milk. Add corn and sugar. Mix well. Cut bread into 1/2-inch cubes and place in a greased 9-inch square baking dish. Pour egg mixture over bread. Dot with butter. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Yield: 9 servings.

title: mom's cream puffs
directions: Bring milk and butter to a fast boil in saucepan.
Add salt and flour, stirring rapidly, until mixture is smooth and forms a ball.
Remove from heat.
Cool approximately 30 minutes.

title: tuna-cheese twist
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet. Mix tuna, olives, celery, green pepper, onion and 1/4 cup of the soup.
Mix baking mix and 1/2 cup cold water until soft dough forms; beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Gently smooth dough into ball on floured cloth-covered board.
Knead 5 times.
Roll dough into rectangle, 14 x 11-inch; place on cookie sheet.
Spoon tuna mixture lengthwise down center of rectangle; sprinkle with 1 cup of the cheese.
Make cuts, 2 1/2 inches long at 1-inch intervals on 14 sides of rectangle.
Fold strips over filling.
Mix egg and 1 tablespoon water; brush over dough.
Bake until light brown, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: quick casserole
directions: Mix well, pour into buttered baking dish. Crush 1 tube Ritz crackers; sprinkle over mixture.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: mexicorn muffins
directions: In a bowl, combine corn bread mix, egg and milk until just blended. Stir in salsa, corn, cheese, sour cream, bacon and jalapeno peppers. Fill greased or paper lined muffin cups 3/4 full. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool 5 minutes before removing from pan to wire rack. Serve warm. Yields 1 dozen.

title: sirloin tips-n-gravy
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook all day or overnight on low.
Serve over rice.

title: white bean dip
directions: In a blender, combine all ingredients, except for the last one.
Cover and process until smooth.
Chill.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Set aside broth.
In a 9 x 12-inch baking dish, place a layer of tortillas that have been dipped in broth.
Layer pepper, onion, chicken and cheese.
Sprinkle 1/2 chili powder over top and repeat.
Combine soups and chilies.
Mix well and pour over layers.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: red pepper pasta
directions: Saute chopped peppers and onion in a bit of oil, preferably olive oil.
Add canned tomatoes and simmer 15 minutes until peppers are soft.
Puree at least half of the sauce and add back to remaining sauce.
Serve over cooked pasta.

title: barbecue chicken wings
directions: Rinse and dry chicken wings.
Cut into two sections/discard tips.
Bake at 375° in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 20 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Mix vanilla wafers and sugar, then add butter, milk, eggs, coconut and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: lemon cloud pie
directions: Beat together pudding mix, sugar, 1/4 cup water and egg in saucepan.
Mix in remaining 1 1/2 cups water.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Cool to room temperature, stirring occasionally.
When completely cool, whisk lightly.
Then fold in whipped topping and coconut.
Spread in crumb crust.
Refrigerate until set, about 40 minutes.

title: the ultimate chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Grease and flour bottom of pan.
Mix first 4 ingredients; set aside.
In a large bowl with mixer at high speed, beat next 3 ingredients 3 minutes or until light and fluffy (fluffy and light is okay, too).
At low speed, beat in the mayonnaise.
Add flour mixture in 4 parts, alternating with third of the water; begin and end with the flour mixture.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until the ol' toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan until you're bored looking at it, then remove and cool on rack.

title: sherry's taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add all ingredients except cheese.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 400° approximately 5 minutes.
Ready to eat with chips.
Use 8 x 12-inch Pyrex.

title: brownie delight
directions: Mix water, cocoa, margarine and oil in saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Pour over flour, sugar and salt.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla flavoring.
Pour into greased and floured pan, 11 x 17 x 1-inch or 2 x 9 x 13-inch.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
When you remove from oven, cake will bounce back when pressed in center.
Frost immediately!

title: yuletide toffee squares
directions: Grease a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Combine oats, brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup, vanilla and salt. Mix well.

title: granny's ketchup
directions: Combine ingredients, bring to a boil and cook in an iron skillet on low heat for 1/2 hour.

title: cabbage for a king
directions: Saute onion in margarine until tender.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Cook cabbage in salted water for 5 minutes. Lightly brown bread cubes in a tablespoon of margarine.
Arrange cabbage in layers, ending with bread and cheese.
Bake in moderate oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: potato soup
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan.
Add carrot and onion.
Cook until tender.
Blend in flour.
When bubbly, gradually stir in milk and bouillon cube.
When slightly thickened, add half of the potatoes.
Mash remaining potatoes and stir in with the parsley and other seasonings.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes; drain and mash.
Add cream cheese, sour cream, salt, pepper and garlic.
Blend well until smooth.
Stir in chopped chives.
Spoon into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: raw veggie dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill for 2 hours.
Serve with fresh veggies.

title: lettuce salad
directions: Make this the night before.
It has to be set overnight. Break up lettuce and put in a casserole dish.
Add peas, pepper and onion in layers.
Cover with mayonnaise.
Sprinkle cheese on top and finish with bacon.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to directions. Cook chopped onion in margarine until tender.
Remove from heat and add flour.
Drain mushrooms, saving the liquid.
Add sherry and enough chicken broth to measure 1 1/2 cups. Gradually stir into flour mixture.

Add light cream. Cook until mixture thickens. Add the wild rice, mushrooms, chicken, diced pimiento, parsley, salt and pepper. Place in a 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup slivered almonds. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: cooked dressing for potato salad
directions: Beat all with a wire whisk.
Cook all together until thick. Add milk if too thick.

title: vegetable beef and biscuit casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soups, water, mixed vegetables and Worcestershire sauce.
Spoon into 3 quart baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until hot and bubbling. Meanwhile, cut each biscuit into halves.
Remove dish from oven. Stir.
Arrange biscuits around the outside of mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake 8 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: 4 layered chocolate dessert
directions: Mix flour, pecans and margarine with pastry blender and pat in a 10-inch square Pyrex.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool completely.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and 1 cup Cool Whip and spread over first layer.
Whip together pudding mix and milk and spread over second layer.
Spread Cool Whip over third layer. Sprinkle with a few chopped pecans.
Chill for 24 hours.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill well.
Serve on any kind of crackers as a snack.

title: sunset  salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Measure 1 cup gelatin. Blend in yogurt.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan or mold.
Chill until set but not firm.
Add reserved liquid to remaining gelatin and chill until slightly thickened.
Arrange orange sections on top of set gelatin-yogurt layer.
Top with clear gelatin.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: In bowl mix egg yolks and all other ingredients.
(Save whites to beat until stiff and fold into mixture.) Fold in egg whites. Bake
in
greased
and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: homemade barbecue sauce
directions: Mix well and brush on your favorite meats.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Use large casserole.
Layer cooked broccoli and cooked chicken in pieces.
Mix chicken soup, lemon juice, mayonnaise and curry powder. Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle bread stuffing evenly, then sprinkle grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is browned.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: breaded okra
directions: Beat egg and milk together.
Dip salted okra in mixture and toss in flour.
Drop in hot oil and fry until golden brown.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine soup, sour cream and green chilies.
Heat through. Set aside.
Mix the chicken, onions and cheese in a bowl.
Spread a small amount of soup mix into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Fill tortillas with chicken mix and add about 1 tablespoon of soup mix. Roll tight and layer in pan.
Pour remaining sauce on top and sprinkle cheese over top.
Cover with foil and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: watergate salad or dessert
directions: Fold pudding mix in whipped topping.
Fold in remaining ingredients and chill.

title: new england boiled dinner
directions: Parboil vegetables until tender and place all in 9 x 13-inch pan, lined with foil and enough extra to fold over top.

title: campout cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In heavy cast-iron skillet, melt margarine.
Pour cherries into skillet.
Sprinkle sugar over cherries.
Shake pan to coat cherries.
Turn off heat.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add butter. Add eggs, Add milk & vanilla. Bake in unbaked pie shell 40-50 minutes. At 350°.

title: prune cake
directions: Bake in greased and floured Bundt cake pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: macaroni with tomatoes
directions: Cook
macaroni; rinse and drain.
Mash tomatoes and add 1/2 cup water, salt, pepper, catsup and sugar.
Cook approximately
5 minutes.
Add macaroni and 1/2 stick butter and heat thoroughly.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven
to
Melt
butter
in 12-inch skillet. Sprinkle
brown
sugar over butter.
Arrange pineapple halves, cherries and
pecans
over sugar mixture.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour evenly over fruit in skillet.
Bake 45 minutes
or
until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Invert at once onto serving plate.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Put spices and brown sugar into basket of large coffee maker. Add juices and water in bottom of coffee maker.
Turn coffee maker on and let perk until sugar is dissolved and spices have blended with juices.
Serve warm.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar, vanilla and oil.
Mix well. Stir in zucchini.
Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder. Blend with creamed mixture.
Fold in dry pudding, nuts and chocolate chips.
Put into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: peanut butter icing
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix in as much powdered sugar as it takes to make it spreadable.

title: baked french toast
directions: Lightly coat a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with Pam.
Arrange bread slices in bottom of pan.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well with whisk or egg beater.
Pour mixture evenly over bread slices. Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serves 10.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add flavorings.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk.
Do not overbeat. Pour into greased and floured tube pan; bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: grandma's potato salad
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients, then combine remaining ingredients.
Dice egg whites and add to potato mixture.
Mash egg yolks and stir into sour cream.
Keep separate and mix together 1/2 hour before serving.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Gradually stir in water.
Add mayonnaise and vanilla until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to package instructions.
Add pineapple juice to cake batter.
Combine brown sugar, butter and 2 tablespoons water in cast iron frypan and cook over low heat, stirring constantly.
Be careful not to scorch.
Remove from heat and arrange pineapple in sugar mixture.
Pour cake batter over arranged pineapple mixture Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until cake is done in center.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Beat egg; blend in soups (do not drain soups).
Add bread and cut up chicken.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Mix melted butter and crumbs.
Spread crumb mixture evenly over the top of noodle mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: beer batter fish
directions: Heat oil in deep frying pan.
Lightly coat fish with 3 to 4 tablespoons of Bisquick.
Mix 1 cup Bisquick, egg, salt, beer and lemon juice.
Dip fish into batter; let excess batter drip off. Fry fish until golden brown (about 2 minutes on each side).
Drain on paper towel.
Serve with tartar sauce.

title: ann's chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Mix and pour in casserole.
Pour chicken soup over top.
Bake for 40 minutes at 375°.

title: cora's pecan pie
directions: Add sugar to eggs.
Add salt, flour and Karo.
Roll nuts in flour and mix.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour to make paste.
Add stock slowly.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook only until it begins to thicken.
Add mayonnaise and chicken soup.
Place chicken and broccoli in casserole alternately.
Add sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan in order and cook at 250° until brown and bubbly.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Mix butter, brown sugar and pineapple slices and put in bottom of pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour in pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: grandma miller's baked cabbage
directions: Butter casserole dish. Cut up celery and onion in small pieces.
Saute in butter.
Slice up cabbage, removing the heart. Parboil it about 10 minutes. Beat eggs with a fork.
Add cubed bread, milk and seasonings.
Mix well all together in casserole. Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top and dot with butter.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Clean and chunk up broccoli.
Mix milk, Miracle Whip and sugar.
Always equal parts of these, whipped.
Combine all ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift together into a large bowl flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder, and salt. Stir in raisins and caraway seed. Combine buttermilk, eggs and melted shortening. Add liquid mixture to dry ingredients and mix well, until flour is just moistened. Turn batter into a 5 1/2 x 9 1/2-inch loaf pan. Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes until it starts to clear side of pan. Remove from pan immediately; allow to cool. May be frozen or kept in refrigerator for some time. Delicious toasted or as is.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream butter and cheese. Sift dry ingredients together. Add to butter and cheese. Shape into small balls. Press 1/2 pecan into each ball. Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 300° for about 30 minutes. Do not overcook.

title: soy mayonnaise #3
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients on high 10 to 15 seconds.
While still blending, slowly dribble in oil.
Continue blending 1 full minute after oil is added.
Stop blender and stir in lemon juice for 5 to 10 seconds.

title: refrigerator salad
directions: Drain peas, beans, sprouts and water chestnuts.
Mix peas, beans, sprouts, celery, water chestnuts and onion together.
Heat together salt, vinegar and sugar or sweetener.
Pour over mixed vegetables.
Place in airtight container and refrigerate overnight.

title: prune apple cake
directions: In a large bowl, beat sugar, oil and eggs for 2 minutes with mixer at medium speed.

title: broccoli and stuffing
directions: Fix stuffing according to directions; cook broccoli until almost done.
Use a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix soup and chicken with 1/2 can milk.
Layer in baking dish: stuffing, soup, broccoli and cheese.
I usually mix everything together and pour over stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry candy
directions: Mix, then add 1/2 cup chopped pecans and 1 cup flaked coconut. Mix all ingredients and refrigerate to chill.
Shape into strawberries.
Roll all except stem end in red decorator's sugar. Dip stem end in green decorator's sugar.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in cobbler dish.
Mix sugar, flour and milk thoroughly.
Add mixture to butter.
DO NOT STIR.
Spoon fruit onto mixture.
DO NOT STIR.
Sprinkle a little sugar on top.
Bake 40 minutes at 450°.

title: polynesian chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Roll chicken in mixture of the flour, salt and pepper; then place in pan and bake for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken pieces; top with peppers, onions, olives and pineapple chunks.
Rinse shrimp in cold water; add to chicken.
Combine tomato soup and pineapple juice (or water) and pour over chicken.
Cover pan with foil and bake 30 minutes more.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: easy potato chip dip
directions: Combine ingredients and refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Serve with chips.

title: banana butter
directions: Combine bananas, lemon juice, cherries and sugar in heavy pan; mix well.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and immediately stir in pectin.
Pour into jars.

title: slushy punch
directions: Mix and freeze 2 to 3 days in large container.
When ready to serve, remove from freezer and thaw 2 to 3 hours.
Add 3 quarts ginger ale.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt first 2 ingredients together in a double boiler.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 9 or 10-inch pie plate. Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion evenly over bottom of pie plate. Place remaining ingredients in blender.
Cover and blend on high speed for 1 minute.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Refrigerate any leftover quiche.
Makes 6 servings.

title: microwave southwest chili
directions: In 3-quart microwave casserole, combine onion, garlic and oil. Heat on High 4 minutes; stir once.
Add beef; cook on High 4 minutes.
Stir to break up lumps.
Cook 4 minutes.
Drain fat. Stir in remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Cook uncovered on High 5 minutes.
Stir; cook 15 minutes longer.

title: strawberry kiwi smoothies
directions: Peel kiwi, cut in quarters and freeze for 20 minutes or until frozen. Add all ingredients to blender. Blender will be full. Mix on low speed for 1-15 seconds. Remove lid and stir with wooden spoon. Mix on medium speed for 15-20 seconds, remove lid and stir again. Mix on high speed for 20-25 seconds, or until smooth. Pour into glasses. Serve immediately.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until tender and mix all ingredients except crackers and butter.
Mix Ritz crackers and butter and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake for 1 hour in a 375° oven.

title: dennis' quick beef stroganoff
directions: Flour the cubed steak and brown in the oil in a hot skillet. Do not drain.
Add onions and garlic.
Mix other ingredients, include the liquid from mushrooms, in large bowl and pour over meat and stir.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: pink stuff
directions: Drain pineapple.
In bowl mix cherry filling and sweetened condensed milk.
Add the pineapple and fold in cherry mixture. Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours.

title: texas macaroni salad
directions: Boil pasta as directed.
Drain; return to pot.
While still hot, add dressing. When cool, add veggies of choice.

title: chocolate covered rice krispies
directions: Heat sugar and Karo in a large saucepan until they begin to boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in peanut butter; mix in Rice Krispies.
Press mixture into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips until smooth.
Spread over Rice Krispies.
When cooled, cut into 48 bars.

title: easy croissants
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine 1 cup flour, yeast, sugar and salt; mix well.

In saucepan, heat 1 cup water, milk and 1/4 cup butter until about 120° to 130° (butter doesn't need to melt). Add to flour mixture. Blend at low speed until moistened; beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Set aside.

title: jesabell
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Let
set
for one day. Pour 1/4 cup over 8 ounces cream cheese.
Serve with crackers.

title: party ryes
directions: Mix together and top slices of bread. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hot rolls
directions: Heat milk and butter until butter is melted.
Add yeast, sugar, salt and 3 eggs (slightly beaten).
Mix well.
Let stand or rise until double in bulk, 2 or 3 hours.
Do not knead.
Make your rolls and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: orange colada
directions: In a blender container, combine first 4 ingredients.
Cover and process on high for 30 seconds.
Add ice and continue to blend until ice is liquefied.
Serve immediately with an orange slice. Yields 6 servings.

title: fruity cole slaw
directions: Drain pineapple.
Cut cabbage into small pieces.
Core, but do not peel apples and chop into small pieces.
Mix cabbage, apples, pineapple, raisins and nuts in a large bowl.
Add mayonnaise to desired thickness and sugar to taste.
Chill before serving.

title: twinkie dessert
directions: Place Twinkies in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add 7-Up, pineapple and ice cream.
Let thicken. Pour over Twinkies.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients together then blend with creamed sugar and shortening alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla and almond (or lemon) extracts.
Bake in greased tube or Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dipped shortbread
directions: Combine flour, butter, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Measure 1 teaspoon of dough, roll into 2 inch logs.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cool completely.
In a double boiler melt shortening and chocolate chips.
Dip one end of cookie into chocolate and roll in nuts or chocolate sprinkles.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Blend together in saucepan cornstarch, salt and 3/4 cup of juice drained from pineapple and cherries (objective, a smooth thin mixture).
When smooth, cook, stirring constantly until mixture is thickened; cool slightly.
Then stir in quartered marshmallows. Chill until somewhat thickened, then beat well using electric mixer.
Gently mix in crushed pineapple, chopped cherries and lemon juice.
Then fold in whipped cream.
Spoon into serving dishes and chill for at least 3 hours.
To garnish, top with chopped pecans.

title: 30 minute cake
directions: Sift together into a large mixing bowl flour, sugar and soda. Melt butter or oleo; add water and chocolate.
Bring to a boil and pour over flour mixture.
Beat eggs; combine eggs, buttermilk and vanilla and beat well.
Pour into a greased 12 1/4 x 14-inch pan and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until firm.
Cake will be moist.
Leave cake in pan.

title: aloha cake
directions: Mix cake as directed, except substitute pineapple juice for water.
Pour into cookie sheet, sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Bake 40 minutes in 350° oven. Add cheese to top after baking.
Return to oven to melt cheese.

title: potatoes o'brien
directions: In a large casserole dish, mix ingredients well.
Cover and bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 10 to 20 minutes to brown.

title: california seafood shell pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta.
Mix with dressing, herbs and chopped onions.
Mix well.
May be prepared several days ahead to this point.
Steam seafood lightly; separate into large bite-size chunks.
Add to pasta mixture with remaining ingredients and chill.
Shortly before serving, add to hollowed-out sourdough bread bowl.

title: hilda's texas cake(this is a cake children love.)
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Pour into a long cake pan or baking tray.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Soften cheese and mix with sausage. Add bisquick. Shape into balls. Flatten with a glass or roll out and cut small circles. Bake at 300° for 20 minutes. Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: gingerbread men
directions: Sift
together
the
flour,
baking
powder,
salt
and ginger.
Beat
egg well and combine with molasses, brown sugar and shortening; mix well.
Add dry ingredients and blend well. Wrap dough
in waxed paper and chill thoroughly.
Roll out 1/3 of the dough
at
a
time
on a lightly floured board to about 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut
with
cookie
cutter
in
shape
of gingerbread man.
Bake
on greased cookie sheet in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
(If dough does not appear stiff enough, add additional 1/4 cup sifted flour.)

title: cucumber spread
directions: Pare cucumber, cut lengthwise and remove seeds.
Chop.
Should be 1 cup.
Add onions and eggs.
Moisten with mayonnaise to spreading consistency.
Season to taste.
Spread on buttered bread.
Garnish with paprika.

title: green chili stew
directions: Brown meat and potatoes together; stir to prevent sticking. Add green chili, tomatoes, beans, garlic, onion flakes and water. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or longer. Recipe is not fussy and flavors blend if cooked longer.
Serve with flour tortillas warmed and folded in fourths.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: ranchero beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients and mix together.
Pour into covered casserole and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: linzer muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease twelve 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups.
Whisk together melted butter, milk, egg and almond extract. Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon in separate bowl.
Stir wet ingredients into dry ingredients.
Spoon batter evenly into muffin cups, filling each about three-quarters full.
After filling cups, insert 1/2 teaspoon raspberry jam into each.
Bake 20 to 22 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center of muffin comes out clean.
After baking, sift on 1 tablespoon confectioners sugar.

title: pretzel saladcrust for 9 x 12-inch pan
directions: Crush enough pretzels to cover the bottom of the pan, not too fine, just break small.
Mix with the melted margarine and 3 teaspoons of sugar.
Press into the bottom of the pan to form the crust. Bake at 400° for 8 minutes, let cool.

title: debbie's tasty chocolate chip cookies(extra large recipe)
directions: Beat ingredients until creamy.
Drop on a cookie sheet and bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate layer dessert
directions: You will also need 1 large bowl.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all
ingredients.
Pour
into
a 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake at 425° until knife comes out clean.

title: fig preserves
directions: Put figs in pan with the soda.
Cover figs with boiling water. Let stand for 5 minutes.
Pour off soda water and rinse with cold water several times.
Boil sugar and water; add figs and cook until figs are transparent.
Place in sterilized jars and seal.

title: low-fat granola cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in egg and vanilla.
Add flour and salt.
Refrigerate dough for 3 to 4 hours.
Roll and cut into cross shapes.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes in 350° oven.
Sprinkle with sherry while still warm. Makes 40 to 50 (2-inch) cookies.

title: pot de cremes
directions: Heat milk just to boiling point.
Put other ingredients in blender.
Pour hot milk over ingredients and blend for 1 minute. Pour into demitasse cups or other small dishes.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Serve with whipped cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: buttermilk scones
directions: Cut butter into dry ingredients until evenly mixed.
Add orange peel and raisins; stir well.
Mix buttermilk, 1 egg and extract together, then add all at once to flour mixture; stir until blended.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Melt margarine.
Add mustard, poppy seed, salt and chopped onion.
Mix well.
Slice through rolls.
Put slice of ham and slice of cheese.
Put half of rolls on.
Pour mixture over rolls and bake for 15 minutes.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Place sugar, egg whites, salt, water and cream of tartar in saucepan over low heat.
Stir well.
Beat with rotary egg beater until mixture stands in peaks.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla. Continue beating until cool.
Spread on cakes.
Covers 2 (8-inch) layer cakes.

title: healthy hash browns
directions: Cut potatoes and onion in 1/2-inch cubes.
Chop up garlic cloves.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in 10-inch nonstick frying pan. Add ingredients to pan; set heat at medium-high and lightly stir to cover them with oil.
Season lightly with salt and heavily with ground pepper.
Cook, covered, 10 minutes.
Cook uncovered, for 10 minutes, turning hash browns over several times to brown evenly. Serve hot.

title: old fashioned cole slaw
directions: Soak shredded cabbage in ice water.
Drain and wrap in towel to crisp.
Sprinkle with salt.
Moisten with salad dressing or modified mayonnaise.
Add sugar, onion, vinegar, cream and mustard or mustardy salad dressing.
Toss together; chill and serve.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Mix all other ingredients together. Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Cool and serve.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: In a 2-quart bowl, mix boned chicken, cream of chicken soup and cream.
In a casserole dish, tear six tortilla shells into small pieces.
Pour half of mixture over shells.
Tear 6 remaining shells over this.
Pour remaining mixture on top.
Sprinkle with chopped green chilies and cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and cheese is melted.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
To freeze, do not cook prior to freezing.

title: corn meal cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix flour with water. Add all the rest of ingredients. Cook on top stove until thick or smooth consistency.
This is good on Ribs or BBQ Beef.

title: pud's marinated carrots
directions: Boil carrots for 5 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Combine with remaining ingredients and refrigerate 24 hours.
Serve as a cold side dish.

title: snowballs
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together.
Sift flour.
Add salt and re-sift.
Add to creamed mixture, working it thoroughly with fingers.
Work in vanilla and nuts or coconut.
Chill about 1 hour, then roll about 1-inch in diameter.
Cut 1-inch lengths and roll into balls.
Place on lightly greased pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 14 to 17 minutes or until lightly browned.
Roll in confectioners sugar when cooled.
